https://schema.org/legislationPassedBy.label: legislationPassedBy
https://schema.org/legislationPassedBy.description: The person or organization that originally passed or made the law: typically parliament (for primary legislation) or government (for secondary legislation). This indicates the "legal author" of the law, as opposed to its physical author.

https://schema.org/Conversation.label: Conversation
https://schema.org/Conversation.description: One or more messages between organizations or people on a particular topic. Individual messages can be linked to the conversation with isPartOf or hasPart properties.

https://schema.org/WatchAction.label: WatchAction
https://schema.org/WatchAction.description: The act of consuming dynamic/moving visual content.

https://schema.org/funding.label: funding
https://schema.org/funding.description: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

https://schema.org/valuePattern.label: valuePattern
https://schema.org/valuePattern.description: Specifies a regular expression for testing literal values according to the HTML spec.

https://schema.org/provider.label: provider
https://schema.org/provider.description: The service provider, service operator, or service performer; the goods producer. Another party (a seller) may offer those services or goods on behalf of the provider. A provider may also serve as the seller.

https://schema.org/honorificPrefix.label: honorificPrefix
https://schema.org/honorificPrefix.description: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

https://schema.org/modifiedTime.label: modifiedTime
https://schema.org/modifiedTime.description: The date and time the reservation was modified.

https://schema.org/numberOfCredits.label: numberOfCredits
https://schema.org/numberOfCredits.description: The number of credits or units awarded by a Course or required to complete an EducationalOccupationalProgram.

https://schema.org/AnalysisNewsArticle.label: AnalysisNewsArticle
https://schema.org/AnalysisNewsArticle.description: An AnalysisNewsArticle is a [[NewsArticle]] that, while based on factual reporting, incorporates the expertise of the author/producer, offering interpretations and conclusions.

https://schema.org/Room.label: Room
https://schema.org/Room.description:
A room is a distinguishable space within a structure, usually separated from other spaces by interior walls (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/WearableSizeGroupEnum.label: WearableSizeGroupEnumeration
https://schema.org/WearableSizeGroupEnum.description: Enumerates common size groups (also known as "size types") for wearable products.

https://schema.org/noBylinesPolicy.label: noBylinesPolicy
https://schema.org/noBylinesPolicy.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement explaining when authors of articles are not named in bylines.

https://schema.org/genre.label: genre
https://schema.org/genre.description: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

https://schema.org/sameAs.label: sameAs
https://schema.org/sameAs.description: URL of a reference Web page that unambiguously indicates the item's identity. E.g. the URL of the item's Wikipedia page, Wikidata entry, or official website.
https://schema.org/sameAs.usage_hint: URL of a reference page that identifies the item (Wikipedia, Wikidata, official site).
https://schema.org/sameAs.example_keywords: same as, equivalent, identical to, also known as URL

https://schema.org/wordCount.label: wordCount
https://schema.org/wordCount.description: The number of words in the text of the CreativeWork such as an Article, Book, etc.

https://schema.org/recommendedIntake.label: recommendedIntake
https://schema.org/recommendedIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

https://schema.org/isGift.label: isGift
https://schema.org/isGift.description: Indicates whether the offer was accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.

https://schema.org/interactingDrug.label: interactingDrug
https://schema.org/interactingDrug.description: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.

https://schema.org/experienceInPlaceOfEd.label: experienceInPlaceOfEducation
https://schema.org/experienceInPlaceOfEd.description: Indicates whether a [[JobPosting]] will accept experience (as indicated by [[OccupationalExperienceRequirements]]) in place of its formal educational qualifications (as indicated by [[educationRequirements]]). If true, indicates that satisfying one of these requirements is sufficient.

https://schema.org/isProprietary.label: isProprietary
https://schema.org/isProprietary.description: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).

https://schema.org/CriticReview.label: CriticReview
https://schema.org/CriticReview.description: A [[CriticReview]] is a more specialized form of Review written or published by a source that is recognized for its reviewing activities. These can include online columns, travel and food guides, TV and radio shows, blogs and other independent Web sites. [[CriticReview]]s are typically more in-depth and professionally written. For simpler, casually written user/visitor/viewer/customer reviews, it is more appropriate to use the [[UserReview]] type. Review aggregator sites such as Metacritic alrea

https://schema.org/CompleteDataFeed.label: CompleteDataFeed
https://schema.org/CompleteDataFeed.description:
A [[CompleteDataFeed]] is a [[DataFeed]] whose standard representation includes content for every item currently in the feed.

This is the equivalent of Atom's element as defined in Feed Paging and Archiving [RFC 5005](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5005), for example (and as defined for Atom), when using data from a feed that represents a collection of items that varies over time (e.g. "Top Twenty Records") there is no need to have newer entries mixed in alongside older, obsolete entries. By ma

https://schema.org/accessModeSufficient.label: accessModeSufficient
https://schema.org/accessModeSufficient.description: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessModeSufficient-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/breadcrumb.label: breadcrumb
https://schema.org/breadcrumb.description: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.

https://schema.org/recordedAs.label: recordedAs
https://schema.org/recordedAs.description: An audio recording of the work.

https://schema.org/IPTCDigitalSourceEnum.label: IPTCDigitalSourceEnumeration
https://schema.org/IPTCDigitalSourceEnum.description: IPTC "Digital Source" codes for use with the [[digitalSourceType]] property, providing information about the source for a digital media object. In general these codes are not declared here to be mutually exclusive, although some combinations would be contradictory if applied simultaneously, or might be considered mutually incompatible by upstream maintainers of the definitions. See the IPTC

https://schema.org/LeaveAction.label: LeaveAction
https://schema.org/LeaveAction.description:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: The antonym of LeaveAction.
* [[UnRegisterAction]]: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

https://schema.org/vehicleConfiguration.label: vehicleConfiguration
https://schema.org/vehicleConfiguration.description: A short text indicating the configuration of the vehicle, e.g. '5dr hatchback ST 2.5 MT 225 hp' or 'limited edition'.

https://schema.org/BoatReservation.label: BoatReservation
https://schema.org/BoatReservation.description:
A reservation for boat travel.

Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/orderItemNumber.label: orderItemNumber
https://schema.org/orderItemNumber.description: The identifier of the order item.

https://schema.org/legislationIdentifier.label: legislationIdentifier
https://schema.org/legislationIdentifier.description: An identifier for the legislation. This can be either a string-based identifier, like the CELEX at EU level or the NOR in France, or a web-based, URL/URI identifier, like an ELI (European Legislation Identifier) or an URN-Lex.

https://schema.org/weightTotal.label: weightTotal
https://schema.org/weightTotal.description:
The permitted total weight of the loaded vehicle, including passengers and cargo and the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/numberOfFullBathrooms.label: numberOfFullBathrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfFullBathrooms.description: Number of full bathrooms - The total number of full and ¾ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsFull field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsFull+Field).

https://schema.org/readBy.label: readBy
https://schema.org/readBy.description: A person who reads (performs) the audiobook.

https://schema.org/Diet.label: Diet
https://schema.org/Diet.description: A strategy of regulating the intake of food to achieve or maintain a specific health-related goal.

https://schema.org/readonlyValue.label: readonlyValue
https://schema.org/readonlyValue.description: Whether or not a property is mutable.  Default is false. Specifying this for a property that also has a value makes it act similar to a "hidden" input in an HTML form.

https://schema.org/containsSeason.label: containsSeason
https://schema.org/containsSeason.description: A season that is part of the media series.

https://schema.org/legislationCommences.label: legislationCommences
https://schema.org/legislationCommences.description: Another legislation that this one sets into force.

https://schema.org/pickupTime.label: pickupTime
https://schema.org/pickupTime.description: When a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

https://schema.org/hoursAvailable.label: hoursAvailable
https://schema.org/hoursAvailable.description: The hours during which this service or contact is available.

https://schema.org/Certification.label: Certification
https://schema.org/Certification.description: A Certification is an official and authoritative statement about a subject, for example a product, service, person, or organization. A certification is typically issued by an indendent certification body, for example a professional organization or government. It formally attests certain characteristics about the subject, for example Organizations can be ISO certified, Food products can be certified Organic or Vegan, a Person can be a certified professional, a Place can be certified for food proc

https://schema.org/MedicalRiskFactor.label: MedicalRiskFactor
https://schema.org/MedicalRiskFactor.description: A risk factor is anything that increases a person's likelihood of developing or contracting a disease, medical condition, or complication.

https://schema.org/targetPlatform.label: targetPlatform
https://schema.org/targetPlatform.description: Type of app development: phone, Metro style, desktop, XBox, etc.

https://schema.org/Continent.label: Continent
https://schema.org/Continent.description: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

https://schema.org/connectedTo.label: connectedTo
https://schema.org/connectedTo.description: Other anatomical structures to which this structure is connected.

https://schema.org/TVSeason.label: TVSeason
https://schema.org/TVSeason.description: Season dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

https://schema.org/ProductCollection.label: ProductCollection
https://schema.org/ProductCollection.description: A set of products (either [[ProductGroup]]s or specific variants) that are listed together e.g. in an [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/VideoObjectSnapshot.label: VideoObjectSnapshot
https://schema.org/VideoObjectSnapshot.description: A specific and exact (byte-for-byte) version of a [[VideoObject]]. Two byte-for-byte identical files, for the purposes of this type, considered identical. If they have different embedded metadata the files will differ. Different external facts about the files, e.g. creator or dateCreated that aren't represented in their actual content, do not affect this notion of identity.

https://schema.org/cvdNumBedsOcc.label: cvdNumBedsOcc
https://schema.org/cvdNumBedsOcc.description: numbedsocc - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient beds that are occupied.

https://schema.org/nonEqual.label: nonEqual
https://schema.org/nonEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

https://schema.org/qualifiedExpense.label: qualifiedExpense
https://schema.org/qualifiedExpense.description: Optional. The types of expenses that are covered by the incentive. For example some incentives are only for the goods (tangible items) but the services (labor) are excluded.

https://schema.org/MusicRecording.label: MusicRecording
https://schema.org/MusicRecording.description: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

https://schema.org/paymentUrl.label: paymentUrl
https://schema.org/paymentUrl.description: The URL for sending a payment.

https://schema.org/acquireLicensePage.label: acquireLicensePage
https://schema.org/acquireLicensePage.description: Indicates a page documenting how licenses can be purchased or otherwise acquired, for the current item.

https://schema.org/hasRepresentation.label: hasRepresentation
https://schema.org/hasRepresentation.description: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.

https://schema.org/suggestedMinAge.label: suggestedMinAge
https://schema.org/suggestedMinAge.description: Minimum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

https://schema.org/3DModel.label: 3DModel
https://schema.org/3DModel.description:
A 3D model represents some kind of 3D content, which may have [[encoding]]s in one or more [[MediaObject]]s. Many 3D formats are available (e.g. see [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Category:3D_graphics_file_formats)); specific encoding formats can be represented using the [[encodingFormat]] property applied to the relevant [[MediaObject]]. For the
case of a single file published after Zip compression, the convention of appending '+zip' to the [[encodingFormat]] can be used. Geospatial,

https://schema.org/polygon.label: polygon
https://schema.org/polygon.description: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.

https://schema.org/duration.label: duration
https://schema.org/duration.description: The duration of the item (movie, audio recording, event, etc.) in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/SchoolDistrict.label: SchoolDistrict
https://schema.org/SchoolDistrict.description: A School District is an administrative area for the administration of schools.

https://schema.org/maximumEnrollment.label: maximumEnrollment
https://schema.org/maximumEnrollment.description: The maximum number of students who may be enrolled in the program.

https://schema.org/numberOfForwardGears.label: numberOfForwardGears
https://schema.org/numberOfForwardGears.description: The total number of forward gears available for the transmission system of the vehicle.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

https://schema.org/DateTime.label: DateTime
https://schema.org/DateTime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see Chapter 5.4 of ISO 8601).

https://schema.org/taxonRank.label: taxonRank
https://schema.org/taxonRank.description: The taxonomic rank of this taxon given preferably as a URI from a controlled vocabulary – typically the ranks from TDWG TaxonRank ontology or equivalent Wikidata URIs.

https://schema.org/actionPlatform.label: actionPlatform
https://schema.org/actionPlatform.description: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.

https://schema.org/AggregateOffer.label: AggregateOffer
https://schema.org/AggregateOffer.description: When a single product is associated with multiple offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.\n\nNote: AggregateOffers are normally expected to associate multiple offers that all share the same defined [[businessFunction]] value, or default to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell if businessFunction is not explicitly defined.

https://schema.org/BroadcastFrequencySpe.label: BroadcastFrequencySpecification
https://schema.org/BroadcastFrequencySpe.description: The frequency in MHz and the modulation used for a particular BroadcastService.

https://schema.org/Manuscript.label: Manuscript
https://schema.org/Manuscript.description: A book, document, or piece of music written by hand rather than typed or printed.

https://schema.org/numTracks.label: numTracks
https://schema.org/numTracks.description: The number of tracks in this album or playlist.

https://schema.org/legislationLegalValue.label: legislationLegalValue
https://schema.org/legislationLegalValue.description: The legal value of this legislation file. The same legislation can be written in multiple files with different legal values. Typically a digitally signed PDF have a "stronger" legal value than the HTML file of the same act.

https://schema.org/sensoryRequirement.label: sensoryRequirement
https://schema.org/sensoryRequirement.description: A description of any sensory requirements and levels necessary to function on the job, including hearing and vision. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

https://schema.org/hasDefinedTerm.label: hasDefinedTerm
https://schema.org/hasDefinedTerm.description: A Defined Term contained in this term set.

https://schema.org/GovernmentPermit.label: GovernmentPermit
https://schema.org/GovernmentPermit.description: A permit issued by a government agency.

https://schema.org/geoCovers.label: geoCovers
https://schema.org/geoCovers.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/mathExpression.label: mathExpression
https://schema.org/mathExpression.description: A mathematical expression (e.g. 'x^2-3x=0') that may be solved for a specific variable, simplified, or transformed. This can take many formats, e.g. LaTeX, Ascii-Math, or math as you would write with a keyboard.

https://schema.org/lender.label: lender
https://schema.org/lender.description: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

https://schema.org/currency.label: currency
https://schema.org/currency.description: The currency in which the monetary amount is expressed.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/temporalCoverage.label: temporalCoverage
https://schema.org/temporalCoverage.description:
The temporalCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the period that the content applies to, i.e. that it describes, either as a DateTime or as a textual string indicating a time period in [ISO 8601 time interval format](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Time_intervals). In
      the case of a Dataset it will typically indicate the relevant time period in a precise notation (e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 would be written "2011/2012"). Other forms of content, e.g. ScholarlyArticl

https://schema.org/PaymentCard.label: PaymentCard
https://schema.org/PaymentCard.description: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.

https://schema.org/shippingDetails.label: shippingDetails
https://schema.org/shippingDetails.description: Indicates information about the shipping policies and options associated with an [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/specialOpeningHoursSp.label: specialOpeningHoursSpecification
https://schema.org/specialOpeningHoursSp.description: The special opening hours of a certain place.\n\nUse this to explicitly override general opening hours brought in scope by [[openingHoursSpecification]] or [[openingHours]].

https://schema.org/publicAccess.label: publicAccess
https://schema.org/publicAccess.description: A flag to signal that the [[Place]] is open to public visitors.  If this property is omitted there is no assumed default boolean value.

https://schema.org/structuralClass.label: structuralClass
https://schema.org/structuralClass.description: The name given to how bone physically connects to each other.

https://schema.org/smokingAllowed.label: smokingAllowed
https://schema.org/smokingAllowed.description: Indicates whether it is allowed to smoke in the place, e.g. in the restaurant, hotel or hotel room.

https://schema.org/UserTweets.label: UserTweets
https://schema.org/UserTweets.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/currenciesAccepted.label: currenciesAccepted
https://schema.org/currenciesAccepted.description: The currency accepted.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/publisher.label: publisher
https://schema.org/publisher.description: The publisher of the article in question.

https://schema.org/targetUrl.label: targetUrl
https://schema.org/targetUrl.description: The URL of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/endOffset.label: endOffset
https://schema.org/endOffset.description: The end time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

https://schema.org/eligibleDuration.label: eligibleDuration
https://schema.org/eligibleDuration.description: The duration for which the given offer is valid.

https://schema.org/costCurrency.label: costCurrency
https://schema.org/costCurrency.description: The currency (in 3-letter) of the drug cost. See: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217.

https://schema.org/hasMeasurement.label: hasMeasurement
https://schema.org/hasMeasurement.description: A measurement of an item, For example, the inseam of pants, the wheel size of a bicycle, the gauge of a screw, or the carbon footprint measured for certification by an authority. Usually an exact measurement, but can also be a range of measurements for adjustable products, for example belts and ski bindings.

https://schema.org/runtime.label: runtime
https://schema.org/runtime.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

https://schema.org/serviceAudience.label: serviceAudience
https://schema.org/serviceAudience.description: The audience eligible for this service.

https://schema.org/vehicleTransmission.label: vehicleTransmission
https://schema.org/vehicleTransmission.description: The type of component used for transmitting the power from a rotating power source to the wheels or other relevant component(s) ("gearbox" for cars).

https://schema.org/QAPage.label: QAPage
https://schema.org/QAPage.description: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

https://schema.org/ParkingFacility.label: ParkingFacility
https://schema.org/ParkingFacility.description: A parking lot or other parking facility.

https://schema.org/reportNumber.label: reportNumber
https://schema.org/reportNumber.description: The number or other unique designator assigned to a Report by the publishing organization.

https://schema.org/exerciseCourse.label: exerciseCourse
https://schema.org/exerciseCourse.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

https://schema.org/HowToSection.label: HowToSection
https://schema.org/HowToSection.description: A sub-grouping of steps in the instructions for how to achieve a result (e.g. steps for making a pie crust within a pie recipe).

https://schema.org/seasons.label: seasons
https://schema.org/seasons.description: A season in a media series.

https://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.label: knownVehicleDamages
https://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.description: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.

https://schema.org/warranty.label: warranty
https://schema.org/warranty.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

https://schema.org/CampingPitch.label: CampingPitch
https://schema.org/CampingPitch.description:
A [[CampingPitch]] is an individual place for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically being part of a larger camping site, or [[Campground]].\n\n
In British English a campsite, or campground, is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individua

https://schema.org/distribution.label: distribution
https://schema.org/distribution.description: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format. This property can be repeated if different variations are available. There is no expectation that different downloadable distributions must contain exactly equivalent information (see also [DCAT](https://www.w3.org/TR/vocab-dcat-3/#Class:Distribution) on this point). Different distributions might include or exclude different subsets of the entire dataset, for example.

https://schema.org/MapCategoryType.label: MapCategoryType
https://schema.org/MapCategoryType.description: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

https://schema.org/TextObject.label: TextObject
https://schema.org/TextObject.description: A text file. The text can be unformatted or contain markup, html, etc.

https://schema.org/actionAccessibilityRe.label: actionAccessibilityRequirement
https://schema.org/actionAccessibilityRe.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action. If more than one value is specified, fulfilling one set of requirements will allow the Action to be performed.

https://schema.org/numberOfAccommodation.label: numberOfAccommodationUnits
https://schema.org/numberOfAccommodation.description: Indicates the total (available plus unavailable) number of accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits]].

https://schema.org/weight.label: weight
https://schema.org/weight.description: The weight of the product or person.

https://schema.org/SiteNavigationElement.label: SiteNavigationElement
https://schema.org/SiteNavigationElement.description: A navigation element of the page.

https://schema.org/associatedArticle.label: associatedArticle
https://schema.org/associatedArticle.description: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.

https://schema.org/commentTime.label: commentTime
https://schema.org/commentTime.description: The time at which the UserComment was made.

https://schema.org/awards.label: awards
https://schema.org/awards.description: Awards won by or for this item.

https://schema.org/steeringPosition.label: steeringPosition
https://schema.org/steeringPosition.description: The position of the steering wheel or similar device (mostly for cars).

https://schema.org/AssignAction.label: AssignAction
https://schema.org/AssignAction.description: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

https://schema.org/legislationConsolidat.label: legislationConsolidates
https://schema.org/legislationConsolidat.description: Indicates another legislation taken into account in this consolidated legislation (which is usually the product of an editorial process that revises the legislation). This property should be used multiple times to refer to both the original version or the previous consolidated version, and to the legislations making the change.

https://schema.org/hasEnergyEfficiencyCa.label: hasEnergyEfficiencyCategory
https://schema.org/hasEnergyEfficiencyCa.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (which could be either a rating out of range of values or a yes/no certification) for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

https://schema.org/RealEstateListing.label: RealEstateListing
https://schema.org/RealEstateListing.description:
A [[RealEstateListing]] is a listing that describes one or more real-estate [[Offer]]s (whose [[businessFunction]] is typically to lease out, or to sell).
  The [[RealEstateListing]] type itself represents the overall listing, as manifested in some [[WebPage]].

https://schema.org/reservationFor.label: reservationFor
https://schema.org/reservationFor.description: The thing -- flight, event, restaurant, etc. being reserved.

https://schema.org/DigitalDocumentPermis.label: DigitalDocumentPermission
https://schema.org/DigitalDocumentPermis.description: A permission for a particular person or group to access a particular file.

https://schema.org/SomeProducts.label: SomeProducts
https://schema.org/SomeProducts.description: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

https://schema.org/cssSelector.label: cssSelector
https://schema.org/cssSelector.description: A CSS selector, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

https://schema.org/DiscoverAction.label: DiscoverAction
https://schema.org/DiscoverAction.description: The act of discovering/finding an object.

https://schema.org/proficiencyLevel.label: proficiencyLevel
https://schema.org/proficiencyLevel.description: Proficiency needed for this content; expected values: 'Beginner', 'Expert'.

https://schema.org/question.label: question
https://schema.org/question.description: A sub property of object. A question.

https://schema.org/thumbnail.label: thumbnail
https://schema.org/thumbnail.description: Thumbnail image for an image or video.

https://schema.org/TaxiReservation.label: TaxiReservation
https://schema.org/TaxiReservation.description: A reservation for a taxi.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/Event.label: Event
https://schema.org/Event.description: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the [[offers]] property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.
https://schema.org/Event.usage_hint: Type for events with dates/locations. Use schema:startDate, schema:endDate, schema:location.
https://schema.org/Event.example_keywords: event, conference, ceremony, meeting, occurrence, happened

https://schema.org/strengthUnit.label: strengthUnit
https://schema.org/strengthUnit.description: The units of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. mg.

https://schema.org/propertyID.label: propertyID
https://schema.org/propertyID.description:
A commonly used identifier for the characteristic represented by the property, e.g. a manufacturer or a standard code for a property. propertyID can be
(1) a prefixed string, mainly meant to be used with standards for product properties; (2) a site-specific, non-prefixed string (e.g. the primary key of the property or the vendor-specific ID of the property), or (3)
a URL indicating the type of the property, either pointing to an external vocabulary, or a Web resource that describes the property

https://schema.org/RuntimePlatform.label: RuntimePlatform
https://schema.org/RuntimePlatform.description: Specialized software environment that provides the essential infrastructure, libraries, and services required to execute a program.

https://schema.org/AdministrativeArea.label: AdministrativeArea
https://schema.org/AdministrativeArea.description: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

https://schema.org/Patient.label: Patient
https://schema.org/Patient.description: A patient is any person recipient of health care services.

https://schema.org/servicePostalAddress.label: servicePostalAddress
https://schema.org/servicePostalAddress.description: The address for accessing the service by mail.

https://schema.org/Permit.label: Permit
https://schema.org/Permit.description: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

https://schema.org/PlayAction.label: PlayAction
https://schema.org/PlayAction.description:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, competition or exercise.

Related actions:

* [[ListenAction]]: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
* [[WatchAction]]: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

https://schema.org/billingDuration.label: billingDuration
https://schema.org/billingDuration.description: Specifies for how long this price (or price component) will be billed. Can be used, for example, to model the contractual duration of a subscription or payment plan. Type can be either a Duration or a Number (in which case the unit of measurement, for example month, is specified by the unitCode property).

https://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGue.label: additionalNumberOfGuests
https://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGue.description: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.

https://schema.org/thumbnailUrl.label: thumbnailUrl
https://schema.org/thumbnailUrl.description: A thumbnail image relevant to the Thing.

https://schema.org/mediaAuthenticityCate.label: mediaAuthenticityCategory
https://schema.org/mediaAuthenticityCate.description: Indicates a MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration classification of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared).

https://schema.org/geoOverlaps.label: geoOverlaps
https://schema.org/geoOverlaps.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/inAlbum.label: inAlbum
https://schema.org/inAlbum.description: The album to which this recording belongs.

https://schema.org/Protein.label: Protein
https://schema.org/Protein.description: Protein is here used in its widest possible definition, as classes of amino acid based molecules. Amyloid-beta Protein in human (UniProt P05067), eukaryota (e.g. an OrthoDB group) or even a single molecule that one can point to are all of type :Protein. A protein can thus be a subclass of another protein, e.g. :Protein as a UniProt record can have multiple isoforms inside it which would also be :Protein. They can be imagined, synthetic, hypothetical or naturally occurring.

https://schema.org/MotorizedBicycle.label: MotorizedBicycle
https://schema.org/MotorizedBicycle.description: A motorized bicycle is a bicycle with an attached motor used to power the vehicle, or to assist with pedaling.

https://schema.org/MedicalIndication.label: MedicalIndication
https://schema.org/MedicalIndication.description: A condition or factor that indicates use of a medical therapy, including signs, symptoms, risk factors, anatomical states, etc.

https://schema.org/commentCount.label: commentCount
https://schema.org/commentCount.description: The number of comments this CreativeWork (e.g. Article, Question or Answer) has received. This is most applicable to works published in Web sites with commenting system; additional comments may exist elsewhere.

https://schema.org/BusinessAudience.label: BusinessAudience
https://schema.org/BusinessAudience.description: A set of characteristics belonging to businesses, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

https://schema.org/availableThrough.label: availableThrough
https://schema.org/availableThrough.description: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.

https://schema.org/busNumber.label: busNumber
https://schema.org/busNumber.description: The unique identifier for the bus.

https://schema.org/Guide.label: Guide
https://schema.org/Guide.description: [[Guide]] is a page or article that recommends specific products or services, or aspects of a thing for a user to consider. A [[Guide]] may represent a Buying Guide and detail aspects of products or services for a user to consider. A [[Guide]] may represent a Product Guide and recommend specific products or services. A [[Guide]] may represent a Ranked List and recommend specific products or services with ranking.

https://schema.org/guidelineSubject.label: guidelineSubject
https://schema.org/guidelineSubject.description: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.

https://schema.org/TheaterGroup.label: TheaterGroup
https://schema.org/TheaterGroup.description: A theater group or company, for example, the Royal Shakespeare Company or Druid Theatre.

https://schema.org/refundType.label: refundType
https://schema.org/refundType.description: A refund type, from an enumerated list.

https://schema.org/Apartment.label: Apartment
https://schema.org/Apartment.description: An apartment (in American English) or flat (in British English) is a self-contained housing unit (a type of residential real estate) that occupies only part of a building (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apartment).

https://schema.org/addressCountry.label: addressCountry
https://schema.org/addressCountry.description: The country. Recommended to be in 2-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1) format, for example "US". For backward compatibility, a 3-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-3](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1_alpha-3) country code such as "SGP" or a full country name such as "Singapore" can also be used.

https://schema.org/catalog.label: catalog
https://schema.org/catalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

https://schema.org/customer.label: customer
https://schema.org/customer.description: Party placing the order or paying the invoice.

https://schema.org/hasMenuItem.label: hasMenuItem
https://schema.org/hasMenuItem.description: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.

https://schema.org/displayLocation.label: displayLocation
https://schema.org/displayLocation.description: The location at which an item can be viewed or experienced in-person.

https://schema.org/Course.label: Course
https://schema.org/Course.description: A description of an educational course which may be offered as distinct instances which take place at different times or take place at different locations, or be offered through different media or modes of study. An educational course is a sequence of one or more educational events and/or creative works which aims to build knowledge, competence or ability of learners.

https://schema.org/roofLoad.label: roofLoad
https://schema.org/roofLoad.description:
The permitted total weight of cargo and installations (e.g. a roof rack) on top of the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]]
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/CheckAction.label: CheckAction
https://schema.org/CheckAction.description: An agent inspects, determines, investigates, inquires, or examines an object's accuracy, quality, condition, or state.

https://schema.org/latitude.label: latitude
https://schema.org/latitude.description: The latitude of a location. For example ```37.42242``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

https://schema.org/Quotation.label: Quotation
https://schema.org/Quotation.description: A quotation. Often but not necessarily from some written work, attributable to a real world author and - if associated with a fictional character - to any fictional Person. Use [[isBasedOn]] to link to source/origin. The [[recordedIn]] property can be used to reference a Quotation from an [[Event]].
https://schema.org/Quotation.usage_hint: Create a Quotation instance with schema:text for the quote text. Use schema:creator or schema:author for who said/wrote it. Use schema:spokenByCharacter if attributing within a creative work.
https://schema.org/Quotation.example_keywords: quote, quotation, said, stated, remarked, exclaimed, objected, famous saying, attributed words

https://schema.org/coverageStartTime.label: coverageStartTime
https://schema.org/coverageStartTime.description: The time when the live blog will begin covering the Event. Note that coverage may begin before the Event's start time. The LiveBlogPosting may also be created before coverage begins.

https://schema.org/Taxon.label: Taxon
https://schema.org/Taxon.description: A set of organisms asserted to represent a natural cohesive biological unit.

https://schema.org/medicalSpecialty.label: medicalSpecialty
https://schema.org/medicalSpecialty.description: A medical specialty of the provider.

https://schema.org/emissionsCO2.label: emissionsCO2
https://schema.org/emissionsCO2.description: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".

https://schema.org/AchieveAction.label: AchieveAction
https://schema.org/AchieveAction.description: The act of accomplishing something via previous efforts. It is an instantaneous action rather than an ongoing process.

https://schema.org/ShortStory.label: ShortStory
https://schema.org/ShortStory.description: Short story or tale. A brief work of literature, usually written in narrative prose.

https://schema.org/WPHeader.label: WPHeader
https://schema.org/WPHeader.description: The header section of the page.

https://schema.org/webCheckinTime.label: webCheckinTime
https://schema.org/webCheckinTime.description: The time when a passenger can check into the flight online.

https://schema.org/experienceRequirement.label: experienceRequirements
https://schema.org/experienceRequirement.description: Description of skills and experience needed for the position or Occupation.

https://schema.org/printPage.label: printPage
https://schema.org/printPage.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the name of the page on which the article is found. Please note that this field is intended for the exact page name (e.g. A5, B18).

https://schema.org/fatContent.label: fatContent
https://schema.org/fatContent.description: The number of grams of fat.

https://schema.org/knowsAbout.label: knowsAbout
https://schema.org/knowsAbout.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a topic that is known about - suggesting possible expertise but not implying it. We do not distinguish skill levels here, or relate this to educational content, events, objectives or [[JobPosting]] descriptions.

https://schema.org/MedicalSignOrSymptom.label: MedicalSignOrSymptom
https://schema.org/MedicalSignOrSymptom.description: Any feature associated or not with a medical condition. In medicine a symptom is generally subjective while a sign is objective.

https://schema.org/syllabusSections.label: syllabusSections
https://schema.org/syllabusSections.description: Indicates (typically several) Syllabus entities that lay out what each section of the overall course will cover.

https://schema.org/Audience.label: Audience
https://schema.org/Audience.description: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

https://schema.org/gtin.label: gtin
https://schema.org/gtin.description:
A Global Trade Item Number ([GTIN](https://www.gs1.org/standards/id-keys/gtin)). GTINs identify trade items, including products and services, using numeric identification codes.

A correct [[gtin]] value should be a valid GTIN, which means that it should be an all-numeric string of either 8, 12, 13 or 14 digits, or a "GS1 Digital Link" URL based on such a string. The numeric component should also have a [valid GS1 check digit](https://www.gs1.org/services/check-digit-calculator) and meet the oth

https://schema.org/orderDelivery.label: orderDelivery
https://schema.org/orderDelivery.description: The delivery of the parcel related to this order or order item.

https://schema.org/archivedAt.label: archivedAt
https://schema.org/archivedAt.description: Indicates a page or other link involved in archival of a [[CreativeWork]]. In the case of [[MediaReview]], the items in a [[MediaReviewItem]] may often become inaccessible, but be archived by archival, journalistic, activist, or law enforcement organizations. In such cases, the referenced page may not directly publish the content.

https://schema.org/cholesterolContent.label: cholesterolContent
https://schema.org/cholesterolContent.description: The number of milligrams of cholesterol.

https://schema.org/workPresented.label: workPresented
https://schema.org/workPresented.description: The movie presented during this event.

https://schema.org/broker.label: broker
https://schema.org/broker.description: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.

https://schema.org/MusicRelease.label: MusicRelease
https://schema.org/MusicRelease.description: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

https://schema.org/epidemiology.label: epidemiology
https://schema.org/epidemiology.description: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.

https://schema.org/numberOfRooms.label: numberOfRooms
https://schema.org/numberOfRooms.description:
The number of rooms (excluding bathrooms and closets) of the accommodation or lodging business.
Typical unit code(s): ROM for room or C62 for no unit. The type of room can be put in the unitText property of the QuantitativeValue.

https://schema.org/PaymentService.label: PaymentService
https://schema.org/PaymentService.description: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.

https://schema.org/Episode.label: Episode
https://schema.org/Episode.description: A media episode (e.g. TV, radio, video game) which can be part of a series or season.

https://schema.org/checkoutPageURLTempla.label: checkoutPageURLTemplate
https://schema.org/checkoutPageURLTempla.description: A URL template (RFC 6570) for a checkout page for an offer. This approach allows merchants to specify a URL for online checkout of the offered product, by interpolating parameters such as the logged in user ID, product ID, quantity, discount code etc. Parameter naming and standardization are not specified here.

https://schema.org/fileSize.label: fileSize
https://schema.org/fileSize.description: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.

https://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.label: expectedPrognosis
https://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.description: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.

https://schema.org/countriesSupported.label: countriesSupported
https://schema.org/countriesSupported.description: Countries for which the application is supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

https://schema.org/signOrSymptom.label: signOrSymptom
https://schema.org/signOrSymptom.description: A sign or symptom of this condition. Signs are objective or physically observable manifestations of the medical condition while symptoms are the subjective experience of the medical condition.

https://schema.org/sampleType.label: sampleType
https://schema.org/sampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

https://schema.org/openingHoursSpecifica.label: openingHoursSpecification
https://schema.org/openingHoursSpecifica.description: The opening hours of a certain place.

https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorType.label: vehicleInteriorType
https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorType.description: The type or material of the interior of the vehicle (e.g. synthetic fabric, leather, wood, etc.). While most interior types are characterized by the material used, an interior type can also be based on vehicle usage or target audience.

https://schema.org/SocialMediaPosting.label: SocialMediaPosting
https://schema.org/SocialMediaPosting.description: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

https://schema.org/TVClip.label: TVClip
https://schema.org/TVClip.description: A short TV program or a segment/part of a TV program.

https://schema.org/MediaReviewItem.label: MediaReviewItem
https://schema.org/MediaReviewItem.description: Represents an item or group of closely related items treated as a unit for the sake of evaluation in a [[MediaReview]]. Authorship etc. apply to the items rather than to the curation/grouping or reviewing party.

https://schema.org/partOfInvoice.label: partOfInvoice
https://schema.org/partOfInvoice.description: The order is being paid as part of the referenced Invoice.

https://schema.org/AmpStory.label: AmpStory
https://schema.org/AmpStory.description: A creative work with a visual storytelling format intended to be viewed online, particularly on mobile devices.

https://schema.org/data.label: data
https://schema.org/data.description: Data associated with the event, like for instance a log message.

https://schema.org/scheduledPaymentDate.label: scheduledPaymentDate
https://schema.org/scheduledPaymentDate.description: The date the invoice is scheduled to be paid.

https://schema.org/ResetPasswordAction.label: ResetPasswordAction
https://schema.org/ResetPasswordAction.description: The action of resetting the password of a device or application.

https://schema.org/geoRadius.label: geoRadius
https://schema.org/geoRadius.description: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).

https://schema.org/PlanAction.label: PlanAction
https://schema.org/PlanAction.description: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

https://schema.org/Place.label: Place
https://schema.org/Place.description: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

https://schema.org/occupationLocation.label: occupationLocation
https://schema.org/occupationLocation.description: The region/country for which this occupational description is appropriate. Note that educational requirements and qualifications can vary between jurisdictions.

https://schema.org/validIn.label: validIn
https://schema.org/validIn.description: The geographic area where the item is valid. Applies for example to a [[Permit]], a [[Certification]], or an [[EducationalOccupationalCredential]].

https://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.label: exerciseRelatedDiet
https://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

https://schema.org/BedDetails.label: BedDetails
https://schema.org/BedDetails.description: An entity holding detailed information about the available bed types, e.g. the quantity of twin beds for a hotel room. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you can use bed directly with a text. See also [[BedType]] (under development).

https://schema.org/digitalSourceType.label: digitalSourceType
https://schema.org/digitalSourceType.description: Indicates an IPTCDigitalSourceEnumeration code indicating the nature of the digital source(s) for some [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/MediaGallery.label: MediaGallery
https://schema.org/MediaGallery.description: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contain media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

https://schema.org/normalRange.label: normalRange
https://schema.org/normalRange.description: Range of acceptable values for a typical patient, when applicable.

https://schema.org/WarrantyPromise.label: WarrantyPromise
https://schema.org/WarrantyPromise.description: A structured value representing the duration and scope of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

https://schema.org/Demand.label: Demand
https://schema.org/Demand.description: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

https://schema.org/MedicalConditionStage.label: MedicalConditionStage
https://schema.org/MedicalConditionStage.description: A stage of a medical condition, such as 'Stage IIIa'.

https://schema.org/PublicationVolume.label: PublicationVolume
https://schema.org/PublicationVolume.description: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

https://schema.org/ImageObjectSnapshot.label: ImageObjectSnapshot
https://schema.org/ImageObjectSnapshot.description: A specific and exact (byte-for-byte) version of an [[ImageObject]]. Two byte-for-byte identical files, for the purposes of this type, considered identical. If they have different embedded metadata (e.g. XMP, EXIF) the files will differ. Different external facts about the files, e.g. creator or dateCreated that aren't represented in their actual content, do not affect this notion of identity.

https://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.label: broadcastOfEvent
https://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.description: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.

https://schema.org/Person.label: Person
https://schema.org/Person.description: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

https://schema.org/stage.label: stage
https://schema.org/stage.description: The stage of the condition, if applicable.

https://schema.org/boardingPolicy.label: boardingPolicy
https://schema.org/boardingPolicy.description: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).

https://schema.org/issn.label: issn
https://schema.org/issn.description: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

https://schema.org/instructor.label: instructor
https://schema.org/instructor.description: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the [[CourseInstance]].

https://schema.org/PeopleAudience.label: PeopleAudience
https://schema.org/PeopleAudience.description: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

https://schema.org/educationalCredential.label: educationalCredentialAwarded
https://schema.org/educationalCredential.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other educational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

https://schema.org/PerformanceRole.label: PerformanceRole
https://schema.org/PerformanceRole.description: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

https://schema.org/transcript.label: transcript
https://schema.org/transcript.description: If this MediaObject is an AudioObject or VideoObject, the transcript of that object.

https://schema.org/byMonth.label: byMonth
https://schema.org/byMonth.description: Defines the month(s) of the year on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-12. January is 1.

https://schema.org/MenuSection.label: MenuSection
https://schema.org/MenuSection.description: A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.

https://schema.org/Occupation.label: Occupation
https://schema.org/Occupation.description: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

https://schema.org/assembly.label: assembly
https://schema.org/assembly.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

https://schema.org/freeShippingThreshold.label: freeShippingThreshold
https://schema.org/freeShippingThreshold.description: A monetary value above (or at) which the shipping rate becomes free. Intended to be used via an [[OfferShippingDetails]] with [[shippingSettingsLink]] matching this [[ShippingRateSettings]].

https://schema.org/discusses.label: discusses
https://schema.org/discusses.description: Specifies the CreativeWork associated with the UserComment.

https://schema.org/requiredGender.label: requiredGender
https://schema.org/requiredGender.description: Audiences defined by a person's gender.

https://schema.org/termsPerYear.label: termsPerYear
https://schema.org/termsPerYear.description: The number of times terms of study are offered per year. Semesters and quarters are common units for term. For example, if the student can only take 2 semesters for the program in one year, then termsPerYear should be 2.

https://schema.org/source.label: source
https://schema.org/source.description: The source or cause of the event.

https://schema.org/assesses.label: assesses
https://schema.org/assesses.description: The item being described is intended to assess the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

https://schema.org/isStoreOn.label: isStoreOn
https://schema.org/isStoreOn.description: The eCommerce marketplace this online store is on.

https://schema.org/relevantSpecialty.label: relevantSpecialty
https://schema.org/relevantSpecialty.description: If applicable, a medical specialty in which this entity is relevant.

https://schema.org/ReserveAction.label: ReserveAction
https://schema.org/ReserveAction.description:
Reserving a concrete object.

Related actions:

* [[ScheduleAction]]: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

https://schema.org/MedicalAudienceType.label: MedicalAudienceType
https://schema.org/MedicalAudienceType.description: Target audiences types for medical web pages. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/gtin12.label: gtin12
https://schema.org/gtin12.description: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/upvoteCount.label: upvoteCount
https://schema.org/upvoteCount.description: The number of upvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

https://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.label: hasCourseInstance
https://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.description: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.

https://schema.org/usNPI.label: usNPI
https://schema.org/usNPI.description: A National Provider Identifier (NPI) is a unique 10-digit identification number issued to health care providers in the United States by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services.

https://schema.org/DrugClass.label: DrugClass
https://schema.org/DrugClass.description: A class of medical drugs, e.g., statins. Classes can represent general pharmacological class, common mechanisms of action, common physiological effects, etc.

https://schema.org/WebPage.label: WebPage
https://schema.org/WebPage.description: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.

https://schema.org/price.label: price
https://schema.org/price.description:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

* Use the [[priceCurrency]] property (with standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS)

https://schema.org/result.label: result
https://schema.org/result.description: The result produced in the action. E.g. John wrote *a book*.

https://schema.org/geoContains.label: geoContains
https://schema.org/geoContains.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/featureList.label: featureList
https://schema.org/featureList.description: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).

https://schema.org/hasMenuSection.label: hasMenuSection
https://schema.org/hasMenuSection.description: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).

https://schema.org/MedicalObservationalS.label: MedicalObservationalStudy
https://schema.org/MedicalObservationalS.description: An observational study is a type of medical study that attempts to infer the possible effect of a treatment through observation of a cohort of subjects over a period of time. In an observational study, the assignment of subjects into treatment groups versus control groups is outside the control of the investigator. This is in contrast with controlled studies, such as the randomized controlled trials represented by MedicalTrial, where each subject is randomly assigned to a treatment group or a co

https://schema.org/BusTrip.label: BusTrip
https://schema.org/BusTrip.description: A trip on a commercial bus line.

https://schema.org/MerchantReturnEnumera.label: MerchantReturnEnumeration
https://schema.org/MerchantReturnEnumera.description: Enumerates several kinds of product return policies.

https://schema.org/Organization.label: Organization
https://schema.org/Organization.description: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

https://schema.org/InfectiousDisease.label: InfectiousDisease
https://schema.org/InfectiousDisease.description: An infectious disease is a clinically evident human disease resulting from the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, like pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and prions. To be considered an infectious disease, such pathogens are known to be able to cause this disease.

https://schema.org/Product.label: Product
https://schema.org/Product.description: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

https://schema.org/license.label: license
https://schema.org/license.description: A license document that applies to this content, typically indicated by URL.

https://schema.org/salaryUponCompletion.label: salaryUponCompletion
https://schema.org/salaryUponCompletion.description: The expected salary upon completing the training.

https://schema.org/query.label: query
https://schema.org/query.description: A sub property of instrument. The query used on this action.

https://schema.org/gender.label: gender
https://schema.org/gender.description: Gender of something, typically a [[Person]], but possibly also fictional characters, animals, etc. While https://schema.org/Male and https://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who are not a binary gender. The [[gender]] property can also be used in an extended sense to cover e.g. the gender of sports teams. As with the gender of individuals, we do not try to enumerate all possibilities. A mixed-gender [[SportsTeam]] can be indicated with a text value of "M

https://schema.org/ContactPointOption.label: ContactPointOption
https://schema.org/ContactPointOption.description: Enumerated options related to a ContactPoint.

https://schema.org/processorRequirements.label: processorRequirements
https://schema.org/processorRequirements.description: Processor architecture required to run the application (e.g. IA64).

https://schema.org/totalHistoricalEnroll.label: totalHistoricalEnrollment
https://schema.org/totalHistoricalEnroll.description: The total number of students that have enrolled in the history of the course.

https://schema.org/foundingDate.label: foundingDate
https://schema.org/foundingDate.description: The date that this organization was founded.

https://schema.org/RentAction.label: RentAction
https://schema.org/RentAction.description: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

https://schema.org/TouristDestination.label: TouristDestination
https://schema.org/TouristDestination.description: A tourist destination. In principle any [[Place]] can be a [[TouristDestination]] from a [[City]], Region or [[Country]] to an [[AmusementPark]] or [[Hotel]]. This Type can be used on its own to describe a general [[TouristDestination]], or be used as an [[additionalType]] to add tourist relevant properties to any other [[Place]].  A [[TouristDestination]] is defined as a [[Place]] that contains, or is colocated with, one or more [[TouristAttraction]]s, often linked by a similar theme or interes

https://schema.org/missionCoveragePriori.label: missionCoveragePrioritiesPolicy
https://schema.org/missionCoveragePriori.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement on coverage priorities, including any public agenda or stance on issues.

https://schema.org/eduQuestionType.label: eduQuestionType
https://schema.org/eduQuestionType.description: For questions that are part of learning resources (e.g. Quiz), eduQuestionType indicates the format of question being given. Example: "Multiple choice", "Open ended", "Flashcard".

https://schema.org/additionalType.label: additionalType
https://schema.org/additionalType.description:
An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. Typically the value is a URI-identified RDF class, and in this case corresponds to the
    use of rdf:type in RDF. Text values can be used sparingly, for cases where useful information can be added without their being an appropriate schema to reference. In the case of text values, the class label

https://schema.org/PreventionIndication.label: PreventionIndication
https://schema.org/PreventionIndication.description: An indication for preventing an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

https://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.label: broadcastChannelId
https://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.description: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.

https://schema.org/AppendAction.label: AppendAction
https://schema.org/AppendAction.description: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

https://schema.org/yearBuilt.label: yearBuilt
https://schema.org/yearBuilt.description: The year an [[Accommodation]] was constructed. This corresponds to the [YearBuilt field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/YearBuilt+Field).

https://schema.org/partOfSeason.label: partOfSeason
https://schema.org/partOfSeason.description: The season to which this episode belongs.

https://schema.org/BloodTest.label: BloodTest
https://schema.org/BloodTest.description: A medical test performed on a sample of a patient's blood.

https://schema.org/broadcastSignalModula.label: broadcastSignalModulation
https://schema.org/broadcastSignalModula.description: The modulation (e.g. FM, AM, etc) used by a particular broadcast service.

https://schema.org/PhysicalActivity.label: PhysicalActivity
https://schema.org/PhysicalActivity.description: Any bodily activity that enhances or maintains physical fitness and overall health and wellness. Includes activity that is part of daily living and routine, structured exercise, and exercise prescribed as part of a medical treatment or recovery plan.

https://schema.org/performers.label: performers
https://schema.org/performers.description: The main performer or performers of the event—for example, a presenter, musician, or actor.

https://schema.org/programName.label: programName
https://schema.org/programName.description: The program providing the membership. It is preferable to use [:program](https://schema.org/program) instead.

https://schema.org/providerMobility.label: providerMobility
https://schema.org/providerMobility.description: Indicates the mobility of a provided service (e.g. 'static', 'dynamic').

https://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.label: amountOfThisGood
https://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.description: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.

https://schema.org/SuperficialAnatomy.label: SuperficialAnatomy
https://schema.org/SuperficialAnatomy.description: Anatomical features that can be observed by sight (without dissection), including the form and proportions of the human body as well as surface landmarks that correspond to deeper subcutaneous structures. Superficial anatomy plays an important role in sports medicine, phlebotomy, and other medical specialties as underlying anatomical structures can be identified through surface palpation. For example, during back surgery, superficial anatomy can be used to palpate and count vertebrae to find the

https://schema.org/actionProcess.label: actionProcess
https://schema.org/actionProcess.description: Description of the process by which the action was performed.

https://schema.org/diversityStaffingRepo.label: diversityStaffingReport
https://schema.org/diversityStaffingRepo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a report on staffing diversity issues. In a news context this might be for example ASNE or RTDNA (US) reports, or self-reported.

https://schema.org/Comment.label: Comment
https://schema.org/Comment.description: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the [[text]] property, and its topic via [[about]], properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

https://schema.org/GeoShape.label: GeoShape
https://schema.org/GeoShape.description: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

https://schema.org/GeoCoordinates.label: GeoCoordinates
https://schema.org/GeoCoordinates.description: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

https://schema.org/legislationTransposes.label: legislationTransposes
https://schema.org/legislationTransposes.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of legislation) fulfills the objectives set by another legislation, by passing appropriate implementation measures. Typically, some legislations of European Union's member states or regions transpose European Directives. This indicates a legally binding link between the 2 legislations.

https://schema.org/sourcedFrom.label: sourcedFrom
https://schema.org/sourcedFrom.description: The neurological pathway that originates the neurons.

https://schema.org/paymentStatus.label: paymentStatus
https://schema.org/paymentStatus.description: The status of payment; whether the invoice has been paid or not.

https://schema.org/requiredCollateral.label: requiredCollateral
https://schema.org/requiredCollateral.description: Assets required to secure loan or credit repayments. It may take form of third party pledge, goods, financial instruments (cash, securities, etc.)

https://schema.org/financialAidEligible.label: financialAidEligible
https://schema.org/financialAidEligible.description: A financial aid type or program which students may use to pay for tuition or fees associated with the program.

https://schema.org/paymentDue.label: paymentDue
https://schema.org/paymentDue.description: The date that payment is due.

https://schema.org/itinerary.label: itinerary
https://schema.org/itinerary.description: Destination(s) ( [[Place]] ) that make up a trip. For a trip where destination order is important use [[ItemList]] to specify that order (see examples).

https://schema.org/addOn.label: addOn
https://schema.org/addOn.description: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).

https://schema.org/baseSalary.label: baseSalary
https://schema.org/baseSalary.description: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.

https://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.label: evidenceOrigin
https://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.description: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.

https://schema.org/foodEstablishment.label: foodEstablishment
https://schema.org/foodEstablishment.description: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.

https://schema.org/byArtist.label: byArtist
https://schema.org/byArtist.description: The artist that performed this album or recording.

https://schema.org/algorithm.label: algorithm
https://schema.org/algorithm.description: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.

https://schema.org/HowToStep.label: HowToStep
https://schema.org/HowToStep.description: A step in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It is an ordered list with HowToDirection and/or HowToTip items.

https://schema.org/numberOfPartialBathro.label: numberOfPartialBathrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfPartialBathro.description: Number of partial bathrooms - The total number of half and ¼ bathrooms in an [[Accommodation]]. This corresponds to the [BathroomsPartial field in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsPartial+Field).

https://schema.org/orderPercentage.label: orderPercentage
https://schema.org/orderPercentage.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the value of the order that is charged as shipping cost.

https://schema.org/hasMolecularFunction.label: hasMolecularFunction
https://schema.org/hasMolecularFunction.description: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

https://schema.org/pickupLocation.label: pickupLocation
https://schema.org/pickupLocation.description: Where a taxi will pick up a passenger or a rental car can be picked up.

https://schema.org/PaymentMethodType.label: PaymentMethodType
https://schema.org/PaymentMethodType.description: The type of payment method, only for generic payment types, specific forms of payments, like card payment should be expressed using subclasses of PaymentMethod.

https://schema.org/payload.label: payload
https://schema.org/payload.description:
The permitted weight of passengers and cargo, EXCLUDING the weight of the empty vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: Many databases specify the permitted TOTAL weight instead, which is the sum of [[weight]] and [[payload]]
* Note 2: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 3: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 4:

https://schema.org/startTime.label: startTime
https://schema.org/startTime.description: The startTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to start.
