For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from *January* to December. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the start of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clari

https://schema.org/isrcCode.label: isrcCode
https://schema.org/isrcCode.description: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.

https://schema.org/MedicalStudy.label: MedicalStudy
https://schema.org/MedicalStudy.description: A medical study is an umbrella type covering all kinds of research studies relating to human medicine or health, including observational studies and interventional trials and registries, randomized, controlled or not. When the specific type of study is known, use one of the extensions of this type, such as MedicalTrial or MedicalObservationalStudy. Also, note that this type should be used to mark up data that describes the study itself; to tag an article that publishes the results of a study, us

https://schema.org/applicableCountry.label: applicableCountry
https://schema.org/applicableCountry.description: A country where a particular merchant return policy applies to, for example the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

https://schema.org/FoodEstablishmentRese.label: FoodEstablishmentReservation
https://schema.org/FoodEstablishmentRese.description: A reservation to dine at a food-related business.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

https://schema.org/Language.label: Language
https://schema.org/Language.description: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in [BCP 47](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IETF_language_tag) can be used via the [[alternateName]] property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using [[ComputerLanguage]].

https://schema.org/FundingScheme.label: FundingScheme
https://schema.org/FundingScheme.description:
A FundingScheme combines organizational, project and policy aspects of grant-based funding
    that sets guidelines, principles and mechanisms to support other kinds of projects and activities.
    Funding is typically organized via [[Grant]] funding. Examples of funding schemes: Swiss Priority Programmes (SPPs); EU Framework 7 (FP7); Horizon 2020; the NIH-R01 Grant Program; Wellcome institutional strategic support fund. For large scale public sector funding, the management and administration of

https://schema.org/Artery.label: Artery
https://schema.org/Artery.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood away from the heart.

https://schema.org/FundingAgency.label: FundingAgency
https://schema.org/FundingAgency.description:
A FundingAgency is an organization that implements one or more [[FundingScheme]]s and manages
    the granting process (via [[Grant]]s, typically [[MonetaryGrant]]s).
    A funding agency is not always required for grant funding, e.g. philanthropic giving, corporate sponsorship etc.
    
Examples of funding agencies include ERC, REA, NIH, Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation, ...

https://schema.org/isRelatedTo.label: isRelatedTo
https://schema.org/isRelatedTo.description: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).

https://schema.org/clipNumber.label: clipNumber
https://schema.org/clipNumber.description: Position of the clip within an ordered group of clips.

https://schema.org/InvestmentOrDeposit.label: InvestmentOrDeposit
https://schema.org/InvestmentOrDeposit.description: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

https://schema.org/colorist.label: colorist
https://schema.org/colorist.description: The individual who adds color to inked drawings.

https://schema.org/PriceSpecification.label: PriceSpecification
https://schema.org/PriceSpecification.description: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use [[MonetaryAmount]] to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.

https://schema.org/keywords.label: keywords
https://schema.org/keywords.description: Keywords or tags used to describe some item. Multiple textual entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas, or by repeating the property.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.label: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption
https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.description: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

https://schema.org/priceCurrency.label: priceCurrency
https://schema.org/priceCurrency.description: The currency of the price, or a price component when attached to [[PriceSpecification]] and its subtypes.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/blogPosts.label: blogPosts
https://schema.org/blogPosts.description: Indicates a post that is part of a [[Blog]]. Note that historically, what we term a "Blog" was once known as a "weblog", and that what we term a "BlogPosting" is now often colloquially referred to as a "blog".

https://schema.org/CollegeOrUniversity.label: CollegeOrUniversity
https://schema.org/CollegeOrUniversity.description: A college, university, or other third-level educational institution.

https://schema.org/ItemListOrderType.label: ItemListOrderType
https://schema.org/ItemListOrderType.description: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

https://schema.org/track.label: track
https://schema.org/track.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song. If an ItemList is given, the list should contain items of type MusicRecording.

https://schema.org/legislationType.label: legislationType
https://schema.org/legislationType.description: The type of the legislation. Examples of values are "law", "act", "directive", "decree", "regulation", "statutory instrument", "loi organique", "règlement grand-ducal", etc., depending on the country.

https://schema.org/OfferForPurchase.label: OfferForPurchase
https://schema.org/OfferForPurchase.description:
An [[OfferForPurchase]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to sell something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [sell](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

https://schema.org/serviceSmsNumber.label: serviceSmsNumber
https://schema.org/serviceSmsNumber.description: The number to access the service by text message.

https://schema.org/interactionService.label: interactionService
https://schema.org/interactionService.description: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.

https://schema.org/slogan.label: slogan
https://schema.org/slogan.description: A slogan or motto associated with the item.

https://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.label: broadcastTimezone
https://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.description: The timezone in [ISO 8601 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) for which the service bases its broadcasts.

https://schema.org/educationalProgramMod.label: educationalProgramMode
https://schema.org/educationalProgramMod.description: Similar to courseMode, the medium or means of delivery of the program as a whole. The value may either be a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous ).

https://schema.org/LegalValueLevel.label: LegalValueLevel
https://schema.org/LegalValueLevel.description: A list of possible levels for the legal validity of a legislation.

https://schema.org/DrugStrength.label: DrugStrength
https://schema.org/DrugStrength.description: A specific strength in which a medical drug is available in a specific country.

https://schema.org/priceType.label: priceType
https://schema.org/priceType.description: Defines the type of a price specified for an offered product, for example a list price, a (temporary) sale price or a manufacturer suggested retail price. If multiple prices are specified for an offer the [[priceType]] property can be used to identify the type of each such specified price. The value of priceType can be specified as a value from enumeration PriceTypeEnumeration or, a UN/EDIFACT 5387 code, or as a free form text string for price types that are not already predefined in PriceTypeEn

https://schema.org/Order.label: Order
https://schema.org/Order.description: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

https://schema.org/labelDetails.label: labelDetails
https://schema.org/labelDetails.description: Link to the drug's label details.

https://schema.org/MedicalTestPanel.label: MedicalTestPanel
https://schema.org/MedicalTestPanel.description: Any collection of tests commonly ordered together.

https://schema.org/ComicCoverArt.label: ComicCoverArt
https://schema.org/ComicCoverArt.description: The artwork on the cover of a comic.

https://schema.org/endDate.label: endDate
https://schema.org/endDate.description: The end date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

https://schema.org/requiredQuantity.label: requiredQuantity
https://schema.org/requiredQuantity.description: The required quantity of the item(s).

https://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode.label: eventAttendanceMode
https://schema.org/eventAttendanceMode.description: The eventAttendanceMode of an event indicates whether it occurs online, offline, or a mix.

https://schema.org/seatSection.label: seatSection
https://schema.org/seatSection.description: The section location of the reserved seat (e.g. Orchestra).

https://schema.org/hasPart.label: hasPart
https://schema.org/hasPart.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

https://schema.org/transitTime.label: transitTime
https://schema.org/transitTime.description:
The typical delay the order has been sent for delivery and the goods reach the final customer.

  In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], use the [[QuantitativeValue]]. Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).

  In the context of [[ShippingConditions]], use the [[ServicePeriod]]. It has a duration (as a [[QuantitativeValue]]) and also business days and a cut-off time.

https://schema.org/OpeningHoursSpecifica.label: OpeningHoursSpecification
https://schema.org/OpeningHoursSpecifica.description:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.


The place is __open__ if the [[opens]] property is specified, and __closed__ otherwise.

If the value for the [[closes]] property is less than the value for the [[opens]] property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.

https://schema.org/BedAndBreakfast.label: BedAndBreakfast
https://schema.org/BedAndBreakfast.description:
Bed and breakfast.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/DrugLegalStatus.label: DrugLegalStatus
https://schema.org/DrugLegalStatus.description: The legal availability status of a medical drug.

https://schema.org/floorSize.label: floorSize
https://schema.org/floorSize.description:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard.

https://schema.org/totalJobOpenings.label: totalJobOpenings
https://schema.org/totalJobOpenings.description: The number of positions open for this job posting. Use a positive integer. Do not use if the number of positions is unclear or not known.

https://schema.org/SeekToAction.label: SeekToAction
https://schema.org/SeekToAction.description: This is the [[Action]] of navigating to a specific [[startOffset]] timestamp within a [[VideoObject]], typically represented with a URL template structure.

https://schema.org/funder.label: funder
https://schema.org/funder.description: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.

https://schema.org/publishedOn.label: publishedOn
https://schema.org/publishedOn.description: A broadcast service associated with the publication event.

https://schema.org/FloorPlan.label: FloorPlan
https://schema.org/FloorPlan.description: A FloorPlan is an explicit representation of a collection of similar accommodations, allowing the provision of common information (room counts, sizes, layout diagrams) and offers for rental or sale. In typical use, some [[ApartmentComplex]] has an [[accommodationFloorPlan]] which is a [[FloorPlan]].  A FloorPlan is always in the context of a particular place, either a larger [[ApartmentComplex]] or a single [[Apartment]]. The visual/spatial aspects of a floor plan (i.e. room layout, [see wikiped

https://schema.org/accessMode.label: accessMode
https://schema.org/accessMode.description: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessMode-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/SizeSpecification.label: SizeSpecification
https://schema.org/SizeSpecification.description: Size related properties of a product, typically a size code ([[name]]) and optionally a [[sizeSystem]], [[sizeGroup]], and product measurements ([[hasMeasurement]]). In addition, the intended audience can be defined through [[suggestedAge]], [[suggestedGender]], and suggested body measurements ([[suggestedMeasurement]]).

https://schema.org/appearance.label: appearance
https://schema.org/appearance.description: Indicates an occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/seasonNumber.label: seasonNumber
https://schema.org/seasonNumber.description: Position of the season within an ordered group of seasons.

https://schema.org/cvdCollectionDate.label: cvdCollectionDate
https://schema.org/cvdCollectionDate.description: collectiondate - Date for which patient counts are reported.

https://schema.org/deliveryLeadTime.label: deliveryLeadTime
https://schema.org/deliveryLeadTime.description: The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

https://schema.org/VirtualLocation.label: VirtualLocation
https://schema.org/VirtualLocation.description: An online or virtual location for attending events. For example, one may attend an online seminar or educational event. While a virtual location may be used as the location of an event, virtual locations should not be confused with physical locations in the real world.

https://schema.org/returnMethod.label: returnMethod
https://schema.org/returnMethod.description: The type of return method offered, specified from an enumeration.

https://schema.org/RadioSeries.label: RadioSeries
https://schema.org/RadioSeries.description: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

https://schema.org/PaintAction.label: PaintAction
https://schema.org/PaintAction.description: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

https://schema.org/DrugCost.label: DrugCost
https://schema.org/DrugCost.description: The cost per unit of a medical drug. Note that this type is not meant to represent the price in an offer of a drug for sale; see the Offer type for that. This type will typically be used to tag wholesale or average retail cost of a drug, or maximum reimbursable cost. Costs of medical drugs vary widely depending on how and where they are paid for, so while this type captures some of the variables, costs should be used with caution by consumers of this schema's markup.

https://schema.org/MediaObject.label: MediaObject
https://schema.org/MediaObject.description: A media object, such as an image, video, audio, or text object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

https://schema.org/representativeOfPage.label: representativeOfPage
https://schema.org/representativeOfPage.description: Indicates whether this image is representative of the content of the page.

https://schema.org/incomeLimit.label: incomeLimit
https://schema.org/incomeLimit.description:
Optional. Income limit for which the incentive is applicable for.

If MonetaryAmount is specified, this should be based on annualized income (e.g. if an incentive is limited to those making <$114,000 annually):

{ "@type": "MonetaryAmount", "maxValue": 114000, "currency": "USD", } Use Text for incentives that are limited based on other criteria, for example if an incentive is only available to recipients making 120% of the median poverty income in their

https://schema.org/printColumn.label: printColumn
https://schema.org/printColumn.description: The number of the column in which the NewsArticle appears in the print edition.

https://schema.org/inChI.label: inChI
https://schema.org/inChI.description: Non-proprietary identifier for molecular entity that can be used in printed and electronic data sources thus enabling easier linking of diverse data compilations.

https://schema.org/toRecipient.label: toRecipient
https://schema.org/toRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient who was directly sent the message.

https://schema.org/DefinedRegion.label: DefinedRegion
https://schema.org/DefinedRegion.description:
A DefinedRegion is a geographic area defined by potentially arbitrary (rather than political, administrative or natural geographical) criteria. Properties are provided for defining a region by reference to sets of postal codes.

Examples: a delivery destination when shopping. Region where regional pricing is configured.

Requirement 1:
Country: US
States: "NY", "CA"

Requirement 2:
Country: US
PostalCode Set: { [94000-94585], [97000, 97999], [13000, 13599]}
{ [12345, 12345], [78945, 78945], }
Re

https://schema.org/issueNumber.label: issueNumber
https://schema.org/issueNumber.description: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".

https://schema.org/pageEnd.label: pageEnd
https://schema.org/pageEnd.description: The page on which the work ends; for example "138" or "xvi".

https://schema.org/ReplaceAction.label: ReplaceAction
https://schema.org/ReplaceAction.description: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

https://schema.org/productID.label: productID
https://schema.org/productID.description: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: ``` meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789" ```.

https://schema.org/HealthPlanNetwork.label: HealthPlanNetwork
https://schema.org/HealthPlanNetwork.description: A US-style health insurance plan network.

https://schema.org/ApplyAction.label: ApplyAction
https://schema.org/ApplyAction.description:
The act of registering to an organization/service without the guarantee to receive it.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, ApplyAction has no guarantees that the application will be accepted.

https://schema.org/realEstateAgent.label: realEstateAgent
https://schema.org/realEstateAgent.description: A sub property of participant. The real estate agent involved in the action.

https://schema.org/usesDevice.label: usesDevice
https://schema.org/usesDevice.description: Device used to perform the test.

https://schema.org/legislationDateOfAppl.label: legislationDateOfApplicability
https://schema.org/legislationDateOfAppl.description: The date at which the Legislation becomes applicable. This can sometimes be distinct from the date of entry into force : a text may come in force today, and state it will become applicable in 3 months.

https://schema.org/countryOfLastProcessi.label: countryOfLastProcessing
https://schema.org/countryOfLastProcessi.description: The place where the item (typically [[Product]]) was last processed and tested before importation.

https://schema.org/SportsOrganization.label: SportsOrganization
https://schema.org/SportsOrganization.description: Represents the collection of all sports organizations, including sports teams, governing bodies, and sports associations.

https://schema.org/duringMedia.label: duringMedia
https://schema.org/duringMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances while performing this direction.

https://schema.org/providesService.label: providesService
https://schema.org/providesService.description: The service provided by this channel.

https://schema.org/mobileUrl.label: mobileUrl
https://schema.org/mobileUrl.description:
The [[mobileUrl]] property is provided for specific situations in which data consumers need to determine whether one of several provided URLs is a dedicated 'mobile site'.

To discourage over-use, and reflecting intial usecases, the property is expected only on [[Product]] and [[Offer]], rather than [[Thing]]. The general trend in web technology is towards [responsive design](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Responsive_web_design) in which content can be flexibly adapted to a wide range of browsing

https://schema.org/actor.label: actor
https://schema.org/actor.description: An actor (individual or a group), e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/geo.label: geo
https://schema.org/geo.description: The geo coordinates of the place.

https://schema.org/maximumVirtualAttende.label: maximumVirtualAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumVirtualAttende.description: The maximum virtual attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OnlineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the online aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

https://schema.org/constraintProperty.label: constraintProperty
https://schema.org/constraintProperty.description: Indicates a property used as a constraint. For example, in the definition of a [[StatisticalVariable]]. The value is a property, either from within Schema.org or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

https://schema.org/aggregateRating.label: aggregateRating
https://schema.org/aggregateRating.description: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.

https://schema.org/MoneyTransfer.label: MoneyTransfer
https://schema.org/MoneyTransfer.description: The act of transferring money from one place to another place. This may occur electronically or physically.

https://schema.org/isPlanForApartment.label: isPlanForApartment
https://schema.org/isPlanForApartment.description: Indicates some accommodation that this floor plan describes.

https://schema.org/cause.label: cause
https://schema.org/cause.description: The cause of a medical condition.

https://schema.org/Car.label: Car
https://schema.org/Car.description: A car is a wheeled, self-powered motor vehicle used for transportation.

https://schema.org/MedicalIntangible.label: MedicalIntangible
https://schema.org/MedicalIntangible.description: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things in the medical space.

https://schema.org/AuthenticateAction.label: AuthenticateAction
https://schema.org/AuthenticateAction.description: The action of authenticating into a device or application.

https://schema.org/ControlAction.label: ControlAction
https://schema.org/ControlAction.description: An agent controls a device or application.

https://schema.org/postalCodeRange.label: postalCodeRange
https://schema.org/postalCodeRange.description: A defined range of postal codes.

https://schema.org/statType.label: statType
https://schema.org/statType.description: Indicates the kind of statistic represented by a [[StatisticalVariable]], e.g. mean, count etc. The value of statType is a property, either from within Schema.org (e.g. [[median]], [[marginOfError]], [[maxValue]], [[minValue]]) or from other compatible (e.g. RDF) systems such as DataCommons.org or Wikidata.org.

https://schema.org/prepTime.label: prepTime
https://schema.org/prepTime.description: The length of time it takes to prepare the items to be used in instructions or a direction, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/itemReviewed.label: itemReviewed
https://schema.org/itemReviewed.description: The item that is being reviewed/rated.

https://schema.org/Recipe.label: Recipe
https://schema.org/Recipe.description: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via [[suitableForDiet]]. The [[keywords]] property can also be used to add more detail.

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnLabel.label: itemDefectReturnLabelSource
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnLabel.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a defect product.

https://schema.org/holdingArchive.label: holdingArchive
https://schema.org/holdingArchive.description: [[ArchiveOrganization]] that holds, keeps or maintains the [[ArchiveComponent]].

https://schema.org/smiles.label: smiles
https://schema.org/smiles.description: A specification in form of a line notation for describing the structure of chemical species using short ASCII strings.  Double bond stereochemistry \ indicators may need to be escaped in the string in formats where the backslash is an escape character.

https://schema.org/TakeAction.label: TakeAction
https://schema.org/TakeAction.description:
The act of gaining ownership of an object from an origin. Reciprocal of GiveAction.

Related actions:

* [[GiveAction]]: The reciprocal of TakeAction.
* [[ReceiveAction]]: Unlike ReceiveAction, TakeAction implies that ownership has been transferred.

https://schema.org/eligibilityToWorkRequ.label: eligibilityToWorkRequirement
https://schema.org/eligibilityToWorkRequ.description: The legal requirements such as citizenship, visa and other documentation required for an applicant to this job.

https://schema.org/measurementTechnique.label: measurementTechnique
https://schema.org/measurementTechnique.description: A technique, method or technology used in an [[Observation]], [[StatisticalVariable]] or [[Dataset]] (or [[DataDownload]], [[DataCatalog]]), corresponding to the method used for measuring the corresponding variable(s) (for datasets, described using [[variableMeasured]]; for [[Observation]], a [[StatisticalVariable]]). Often but not necessarily each [[variableMeasured]] will have an explicit representation as (or mapping to) an property such as those defined in Schema.org, or other RDF vocabulari

https://schema.org/strengthValue.label: strengthValue
https://schema.org/strengthValue.description: The value of an active ingredient's strength, e.g. 325.

https://schema.org/relatedTherapy.label: relatedTherapy
https://schema.org/relatedTherapy.description: A medical therapy related to this anatomy.

https://schema.org/namedPosition.label: namedPosition
https://schema.org/namedPosition.description: A position played, performed or filled by a person or organization, as part of an organization. For example, an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

https://schema.org/RadioClip.label: RadioClip
https://schema.org/RadioClip.description: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

https://schema.org/jobStartDate.label: jobStartDate
https://schema.org/jobStartDate.description: The date on which a successful applicant for this job would be expected to start work. Choose a specific date in the future or use the jobImmediateStart property to indicate the position is to be filled as soon as possible.

https://schema.org/material.label: material
https://schema.org/material.description: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

https://schema.org/candidate.label: candidate
https://schema.org/candidate.description: A sub property of object. The candidate subject of this action.

https://schema.org/accessibilityControl.label: accessibilityControl
https://schema.org/accessibilityControl.description: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityControl-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/arterialBranch.label: arterialBranch
https://schema.org/arterialBranch.description: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.

https://schema.org/numberOfSeasons.label: numberOfSeasons
https://schema.org/numberOfSeasons.description: The number of seasons in this series.

https://schema.org/recordedAt.label: recordedAt
https://schema.org/recordedAt.description: The Event where the CreativeWork was recorded. The CreativeWork may capture all or part of the event.

https://schema.org/SeaBodyOfWater.label: SeaBodyOfWater
https://schema.org/SeaBodyOfWater.description: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

https://schema.org/studyDesign.label: studyDesign
https://schema.org/studyDesign.description: Specifics about the observational study design (enumerated).

https://schema.org/bankAccountType.label: bankAccountType
https://schema.org/bankAccountType.description: The type of a bank account.

https://schema.org/Service.label: Service
https://schema.org/Service.description: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

https://schema.org/trainNumber.label: trainNumber
https://schema.org/trainNumber.description: The unique identifier for the train.

https://schema.org/clincalPharmacology.label: clincalPharmacology
https://schema.org/clincalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

https://schema.org/OnlineBusiness.label: OnlineBusiness
https://schema.org/OnlineBusiness.description: A particular online business, either standalone or the online part of a broader organization. Examples include an eCommerce site, an online travel booking site, an online learning site, an online logistics and shipping provider, an online (virtual) doctor, etc.

https://schema.org/authenticator.label: authenticator
https://schema.org/authenticator.description: The Organization responsible for authenticating the user's subscription. For example, many media apps require a cable/satellite provider to authenticate your subscription before playing media.

https://schema.org/CivicStructure.label: CivicStructure
https://schema.org/CivicStructure.description: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

https://schema.org/serviceOutput.label: serviceOutput
https://schema.org/serviceOutput.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

https://schema.org/productSupported.label: productSupported
https://schema.org/productSupported.description: The product or service this support contact point is related to (such as product support for a particular product line). This can be a specific product or product line (e.g. "iPhone") or a general category of products or services (e.g. "smartphones").

https://schema.org/rangeIncludes.label: rangeIncludes
https://schema.org/rangeIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that constitutes (one of) the expected type(s) for values of the property.

https://schema.org/recipeInstructions.label: recipeInstructions
https://schema.org/recipeInstructions.description: A step in making the recipe, in the form of a single item (document, video, etc.) or an ordered list with HowToStep and/or HowToSection items.

https://schema.org/bed.label: bed
https://schema.org/bed.description:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.

https://schema.org/accelerationTime.label: accelerationTime
https://schema.org/accelerationTime.description:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

* Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]], or use [[valueReference]] with a [[QuantitativeValue]] of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.

https://schema.org/merchantReturnDays.label: merchantReturnDays
https://schema.org/merchantReturnDays.description: Specifies either a fixed return date or the number of days (from the delivery date) that a product can be returned. Used when the [[returnPolicyCategory]] property is specified as [[MerchantReturnFiniteReturnWindow]].

https://schema.org/successorOf.label: successorOf
https://schema.org/successorOf.description: A pointer from a newer variant of a product  to its previous, often discontinued predecessor.

https://schema.org/Grant.label: Grant
https://schema.org/Grant.description:
A grant, typically financial or otherwise quantifiable, of resources. Typically a [[funder]] sponsors some [[MonetaryAmount]] to an [[Organization]] or [[Person]],
    sometimes not necessarily via a dedicated or long-lived [[Project]], resulting in one or more outputs, or [[fundedItem]]s. For financial sponsorship, indicate the [[funder]] of a [[MonetaryGrant]]. For non-financial support, indicate [[sponsor]] of [[Grant]]s of resources (e.g. office space).

Grants support  activities directed t

https://schema.org/applicationStartDate.label: applicationStartDate
https://schema.org/applicationStartDate.description: The date at which the program begins collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle.

https://schema.org/countryOfAssembly.label: countryOfAssembly
https://schema.org/countryOfAssembly.description: The place where the product was assembled.

https://schema.org/characterAttribute.label: characterAttribute
https://schema.org/characterAttribute.description: A piece of data that represents a particular aspect of a fictional character (skill, power, character points, advantage, disadvantage).

https://schema.org/coursePrerequisites.label: coursePrerequisites
https://schema.org/coursePrerequisites.description: Requirements for taking the Course. May be completion of another [[Course]] or a textual description like "permission of instructor". Requirements may be a pre-requisite competency, referenced using [[AlignmentObject]].

https://schema.org/dependencies.label: dependencies
https://schema.org/dependencies.description: Prerequisites needed to fulfill steps in article.

https://schema.org/leiCode.label: leiCode
https://schema.org/leiCode.description: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

https://schema.org/loanPaymentAmount.label: loanPaymentAmount
https://schema.org/loanPaymentAmount.description: The amount of money to pay in a single payment.

https://schema.org/LegalForceStatus.label: LegalForceStatus
https://schema.org/LegalForceStatus.description: A list of possible statuses for the legal force of a legislation.

https://schema.org/HealthPlanFormulary.label: HealthPlanFormulary
https://schema.org/HealthPlanFormulary.description: For a given health insurance plan, the specification for costs and coverage of prescription drugs.

https://schema.org/orderItemStatus.label: orderItemStatus
https://schema.org/orderItemStatus.description: The current status of the order item.

https://schema.org/evidenceLevel.label: evidenceLevel
https://schema.org/evidenceLevel.description: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).

https://schema.org/knowsLanguage.label: knowsLanguage
https://schema.org/knowsLanguage.description: Of a [[Person]], and less typically of an [[Organization]], to indicate a known language. We do not distinguish skill levels or reading/writing/speaking/signing here. Use language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

https://schema.org/ProductGroup.label: ProductGroup
https://schema.org/ProductGroup.description:
A ProductGroup represents a group of [[Product]]s that vary only in certain well-described ways, such as by [[size]], [[color]], [[material]] etc.

While a ProductGroup itself is not directly offered for sale, the various varying products that it represents can be. The ProductGroup serves as a prototype or template, standing in for all of the products who have an [[isVariantOf]] relationship to it. As such, properties (including additional types) can be applied to the ProductGroup to represent c

https://schema.org/maintainer.label: maintainer
https://schema.org/maintainer.description: A maintainer of a [[Dataset]], software package ([[SoftwareApplication]]), or other [[Project]]. A maintainer is a [[Person]] or [[Organization]] that manages contributions to, and/or publication of, some (typically complex) artifact. It is common for distributions of software and data to be based on "upstream" sources. When [[maintainer]] is applied to a specific version of something e.g. a particular version or packaging of a [[Dataset]], it is always  possible that the upstream source has a d

https://schema.org/PlayGameAction.label: PlayGameAction
https://schema.org/PlayGameAction.description: The act of playing a video game.

https://schema.org/ShippingDeliveryTime.label: ShippingDeliveryTime
https://schema.org/ShippingDeliveryTime.description: ShippingDeliveryTime provides various pieces of information about delivery times for shipping.

https://schema.org/meetsEmissionStandard.label: meetsEmissionStandard
https://schema.org/meetsEmissionStandard.description: Indicates that the vehicle meets the respective emission standard.

https://schema.org/playerType.label: playerType
https://schema.org/playerType.description: Player type required—for example, Flash or Silverlight.

https://schema.org/populationType.label: populationType
https://schema.org/populationType.description: Indicates the populationType common to all members of a [[StatisticalPopulation]] or all cases within the scope of a [[StatisticalVariable]].

https://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.label: healthPlanCopayOption
https://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.description: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?

https://schema.org/DanceGroup.label: DanceGroup
https://schema.org/DanceGroup.description: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

https://schema.org/timeRequired.label: timeRequired
https://schema.org/timeRequired.description: Approximate or typical time it usually takes to work with or through the content of this work for the typical or target audience.

https://schema.org/tool.label: tool
https://schema.org/tool.description: A sub property of instrument. An object used (but not consumed) when performing instructions or a direction.

https://schema.org/sha256.label: sha256
https://schema.org/sha256.description: The [SHA-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA-2) SHA256 hash of the content of the item. For example, a zero-length input has value 'e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855'.

https://schema.org/isBasedOn.label: isBasedOn
https://schema.org/isBasedOn.description: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaptation.

https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.label: spokenByCharacter
https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.description: The (e.g. fictional) character, Person or Organization to whom the quotation is attributed within the containing CreativeWork.
https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.usage_hint: The person/character who spoke the quotation. Domain is Quotation. For real people quoted, use this or schema:creator.
https://schema.org/spokenByCharacter.example_keywords: said by, spoken by, quoted, attributed to, who said

https://schema.org/downvoteCount.label: downvoteCount
https://schema.org/downvoteCount.description: The number of downvotes this question, answer or comment has received from the community.

https://schema.org/parentService.label: parentService
https://schema.org/parentService.description: A broadcast service to which the broadcast service may belong to such as regional variations of a national channel.

https://schema.org/partOfOrder.label: partOfOrder
https://schema.org/partOfOrder.description: The overall order the items in this delivery were included in.

https://schema.org/LocalBusiness.label: LocalBusiness
https://schema.org/LocalBusiness.description: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

https://schema.org/warning.label: warning
https://schema.org/warning.description: Any FDA or other warnings about the drug (text or URL).

https://schema.org/SuspendAction.label: SuspendAction
https://schema.org/SuspendAction.description: The act of momentarily pausing a device or application (e.g. pause music playback or pause a timer).

https://schema.org/dropoffTime.label: dropoffTime
https://schema.org/dropoffTime.description: When a rental car can be dropped off.

https://schema.org/legislationJurisdicti.label: legislationJurisdiction
https://schema.org/legislationJurisdicti.description: The jurisdiction from which the legislation originates.

https://schema.org/MediaSubscription.label: MediaSubscription
https://schema.org/MediaSubscription.description: A subscription which allows a user to access media including audio, video, books, etc.

https://schema.org/SportsActivityLocatio.label: SportsActivityLocation
https://schema.org/SportsActivityLocatio.description: A sports location, such as a playing field.

https://schema.org/Intangible.label: Intangible
https://schema.org/Intangible.description: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

https://schema.org/MedicalStudyStatus.label: MedicalStudyStatus
https://schema.org/MedicalStudyStatus.description: The status of a medical study. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/Resort.label: Resort
https://schema.org/Resort.description:
A resort is a place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for holidays or vacations. Resorts are places, towns or sometimes commercial establishments operated by a single company (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/answerCount.label: answerCount
https://schema.org/answerCount.description: The number of answers this question has received.

https://schema.org/yearlyRevenue.label: yearlyRevenue
https://schema.org/yearlyRevenue.description: The size of the business in annual revenue.

https://schema.org/NLNonprofitType.label: NLNonprofitType
https://schema.org/NLNonprofitType.description: NLNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the Netherlands.

https://schema.org/Atlas.label: Atlas
https://schema.org/Atlas.description: A collection or bound volume of maps, charts, plates or tables, physical or in media form illustrating any subject.

https://schema.org/MediaEnumeration.label: MediaEnumeration
https://schema.org/MediaEnumeration.description: MediaEnumeration enumerations are lists of codes, labels etc. useful for describing media objects. They may be reflections of externally developed lists, or created at schema.org, or a combination.

https://schema.org/maxPrice.label: maxPrice
https://schema.org/maxPrice.description: The highest price if the price is a range.

https://schema.org/PriceTypeEnumeration.label: PriceTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/PriceTypeEnumeration.description: Enumerates different price types, for example list price, invoice price, and sale price.

https://schema.org/ReturnFeesEnumeration.label: ReturnFeesEnumeration
https://schema.org/ReturnFeesEnumeration.description: Enumerates several kinds of policies for product return fees.

https://schema.org/UnitPriceSpecificatio.label: UnitPriceSpecification
https://schema.org/UnitPriceSpecificatio.description: The price asked for a given offer by the respective organization or person.

https://schema.org/availableStrength.label: availableStrength
https://schema.org/availableStrength.description: An available dosage strength for the drug.

https://schema.org/RadioSeason.label: RadioSeason
https://schema.org/RadioSeason.description: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

https://schema.org/estimatedFlightDurati.label: estimatedFlightDuration
https://schema.org/estimatedFlightDurati.description: The estimated time the flight will take.

https://schema.org/ReturnAction.label: ReturnAction
https://schema.org/ReturnAction.description: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

https://schema.org/lodgingUnitDescriptio.label: lodgingUnitDescription
https://schema.org/lodgingUnitDescriptio.description: A full description of the lodging unit.

https://schema.org/playersOnline.label: playersOnline
https://schema.org/playersOnline.description: Number of players on the server.

https://schema.org/extendedAddress.label: extendedAddress
https://schema.org/extendedAddress.description: An address extension such as an apartment number, C/O or alternative name.

https://schema.org/OfferShippingDetails.label: OfferShippingDetails
https://schema.org/OfferShippingDetails.description:
OfferShippingDetails represents information about shipping destinations.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping rates for different destinations:

One entity for Alaska/Hawaii. A different one for continental US. A different one for all France.

Multiple of these entities can be used to represent different shipping costs and delivery times.

Two entities that are identical but differ in rate and time:

E.g. Cheaper and slower: $5 in 5-7 days
or Fast and expensive

https://schema.org/sugarContent.label: sugarContent
https://schema.org/sugarContent.description: The number of grams of sugar.

https://schema.org/PresentationDigitalDo.label: PresentationDigitalDocument
https://schema.org/PresentationDigitalDo.description: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.

https://schema.org/gtin14.label: gtin14
https://schema.org/gtin14.description: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/Drawing.label: Drawing
https://schema.org/Drawing.description: A picture or diagram made with a pencil, pen, or crayon rather than paint.

https://schema.org/tributary.label: tributary
https://schema.org/tributary.description: The anatomical or organ system that the vein flows into; a larger structure that the vein connects to.

https://schema.org/value.label: value
https://schema.org/value.description:
The value of a [[QuantitativeValue]] (including [[Observation]]) or property value node.

* For [[QuantitativeValue]] and [[MonetaryAmount]], the recommended type for values is 'Number'.
* For [[PropertyValue]], it can be 'Text', 'Number', 'Boolean', or 'StructuredValue'.
* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point.

https://schema.org/BefriendAction.label: BefriendAction
https://schema.org/BefriendAction.description:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone (object) mutually/bidirectionally/symmetrically.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, BefriendAction implies that the connection is reciprocal.

https://schema.org/AgreeAction.label: AgreeAction
https://schema.org/AgreeAction.description: The act of expressing a consistency of opinion with the object. An agent agrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

https://schema.org/brand.label: brand
https://schema.org/brand.description: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.

https://schema.org/streetAddress.label: streetAddress
https://schema.org/streetAddress.description: The street address. For example, 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy.

https://schema.org/codeValue.label: codeValue
https://schema.org/codeValue.description: A short textual code that uniquely identifies the value.

https://schema.org/identifier.label: identifier
https://schema.org/identifier.description: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of [[Thing]], such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#identifierBg) for more details.

https://schema.org/RiverBodyOfWater.label: RiverBodyOfWater
https://schema.org/RiverBodyOfWater.description: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

https://schema.org/downPayment.label: downPayment
https://schema.org/downPayment.description: a type of payment made in cash during the onset of the purchase of an expensive good/service. The payment typically represents only a percentage of the full purchase price.

https://schema.org/skills.label: skills
https://schema.org/skills.description: A statement of knowledge, skill, ability, task or any other assertion expressing a competency that is either claimed by a person, an organization or desired or required to fulfill a role or to work in an occupation.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19MechVentPats.label: cvdNumC19MechVentPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19MechVentPats.description: numc19mechventpats - HOSPITALIZED and VENTILATED: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19 and are on a mechanical ventilator.

https://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.label: associatedAnatomy
https://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.description: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.

https://schema.org/editEIDR.label: editEIDR
https://schema.org/editEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing a specific edit / edition for a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" whose [[titleEIDR]] is "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J" has several edits, e.g. "10.5240/1F2A-E1C5-680A-14C6-E76B-I" and "10.5240/8A35-3BEE-6497-5D12-9E4F-3".

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]] and [[TVEpisode]] can be used for both works and their multiple expressions, it is possi

https://schema.org/unsaturatedFatContent.label: unsaturatedFatContent
https://schema.org/unsaturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of unsaturated fat.

https://schema.org/MedicalScholarlyArtic.label: MedicalScholarlyArticle
https://schema.org/MedicalScholarlyArtic.description: A scholarly article in the medical domain.

https://schema.org/returnFees.label: returnFees
https://schema.org/returnFees.description: The type of return fees for purchased products (for any return reason).

https://schema.org/ConfirmAction.label: ConfirmAction
https://schema.org/ConfirmAction.description:
The act of notifying someone that a future event/action is going to happen as expected.

Related actions:

* [[CancelAction]]: The antonym of ConfirmAction.

https://schema.org/naics.label: naics
https://schema.org/naics.description: The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) code for a particular organization or business person.

https://schema.org/firstPerformance.label: firstPerformance
https://schema.org/firstPerformance.description: The date and place the work was first performed.

https://schema.org/referencesOrder.label: referencesOrder
https://schema.org/referencesOrder.description: The Order(s) related to this Invoice. One or more Orders may be combined into a single Invoice.

https://schema.org/departureGate.label: departureGate
https://schema.org/departureGate.description: Identifier of the flight's departure gate.

https://schema.org/founder.label: founder
https://schema.org/founder.description: A person or organization who founded this organization.

https://schema.org/TVSeries.label: TVSeries
https://schema.org/TVSeries.description: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to TV broadcast and associated online delivery.

https://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.label: expectsAcceptanceOf
https://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.description: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.

https://schema.org/WantAction.label: WantAction
https://schema.org/WantAction.description: The act of expressing a desire about the object. An agent wants an object.

https://schema.org/hasMerchantReturnPoli.label: hasMerchantReturnPolicy
https://schema.org/hasMerchantReturnPoli.description: Specifies a MerchantReturnPolicy that may be applicable.

https://schema.org/artworkSurface.label: artworkSurface
https://schema.org/artworkSurface.description: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

https://schema.org/WPSideBar.label: WPSideBar
https://schema.org/WPSideBar.description: A sidebar section of the page.

https://schema.org/parentOrganization.label: parentOrganization
https://schema.org/parentOrganization.description: The larger organization that this organization is a [[subOrganization]] of, if any.

https://schema.org/possibleTreatment.label: possibleTreatment
https://schema.org/possibleTreatment.description: A possible treatment to address this condition, sign or symptom.

https://schema.org/inverseOf.label: inverseOf
https://schema.org/inverseOf.description: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.

https://schema.org/eligibleWithSupplier.label: eligibleWithSupplier
https://schema.org/eligibleWithSupplier.description: The supplier of the incentivized item/service for which the incentive is valid for such as a utility company, merchant, or contractor.

https://schema.org/seatingCapacity.label: seatingCapacity
https://schema.org/seatingCapacity.description: The number of persons that can be seated (e.g. in a vehicle), both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

https://schema.org/releaseNotes.label: releaseNotes
https://schema.org/releaseNotes.description: Description of what changed in this version.

https://schema.org/PerformAction.label: PerformAction
https://schema.org/PerformAction.description: The act of participating in performance arts.

https://schema.org/hasAdultConsideration.label: hasAdultConsideration
https://schema.org/hasAdultConsideration.description: Used to tag an item to be intended or suitable for consumption or use by adults only.

https://schema.org/exerciseType.label: exerciseType
https://schema.org/exerciseType.description: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.

https://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyVal.label: broadcastFrequencyValue
https://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyVal.description: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.

https://schema.org/originalMediaLink.label: originalMediaLink
https://schema.org/originalMediaLink.description: Link to the page containing an original version of the content, or directly to an online copy of the original [[MediaObject]] content, e.g. video file.

https://schema.org/hasMap.label: hasMap
https://schema.org/hasMap.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/orderQuantity.label: orderQuantity
https://schema.org/orderQuantity.description: The number of the item ordered. If the property is not set, assume the quantity is one.

https://schema.org/areaServed.label: areaServed
https://schema.org/areaServed.description: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.

https://schema.org/artist.label: artist
https://schema.org/artist.description:
The primary artist for a work
    	in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    	primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.

https://schema.org/object.label: object
https://schema.org/object.description: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). E.g. John read *a book*.

https://schema.org/comprisedOf.label: comprisedOf
https://schema.org/comprisedOf.description: Specifying something physically contained by something else. Typically used here for the underlying anatomical structures, such as organs, that comprise the anatomical system.

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.label: customerRemorseReturnFees
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The type of return fees if the product is returned due to customer remorse.

https://schema.org/Class.label: Class
https://schema.org/Class.description: A class, also often called a 'Type'; equivalent to rdfs:Class.

https://schema.org/firstAppearance.label: firstAppearance
https://schema.org/firstAppearance.description: Indicates the first known occurrence of a [[Claim]] in some [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/containedIn.label: containedIn
https://schema.org/containedIn.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.label: globalLocationNumber
https://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.description: The [Global Location Number](http://www.gs1.org/gln) (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.

https://schema.org/handlingTime.label: handlingTime
https://schema.org/handlingTime.description:
The typical delay between the receipt of the order and the goods either leaving the warehouse or being prepared for pickup, in case the delivery method is on site pickup.

In the context of [[ShippingDeliveryTime]], Typical properties: minValue, maxValue, unitCode (d for DAY).  This is by common convention assumed to mean business days (if a unitCode is used, coded as "d"), i.e. only counting days when the business normally operates.

In the context of [[ShippingService]], use the [[ServicePerio

https://schema.org/MathSolver.label: MathSolver
https://schema.org/MathSolver.description: A math solver which is capable of solving a subset of mathematical problems.

https://schema.org/proprietaryName.label: proprietaryName
https://schema.org/proprietaryName.description: Proprietary name given to the diet plan, typically by its originator or creator.

https://schema.org/shippingConditions.label: shippingConditions
https://schema.org/shippingConditions.description: The conditions (constraints, price) applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

https://schema.org/PrependAction.label: PrependAction
https://schema.org/PrependAction.description: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

https://schema.org/FilmAction.label: FilmAction
https://schema.org/FilmAction.description: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.

https://schema.org/availableDeliveryMeth.label: availableDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/availableDeliveryMeth.description: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.

https://schema.org/opponent.label: opponent
https://schema.org/opponent.description: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.

https://schema.org/size.label: size
https://schema.org/size.description: A standardized size of a product or creative work, specified either through a simple textual string (for example 'XL', '32Wx34L'), a  QuantitativeValue with a unitCode, or a comprehensive and structured [[SizeSpecification]]; in other cases, the [[width]], [[height]], [[depth]] and [[weight]] properties may be more applicable.

https://schema.org/courseSchedule.label: courseSchedule
https://schema.org/courseSchedule.description: Represents the length and pace of a course, expressed as a [[Schedule]].

https://schema.org/inventoryLevel.label: inventoryLevel
https://schema.org/inventoryLevel.description: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.

https://schema.org/SolveMathAction.label: SolveMathAction
https://schema.org/SolveMathAction.description: The action that takes in a math expression and directs users to a page potentially capable of solving/simplifying that expression.

https://schema.org/insertion.label: insertion
https://schema.org/insertion.description: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.

https://schema.org/ArriveAction.label: ArriveAction
https://schema.org/ArriveAction.description: The act of arriving at a place. An agent arrives at a destination from a fromLocation, optionally with participants.

https://schema.org/alignmentType.label: alignmentType
https://schema.org/alignmentType.description: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', and 'educationalSubject'.

https://schema.org/printEdition.label: printEdition
https://schema.org/printEdition.description: The edition of the print product in which the NewsArticle appears.

https://schema.org/membershipNumber.label: membershipNumber
https://schema.org/membershipNumber.description: A unique identifier for the membership.

https://schema.org/EmployeeRole.label: EmployeeRole
https://schema.org/EmployeeRole.description: A subclass of OrganizationRole used to describe employee relationships.

https://schema.org/suggestedGender.label: suggestedGender
https://schema.org/suggestedGender.description: The suggested gender of the intended person or audience, for example "male", "female", or "unisex".

https://schema.org/valueAddedTaxIncluded.label: valueAddedTaxIncluded
https://schema.org/valueAddedTaxIncluded.description: Specifies whether the applicable value-added tax (VAT) is included in the price specification or not.

https://schema.org/ExchangeRateSpecifica.label: ExchangeRateSpecification
https://schema.org/ExchangeRateSpecifica.description: A structured value representing exchange rate.

https://schema.org/owner.label: owner
https://schema.org/owner.description: A person or organization who owns this Thing.

https://schema.org/branch.label: branch
https://schema.org/branch.description: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with [[branchOf]].

https://schema.org/hasVariant.label: hasVariant
https://schema.org/hasVariant.description: Indicates a [[Product]] that is a member of this [[ProductGroup]] (or [[ProductModel]]).

https://schema.org/pronouns.label: pronouns
https://schema.org/pronouns.description:
A short string listing or describing pronouns for a person. Typically the person concerned is the best authority as pronouns are a critical part of personal identity and expression. Publishers and consumers of this information are reminded to treat this data responsibly, take country-specific laws related to gender expression into account, and be wary of out-of-date data and drawing unwarranted inferences about the person being described.

In English, formulations such as "they/them", "she/her",

https://schema.org/SoftwareSourceCode.label: SoftwareSourceCode
https://schema.org/SoftwareSourceCode.description: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

https://schema.org/citation.label: citation
https://schema.org/citation.description: A citation or reference to another creative work, such as another publication, web page, scholarly article, etc.

https://schema.org/EmployerAggregateRati.label: EmployerAggregateRating
https://schema.org/EmployerAggregateRati.description: An aggregate rating of an Organization related to its role as an employer.

https://schema.org/EducationalOccupation.label: EducationalOccupationalProgram
https://schema.org/EducationalOccupation.description: A program offered by an institution which determines the learning progress to achieve an outcome, usually a credential like a degree or certificate. This would define a discrete set of opportunities (e.g., job, courses) that together constitute a program with a clear start, end, set of requirements, and transition to a new occupational opportunity (e.g., a job), or sometimes a higher educational opportunity (e.g., an advanced degree).

https://schema.org/courseMode.label: courseMode
https://schema.org/courseMode.description: The medium or means of delivery of the course instance or the mode of study, either as a text label (e.g. "online", "onsite" or "blended"; "synchronous" or "asynchronous"; "full-time" or "part-time") or as a URL reference to a term from a controlled vocabulary (e.g. https://ceds.ed.gov/element/001311#Asynchronous).

https://schema.org/healthPlanNetworkId.label: healthPlanNetworkId
https://schema.org/healthPlanNetworkId.description: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans.)

https://schema.org/event.label: event
https://schema.org/event.description: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.

https://schema.org/phoneticText.label: phoneticText
https://schema.org/phoneticText.description: Representation of a text [[textValue]] using the specified [[speechToTextMarkup]]. For example the city name of Houston in IPA: /ˈhjuːstən/.

https://schema.org/returnShippingFeesAmo.label: returnShippingFeesAmount
https://schema.org/returnShippingFeesAmo.description: Amount of shipping costs for product returns (for any reason). Applicable when property [[returnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

https://schema.org/governmentBenefitsInf.label: governmentBenefitsInfo
https://schema.org/governmentBenefitsInf.description: governmentBenefitsInfo provides information about government benefits associated with a SpecialAnnouncement.

https://schema.org/partOfTVSeries.label: partOfTVSeries
https://schema.org/partOfTVSeries.description: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.

https://schema.org/IncentiveQualifiedExp.label: IncentiveQualifiedExpenseType
https://schema.org/IncentiveQualifiedExp.description: The types of expenses that are covered by the incentive. For example some incentives are only for the goods (tangible items) but the services (labor) are excluded.

https://schema.org/addressRegion.label: addressRegion
https://schema.org/addressRegion.description: The region in which the locality is, and which is in the country. For example, California or another appropriate first-level [Administrative division](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_administrative_divisions_by_country).

https://schema.org/broadcastSubChannel.label: broadcastSubChannel
https://schema.org/broadcastSubChannel.description: The subchannel used for the broadcast.

https://schema.org/Seat.label: Seat
https://schema.org/Seat.description: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

https://schema.org/numberOfDoors.label: numberOfDoors
https://schema.org/numberOfDoors.description: The number of doors.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

https://schema.org/deathDate.label: deathDate
https://schema.org/deathDate.usage_hint: Date of death. Use xsd:date format.
https://schema.org/deathDate.example_keywords: died, death date, date of death, passed away

https://schema.org/LocationFeatureSpecif.label: LocationFeatureSpecification
https://schema.org/LocationFeatureSpecif.description: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

https://schema.org/employerOverview.label: employerOverview
https://schema.org/employerOverview.description: A description of the employer, career opportunities and work environment for this position.

https://schema.org/MerchantReturnPolicyS.label: MerchantReturnPolicySeasonalOverride
https://schema.org/MerchantReturnPolicyS.description: A seasonal override of a return policy, for example used for holidays.

https://schema.org/affiliation.label: affiliation
https://schema.org/affiliation.description: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.

https://schema.org/interactionStatistic.label: interactionStatistic
https://schema.org/interactionStatistic.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.

https://schema.org/UserComments.label: UserComments
https://schema.org/UserComments.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/acceptsReservations.label: acceptsReservations
https://schema.org/acceptsReservations.description: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings ```Yes``` or ```No```.

https://schema.org/workExample.label: workExample
https://schema.org/workExample.description: Example/instance/realization/derivation of the concept of this creative work. E.g. the paperback edition, first edition, or e-book.

https://schema.org/InteractAction.label: InteractAction
https://schema.org/InteractAction.description: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

https://schema.org/touristType.label: touristType
https://schema.org/touristType.description: Attraction suitable for type(s) of tourist. E.g. children, visitors from a particular country, etc.

https://schema.org/LearningResource.label: LearningResource
https://schema.org/LearningResource.description:
The LearningResource type can be used to indicate [[CreativeWork]]s (whether physical or digital) that have a particular and explicit orientation towards learning, education, skill acquisition, and other educational purposes.

[[LearningResource]] is expected to be used as an addition to a primary type such as [[Book]], [[VideoObject]], [[Product]] etc.

[[EducationEvent]] serves a similar purpose for event-like things (e.g. a [[Trip]]). A [[LearningResource]] may be created as a result of an [[

https://schema.org/certificationStatus.label: certificationStatus
https://schema.org/certificationStatus.description: Indicates the current status of a certification: active or inactive. See also  [gs1:certificationStatus](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationStatus).

https://schema.org/xpath.label: xpath
https://schema.org/xpath.description: An XPath, e.g. of a [[SpeakableSpecification]] or [[WebPageElement]]. In the latter case, multiple matches within a page can constitute a single conceptual "Web page element".

https://schema.org/closes.label: closes
https://schema.org/closes.description: The closing hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

https://schema.org/uploadDate.label: uploadDate
https://schema.org/uploadDate.description: Date (including time if available) when this media object was uploaded to this site.

https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBeds.label: cvdNumICUBeds
https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBeds.description: numicubeds - ICU BEDS: Total number of staffed inpatient intensive care unit (ICU) beds.

https://schema.org/iataCode.label: iataCode
https://schema.org/iataCode.description: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.

https://schema.org/gtin8.label: gtin8
https://schema.org/gtin8.description: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/nutrition.label: nutrition
https://schema.org/nutrition.description: Nutrition information about the recipe or menu item.

https://schema.org/typeOfGood.label: typeOfGood
https://schema.org/typeOfGood.description: The product that this structured value is referring to.

https://schema.org/possibleComplication.label: possibleComplication
https://schema.org/possibleComplication.description: A possible unexpected and unfavorable evolution of a medical condition. Complications may include worsening of the signs or symptoms of the disease, extension of the condition to other organ systems, etc.

https://schema.org/BuyAction.label: BuyAction
https://schema.org/BuyAction.description: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

https://schema.org/PriceComponentTypeEnu.label: PriceComponentTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/PriceComponentTypeEnu.description: Enumerates different price components that together make up the total price for an offered product.

https://schema.org/ShippingConditions.label: ShippingConditions
https://schema.org/ShippingConditions.description: ShippingConditions represent a set of constraints and information about the conditions of shipping a product. Such conditions may apply to only a subset of the products being shipped, depending on aspects of the product like weight, size, price, destination, and others. All the specified conditions must be met for this ShippingConditions to apply.

https://schema.org/webFeed.label: webFeed
https://schema.org/webFeed.description: The URL for a feed, e.g. associated with a podcast series, blog, or series of date-stamped updates. This is usually RSS or Atom.

https://schema.org/HealthInsurancePlan.label: HealthInsurancePlan
https://schema.org/HealthInsurancePlan.description: A US-style health insurance plan, including PPOs, EPOs, and HMOs.

https://schema.org/supersededBy.label: supersededBy
https://schema.org/supersededBy.description: Relates a term (i.e. a property, class or enumeration) to one that supersedes it.

https://schema.org/BroadcastEvent.label: BroadcastEvent
https://schema.org/BroadcastEvent.description: An over the air or online broadcast event.

https://schema.org/sku.label: sku
https://schema.org/sku.description: The Stock Keeping Unit (SKU), i.e. a merchant-specific identifier for a product or service, or the product to which the offer refers.

https://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.label: isLiveBroadcast
https://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.description: True if the broadcast is of a live event.

https://schema.org/maxValue.label: maxValue
https://schema.org/maxValue.description: The upper value of some characteristic or property.

https://schema.org/tourBookingPage.label: tourBookingPage
https://schema.org/tourBookingPage.description: A page providing information on how to book a tour of some [[Place]], such as an [[Accommodation]] or [[ApartmentComplex]] in a real estate setting, as well as other kinds of tours as appropriate.

https://schema.org/LoginAction.label: LoginAction
https://schema.org/LoginAction.description: The action of logging into a device or application.

https://schema.org/QuantitativeValue.label: QuantitativeValue
https://schema.org/QuantitativeValue.description: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

https://schema.org/artform.label: artform
https://schema.org/artform.description: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.

https://schema.org/unitCode.label: unitCode
https://schema.org/unitCode.description: The unit of measurement given using the UN/CEFACT Common Code (3 characters) or a URL. Other codes than the UN/CEFACT Common Code may be used with a prefix followed by a colon.

https://schema.org/materialExtent.label: materialExtent
https://schema.org/materialExtent.description: The quantity of the materials being described or an expression of the physical space they occupy.

https://schema.org/softwareRequirements.label: softwareRequirements
https://schema.org/softwareRequirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

https://schema.org/ReportedDoseSchedule.label: ReportedDoseSchedule
https://schema.org/ReportedDoseSchedule.description: A patient-reported or observed dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

https://schema.org/WPFooter.label: WPFooter
https://schema.org/WPFooter.description: The footer section of the page.

https://schema.org/superEvent.label: superEvent
https://schema.org/superEvent.description: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

https://schema.org/CancelAction.label: CancelAction
https://schema.org/CancelAction.description:
The act of asserting that a future event/action is no longer going to happen.

Related actions:

* [[ConfirmAction]]: The antonym of CancelAction.

https://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.label: expectedArrivalFrom
https://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.description: The earliest date the package may arrive.

https://schema.org/LoanOrCredit.label: LoanOrCredit
https://schema.org/LoanOrCredit.description: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money, or line of credit, under agreed terms and charges.

https://schema.org/PaymentStatusType.label: PaymentStatusType
