https://schema.org/PaymentStatusType.description: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.

https://schema.org/OnDemandEvent.label: OnDemandEvent
https://schema.org/OnDemandEvent.description: A publication event, e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

https://schema.org/SequentialArt.label: SequentialArt
https://schema.org/SequentialArt.description: An art forms that use images deployed in a specific order for the purpose of graphic storytelling (i.e., narration of graphic stories) or conveying information. Examples of SequentialArt are Franco-Belgian Bande Dessinée, Comics in the USA and 漫画 (Manga) in Japan.

https://schema.org/domainIncludes.label: domainIncludes
https://schema.org/domainIncludes.description: Relates a property to a class that is (one of) the type(s) the property is expected to be used on.

https://schema.org/distinguishingSign.label: distinguishingSign
https://schema.org/distinguishingSign.description: One of a set of signs and symptoms that can be used to distinguish this diagnosis from others in the differential diagnosis.

https://schema.org/ccRecipient.label: ccRecipient
https://schema.org/ccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient copied on a message.

https://schema.org/measurementMethod.label: measurementMethod
https://schema.org/measurementMethod.description: A subproperty of [[measurementTechnique]] that can be used for specifying specific methods, in particular via [[MeasurementMethodEnum]].

https://schema.org/employmentUnit.label: employmentUnit
https://schema.org/employmentUnit.description: Indicates the department, unit and/or facility where the employee reports and/or in which the job is to be performed.

https://schema.org/recordLabel.label: recordLabel
https://schema.org/recordLabel.description: The label that issued the release.

https://schema.org/legalName.label: legalName
https://schema.org/legalName.description: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.

https://schema.org/SearchRescueOrganizat.label: SearchRescueOrganization
https://schema.org/SearchRescueOrganizat.description: A Search and Rescue organization of some kind.

https://schema.org/recipeIngredient.label: recipeIngredient
https://schema.org/recipeIngredient.description: An ingredient or ordered list of ingredients and potentially quantities used in the recipe, e.g. 1 cup of sugar, flour or garlic.  The ingredients can be represented as free text or more structured values.

https://schema.org/category.label: category
https://schema.org/category.description: A category for the item. Greater signs or slashes can be used to informally indicate a category hierarchy.

https://schema.org/MenuItem.label: MenuItem
https://schema.org/MenuItem.description: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

https://schema.org/healthCondition.label: healthCondition
https://schema.org/healthCondition.description: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.

https://schema.org/Drug.label: Drug
https://schema.org/Drug.description: A chemical or biologic substance, used as a medical therapy, that has a physiological effect on an organism. Here the term drug is used interchangeably with the term medicine although clinical knowledge makes a clear difference between them.

https://schema.org/ExerciseAction.label: ExerciseAction
https://schema.org/ExerciseAction.description: The act of participating in exertive activity for the purposes of improving health and fitness.

https://schema.org/membershipPointsEarne.label: membershipPointsEarned
https://schema.org/membershipPointsEarne.description: The number of membership points earned by the member. If necessary, the unitText can be used to express the units the points are issued in. (E.g. stars, miles, etc.)

https://schema.org/follows.label: follows
https://schema.org/follows.description: The most generic uni-directional social relation.

https://schema.org/lesserOrEqual.label: lesserOrEqual
https://schema.org/lesserOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

https://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.label: beneficiaryBank
https://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.description: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary.

https://schema.org/BrokerageAccount.label: BrokerageAccount
https://schema.org/BrokerageAccount.description: An account that allows an investor to deposit funds and place investment orders with a licensed broker or brokerage firm.

https://schema.org/tocContinuation.label: tocContinuation
https://schema.org/tocContinuation.description: A [[HyperTocEntry]] can have a [[tocContinuation]] indicated, which is another [[HyperTocEntry]] that would be the default next item to play or render.

https://schema.org/certificationRating.label: certificationRating
https://schema.org/certificationRating.description: Rating of a certification instance (as defined by an independent certification body). Typically this rating can be used to rate the level to which the requirements of the certification instance are fulfilled. See also [gs1:certificationValue](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationValue).

https://schema.org/prescribingInfo.label: prescribingInfo
https://schema.org/prescribingInfo.description: Link to prescribing information for the drug.

https://schema.org/hasTierBenefit.label: hasTierBenefit
https://schema.org/hasTierBenefit.description: A member benefit for a particular tier of a loyalty program.

https://schema.org/measurementDenominato.label: measurementDenominator
https://schema.org/measurementDenominato.description: Identifies the denominator variable when an observation represents a ratio or percentage.

https://schema.org/DiagnosticProcedure.label: DiagnosticProcedure
https://schema.org/DiagnosticProcedure.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for diagnostic, as opposed to therapeutic, purposes.

https://schema.org/isTierOf.label: isTierOf
https://schema.org/isTierOf.description: The member program this tier is a part of.

https://schema.org/spatial.label: spatial
https://schema.org/spatial.description:
The "spatial" property can be used in cases when more specific properties
(e.g. [[locationCreated]], [[spatialCoverage]], [[contentLocation]]) are not known to be appropriate.

https://schema.org/language.label: language
https://schema.org/language.description: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

https://schema.org/HealthPlanCostSharing.label: HealthPlanCostSharingSpecification
https://schema.org/HealthPlanCostSharing.description: A description of costs to the patient under a given network or formulary.

https://schema.org/valueReference.label: valueReference
https://schema.org/valueReference.description: A secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature or a type of measurement.

https://schema.org/carrierRequirements.label: carrierRequirements
https://schema.org/carrierRequirements.description: Specifies specific carrier(s) requirements for the application (e.g. an application may only work on a specific carrier network).

https://schema.org/TravelAction.label: TravelAction
https://schema.org/TravelAction.description: The act of traveling from a fromLocation to a destination by a specified mode of transport, optionally with participants.

https://schema.org/molecularFormula.label: molecularFormula
https://schema.org/molecularFormula.description: The empirical formula is the simplest whole number ratio of all the atoms in a molecule.

https://schema.org/reviewCount.label: reviewCount
https://schema.org/reviewCount.description: The count of total number of reviews.

https://schema.org/cookingMethod.label: cookingMethod
https://schema.org/cookingMethod.description: The method of cooking, such as Frying, Steaming, ...

https://schema.org/courseWorkload.label: courseWorkload
https://schema.org/courseWorkload.description: The amount of work expected of students taking the course, often provided as a figure per week or per month, and may be broken down by type. For example, "2 hours of lectures, 1 hour of lab work and 3 hours of independent study per week".

https://schema.org/associatedClaimReview.label: associatedClaimReview
https://schema.org/associatedClaimReview.description: An associated [[ClaimReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

https://schema.org/releaseOf.label: releaseOf
https://schema.org/releaseOf.description: The album this is a release of.

https://schema.org/MedicalObservationalS.label: MedicalObservationalStudyDesign
https://schema.org/MedicalObservationalS.description: Design models for observational medical studies. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/videoFormat.label: videoFormat
https://schema.org/videoFormat.description: The type of screening or video broadcast used (e.g. IMAX, 3D, SD, HD, etc.).

https://schema.org/homeTeam.label: homeTeam
https://schema.org/homeTeam.description: The home team in a sports event.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OFMechVentPa.label: cvdNumC19OFMechVentPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OFMechVentPa.description: numc19ofmechventpats - ED/OVERFLOW and VENTILATED: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed and on a mechanical ventilator.

https://schema.org/parentTaxon.label: parentTaxon
https://schema.org/parentTaxon.description: Closest parent taxon of the taxon in question.

https://schema.org/DeactivateAction.label: DeactivateAction
https://schema.org/DeactivateAction.description: The act of stopping or deactivating a device or application (e.g. stopping a timer or turning off a flashlight).

https://schema.org/MovieSeries.label: MovieSeries
https://schema.org/MovieSeries.description: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

https://schema.org/elevation.label: elevation
https://schema.org/elevation.description: The elevation of a location ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)). Values may be of the form 'NUMBER UNIT\_OF\_MEASUREMENT' (e.g., '1,000 m', '3,200 ft') while numbers alone should be assumed to be a value in meters.

https://schema.org/gtin13.label: gtin13
https://schema.org/gtin13.description: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceding zero. See [GS1 GTIN Summary](http://www.gs1.org/barcodes/technical/idkeys/gtin) for more details.

https://schema.org/Observation.label: Observation
https://schema.org/Observation.description: Instances of the class [[Observation]] are used to specify observations about an entity at a particular time. The principal properties of an [[Observation]] are [[observationAbout]], [[measuredProperty]], [[statType]], [[value] and [[observationDate]]  and [[measuredProperty]]. Some but not all Observations represent a [[QuantitativeValue]]. Quantitative observations can be about a [[StatisticalVariable]], which is an abstract specification about which we can make observations that are grounded

https://schema.org/subTrip.label: subTrip
https://schema.org/subTrip.description: Identifies a [[Trip]] that is a subTrip of this Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

https://schema.org/FMRadioChannel.label: FMRadioChannel
https://schema.org/FMRadioChannel.description: A radio channel that uses FM.

https://schema.org/ChemicalSubstance.label: ChemicalSubstance
https://schema.org/ChemicalSubstance.description: A chemical substance is 'a portion of matter of constant composition, composed of molecular entities of the same type or of different types' (source: [ChEBI:59999](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/chebi/searchId.do?chebiId=59999)).

https://schema.org/USNonprofitType.label: USNonprofitType
https://schema.org/USNonprofitType.description: USNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the United States.

https://schema.org/producer.label: producer
https://schema.org/producer.description: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, TV/radio series etc.).

https://schema.org/audienceType.label: audienceType
https://schema.org/audienceType.description: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HOPats.label: cvdNumC19HOPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HOPats.description: numc19hopats - HOSPITAL ONSET: Patients hospitalized in an NHSN inpatient care location with onset of suspected or confirmed COVID-19 14 or more days after hospitalization.

https://schema.org/procedureType.label: procedureType
https://schema.org/procedureType.description: The type of procedure, for example Surgical, Noninvasive, or Percutaneous.

https://schema.org/ComicIssue.label: ComicIssue
https://schema.org/ComicIssue.description:
Individual comic issues are serially published as
    	part of a larger series. For the sake of consistency, even one-shot issues
    	belong to a series comprised of a single issue. All comic issues can be
    	uniquely identified by: the combination of the name and volume number of the
    	series to which the issue belongs; the issue number; and the variant
    	description of the issue (if any).

https://schema.org/Reservoir.label: Reservoir
https://schema.org/Reservoir.description: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

https://schema.org/vehicleSpecialUsage.label: vehicleSpecialUsage
https://schema.org/vehicleSpecialUsage.description: Indicates whether the vehicle has been used for special purposes, like commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi. The legislation in many countries requires this information to be revealed when offering a car for sale.

https://schema.org/safetyConsideration.label: safetyConsideration
https://schema.org/safetyConsideration.description: Any potential safety concern associated with the supplement. May include interactions with other drugs and foods, pregnancy, breastfeeding, known adverse reactions, and documented efficacy of the supplement.

https://schema.org/offers.label: offers
https://schema.org/offers.description: An offer to provide this item—for example, an offer to sell a product, rent the DVD of a movie, perform a service, or give away tickets to an event. Use [[businessFunction]] to indicate the kind of transaction offered, i.e. sell, lease, etc. This property can also be used to describe a [[Demand]]. While this property is listed as expected on a number of common types, it can be used in others. In that case, using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the natur

https://schema.org/TextDigitalDocument.label: TextDigitalDocument
https://schema.org/TextDigitalDocument.description: A file composed primarily of text.

https://schema.org/departureBoatTerminal.label: departureBoatTerminal
https://schema.org/departureBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat departs.

https://schema.org/mentions.label: mentions
https://schema.org/mentions.description: Indicates that the CreativeWork contains a reference to, but is not necessarily about a concept.

https://schema.org/vehicleSeatingCapacit.label: vehicleSeatingCapacity
https://schema.org/vehicleSeatingCapacit.description: The number of passengers that can be seated in the vehicle, both in terms of the physical space available, and in terms of limitations set by law.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62 for persons.

https://schema.org/APIReference.label: APIReference
https://schema.org/APIReference.description: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

https://schema.org/signDetected.label: signDetected
https://schema.org/signDetected.description: A sign detected by the test.

https://schema.org/EnergyStarEnergyEffic.label: EnergyStarEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
https://schema.org/EnergyStarEnergyEffic.description: Used to indicate whether a product is EnergyStar certified.

https://schema.org/Quiz.label: Quiz
https://schema.org/Quiz.description: Quiz: A test of knowledge, skills and abilities.

https://schema.org/acceptedOffer.label: acceptedOffer
https://schema.org/acceptedOffer.description: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.

https://schema.org/costPerUnit.label: costPerUnit
https://schema.org/costPerUnit.description: The cost per unit of the drug.

https://schema.org/Vein.label: Vein
https://schema.org/Vein.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries blood to the heart.

https://schema.org/encodings.label: encodings
https://schema.org/encodings.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/servicePhone.label: servicePhone
https://schema.org/servicePhone.description: The phone number to use to access the service.

https://schema.org/RadioEpisode.label: RadioEpisode
https://schema.org/RadioEpisode.description: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

https://schema.org/workload.label: workload
https://schema.org/workload.description: Quantitative measure of the physiologic output of the exercise; also referred to as energy expenditure.

https://schema.org/loanPaymentFrequency.label: loanPaymentFrequency
https://schema.org/loanPaymentFrequency.description: Frequency of payments due, i.e. number of months between payments. This is defined as a frequency, i.e. the reciprocal of a period of time.

https://schema.org/Legislation.label: Legislation
https://schema.org/Legislation.description: A legal document such as an act, decree, bill, etc. (enforceable or not) or a component of a legal act (like an article).

https://schema.org/valueName.label: valueName
https://schema.org/valueName.description: Indicates the name of the PropertyValueSpecification to be used in URL templates and form encoding in a manner analogous to HTML's input@name.

https://schema.org/timeToComplete.label: timeToComplete
https://schema.org/timeToComplete.description: The expected length of time to complete the program if attending full-time.

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.label: customerRemorseReturnShippingFeesAmount
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The amount of shipping costs if a product is returned due to customer remorse. Applicable when property [[customerRemorseReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

https://schema.org/seasonalOverride.label: seasonalOverride
https://schema.org/seasonalOverride.description: Limited period during which these shipping conditions apply.

https://schema.org/VacationRental.label: VacationRental
https://schema.org/VacationRental.description: A kind of lodging business that focuses on renting single properties for limited time.

https://schema.org/HotelRoom.label: HotelRoom
https://schema.org/HotelRoom.description:
A hotel room is a single room in a hotel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/AcceptAction.label: AcceptAction
https://schema.org/AcceptAction.description:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[RejectAction]]: The antonym of AcceptAction.

https://schema.org/DeliveryEvent.label: DeliveryEvent
https://schema.org/DeliveryEvent.description: An event involving the delivery of an item.

https://schema.org/ListItem.label: ListItem
https://schema.org/ListItem.description: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

https://schema.org/domiciledMortgage.label: domiciledMortgage
https://schema.org/domiciledMortgage.description: Whether borrower is a resident of the jurisdiction where the property is located.

https://schema.org/study.label: study
https://schema.org/study.description: A medical study or trial related to this entity.

https://schema.org/lowPrice.label: lowPrice
https://schema.org/lowPrice.description:
The lowest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/Joint.label: Joint
https://schema.org/Joint.description: The anatomical location at which two or more bones make contact.

https://schema.org/isFamilyFriendly.label: isFamilyFriendly
https://schema.org/isFamilyFriendly.description: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.

https://schema.org/DeleteAction.label: DeleteAction
https://schema.org/DeleteAction.description: The act of editing a recipient by removing one of its objects.

https://schema.org/referenceQuantity.label: referenceQuantity
https://schema.org/referenceQuantity.description: The reference quantity for which a certain price applies, e.g. 1 EUR per 4 kWh of electricity. This property is a replacement for unitOfMeasurement for the advanced cases where the price does not relate to a standard unit.

https://schema.org/serviceUrl.label: serviceUrl
https://schema.org/serviceUrl.description: The website to access the service.

https://schema.org/mileageFromOdometer.label: mileageFromOdometer
https://schema.org/mileageFromOdometer.description: The total distance travelled by the particular vehicle since its initial production, as read from its odometer.\n\nTypical unit code(s): KMT for kilometers, SMI for statute miles.

https://schema.org/riskFactor.label: riskFactor
https://schema.org/riskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable factor that increases the risk of a patient contracting this condition, e.g. age,  coexisting condition.

https://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.label: accessibilityFeature
https://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.description: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityFeature-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/legislationLegalForce.label: legislationLegalForce
https://schema.org/legislationLegalForce.description: Whether the legislation is currently in force, not in force, or partially in force.

https://schema.org/monthsOfExperience.label: monthsOfExperience
https://schema.org/monthsOfExperience.description: Indicates the minimal number of months of experience required for a position.

https://schema.org/secondaryPrevention.label: secondaryPrevention
https://schema.org/secondaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent reoccurrence of the medical condition after an initial episode of the condition.

https://schema.org/ScreeningEvent.label: ScreeningEvent
https://schema.org/ScreeningEvent.description: A screening of a movie or other video.

https://schema.org/addressLocality.label: addressLocality
https://schema.org/addressLocality.description: The locality in which the street address is, and which is in the region. For example, Mountain View.

https://schema.org/Game.label: Game
https://schema.org/Game.description: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting.

https://schema.org/datasetTimeInterval.label: datasetTimeInterval
https://schema.org/datasetTimeInterval.description: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

https://schema.org/ScheduleAction.label: ScheduleAction
https://schema.org/ScheduleAction.description:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.

Related actions:

* [[ReserveAction]]: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

https://schema.org/MiddleSchool.label: MiddleSchool
https://schema.org/MiddleSchool.description: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

https://schema.org/jobImmediateStart.label: jobImmediateStart
https://schema.org/jobImmediateStart.description: An indicator as to whether a position is available for an immediate start.

https://schema.org/claimReviewed.label: claimReviewed
https://schema.org/claimReviewed.description: A short summary of the specific claims reviewed in a ClaimReview.

https://schema.org/MedicalImagingTechniq.label: MedicalImagingTechnique
https://schema.org/MedicalImagingTechniq.description: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/nationality.label: nationality
https://schema.org/nationality.usage_hint: Nationality of a person. Use for current/primary nationality. For historical citizenships with dates, consider Role pattern.

https://schema.org/step.label: step
https://schema.org/step.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection.

https://schema.org/ReadAction.label: ReadAction
https://schema.org/ReadAction.description: The act of consuming written content.

https://schema.org/CurrencyConversionSer.label: CurrencyConversionService
https://schema.org/CurrencyConversionSer.description: A service to convert funds from one currency to another currency.

https://schema.org/containsPlace.label: containsPlace
https://schema.org/containsPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

https://schema.org/memberOf.label: memberOf
https://schema.org/memberOf.description: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.
https://schema.org/memberOf.usage_hint: Organization someone is a member of. Use Role pattern if membership has dates.
https://schema.org/memberOf.example_keywords: member of, belongs to, part of, affiliated with

https://schema.org/DrawAction.label: DrawAction
https://schema.org/DrawAction.description: The act of producing a visual/graphical representation of an object, typically with a pen/pencil and paper as instruments.

https://schema.org/suggestedAnswer.label: suggestedAnswer
https://schema.org/suggestedAnswer.description: An answer (possibly one of several, possibly incorrect) to a Question, e.g. on a Question/Answer site.

https://schema.org/bookingTime.label: bookingTime
https://schema.org/bookingTime.description: The date and time the reservation was booked.

https://schema.org/gameServer.label: gameServer
https://schema.org/gameServer.description: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.

https://schema.org/videoFrameSize.label: videoFrameSize
https://schema.org/videoFrameSize.description: The frame size of the video.

https://schema.org/ShareAction.label: ShareAction
https://schema.org/ShareAction.description: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

https://schema.org/MedicalSign.label: MedicalSign
https://schema.org/MedicalSign.description: Any physical manifestation of a person's medical condition discoverable by objective diagnostic tests or physical examination.

https://schema.org/code.label: code
https://schema.org/code.description: A medical code for the entity, taken from a controlled vocabulary or ontology such as ICD-9, DiseasesDB, MeSH, SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, etc.

https://schema.org/dateIssued.label: dateIssued
https://schema.org/dateIssued.description: The date the ticket was issued.

https://schema.org/version.label: version
https://schema.org/version.description: The version of the CreativeWork embodied by a specified resource.

https://schema.org/availableFrom.label: availableFrom
https://schema.org/availableFrom.description: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.

https://schema.org/employmentType.label: employmentType
https://schema.org/employmentType.description: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).

https://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPol.label: actionableFeedbackPolicy
https://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPol.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other news-related [[Organization]], a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.

https://schema.org/floorLimit.label: floorLimit
https://schema.org/floorLimit.description: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.

https://schema.org/numberOfBeds.label: numberOfBeds
https://schema.org/numberOfBeds.description: The quantity of the given bed type available in the HotelRoom, Suite, House, or Apartment.

https://schema.org/purchaseDate.label: purchaseDate
https://schema.org/purchaseDate.description: The date the item, e.g. vehicle, was purchased by the current owner.

https://schema.org/originalMediaContextD.label: originalMediaContextDescription
https://schema.org/originalMediaContextD.description: Describes, in a [[MediaReview]] when dealing with [[DecontextualizedContent]], background information that can contribute to better interpretation of the [[MediaObject]].

https://schema.org/multipleValues.label: multipleValues
https://schema.org/multipleValues.description: Whether multiple values are allowed for the property.  Default is false.

https://schema.org/ServicePeriod.label: ServicePeriod
https://schema.org/ServicePeriod.description: ServicePeriod represents a duration with some constraints about cutoff time and business days. This is used e.g. in shipping for handling times or transit time.

https://schema.org/events.label: events
https://schema.org/events.description: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.

https://schema.org/OrderAction.label: OrderAction
https://schema.org/OrderAction.description: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

https://schema.org/contactlessPayment.label: contactlessPayment
https://schema.org/contactlessPayment.description: A secure method for consumers to purchase products or services via debit, credit or smartcards by using RFID or NFC technology.

https://schema.org/recordedIn.label: recordedIn
https://schema.org/recordedIn.description: The CreativeWork that captured all or part of this Event.

https://schema.org/flightNumber.label: flightNumber
https://schema.org/flightNumber.description: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnShipp.label: itemDefectReturnShippingFeesAmount
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnShipp.description: Amount of shipping costs for defect product returns. Applicable when property [[itemDefectReturnFees]] equals [[ReturnShippingFees]].

https://schema.org/CoverArt.label: CoverArt
https://schema.org/CoverArt.description: The artwork on the outer surface of a CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/remainingAttendeeCapa.label: remainingAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/remainingAttendeeCapa.description: The number of attendee places for an event that remain unallocated.

https://schema.org/Chapter.label: Chapter
https://schema.org/Chapter.description: One of the sections into which a book is divided. A chapter usually has a section number or a name.

https://schema.org/hasTiers.label: hasTiers
https://schema.org/hasTiers.description: The tiers of a member program.

https://schema.org/birthDate.label: birthDate
https://schema.org/birthDate.usage_hint: Date of birth. Use xsd:date format. Only for actual birth, not other events.
https://schema.org/birthDate.example_keywords: born, birth date, date of birth, birthday

https://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.label: ineligibleRegion
https://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.\n\nSee also [[eligibleRegion]].

https://schema.org/blogPost.label: blogPost
https://schema.org/blogPost.description: A posting that is part of this blog.

https://schema.org/arrivalBoatTerminal.label: arrivalBoatTerminal
https://schema.org/arrivalBoatTerminal.description: The terminal or port from which the boat arrives.

https://schema.org/permittedUsage.label: permittedUsage
https://schema.org/permittedUsage.description: Indications regarding the permitted usage of the accommodation.

https://schema.org/hasEnergyConsumptionD.label: hasEnergyConsumptionDetails
https://schema.org/hasEnergyConsumptionD.description: Defines the energy efficiency Category (also known as "class" or "rating") for a product according to an international energy efficiency standard.

https://schema.org/endorsers.label: endorsers
https://schema.org/endorsers.description: People or organizations that endorse the plan.

https://schema.org/PerformingArtsEvent.label: PerformingArtsEvent
https://schema.org/PerformingArtsEvent.description:
Live performance Event of the performing arts (music, theatre, dance, acrobatics, spoken word), including performance art and performative sports (e.g. choreographed forms of martial arts, figure skating, competitive ballroom dancing).

Note: Use additionalType to differentiate between productions / shows (PerformanceWork, EventSeries), tours (EventSeries), and individual

https://schema.org/RsvpResponseType.label: RsvpResponseType
https://schema.org/RsvpResponseType.description: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

https://schema.org/purchaseType.label: purchaseType
https://schema.org/purchaseType.description: Optional. The type of purchase the consumer must make in order to qualify for this incentive.

https://schema.org/EndorsementRating.label: EndorsementRating
https://schema.org/EndorsementRating.description:
An EndorsementRating is a rating that expresses some level of endorsement, for example inclusion in a "critic's pick" blog, a
"Like" or "+1" on a social network. It can be considered the [[result]] of an [[EndorseAction]] in which the [[object]] of the action is rated positively by
some [[agent]]. As is common elsewhere in schema.org, it is sometimes more useful to describe the results of such an action without explicitly describing the [[Action]].

An [[EndorsementRating]] may be part of a nume

https://schema.org/operatingSystem.label: operatingSystem
https://schema.org/operatingSystem.description: Operating systems supported (Windows 7, OS X 10.6, Android 1.6).

https://schema.org/referee.label: referee
https://schema.org/referee.description: An official who watches a game or match closely to enforce the rules and arbitrate on matters arising from the play such as referees, umpires or judges. The name of the effective function can vary according to the sport.

https://schema.org/LifestyleModification.label: LifestyleModification
https://schema.org/LifestyleModification.description: A process of care involving exercise, changes to diet, fitness routines, and other lifestyle changes aimed at improving a health condition.

https://schema.org/NonprofitType.label: NonprofitType
https://schema.org/NonprofitType.description: NonprofitType enumerates several kinds of official non-profit types of which a non-profit organization can be.

https://schema.org/applicationDeadline.label: applicationDeadline
https://schema.org/applicationDeadline.description: The date on which the program stops collecting applications for the next enrollment cycle. Flexible application deadlines (for example, a program with rolling admissions) can be described in a textual string, rather than as a DateTime.

https://schema.org/gameEdition.label: gameEdition
https://schema.org/gameEdition.description: The edition of a video game.

https://schema.org/LegislationObject.label: LegislationObject
https://schema.org/LegislationObject.description: A specific object or file containing a Legislation. Note that the same Legislation can be published in multiple files. For example, a digitally signed PDF, a plain PDF and an HTML version.

https://schema.org/MedicalWebPage.label: MedicalWebPage
https://schema.org/MedicalWebPage.description: A web page that provides medical information.

https://schema.org/OfferItemCondition.label: OfferItemCondition
https://schema.org/OfferItemCondition.description: A list of possible conditions for the item.

https://schema.org/PostalCodeRangeSpecif.label: PostalCodeRangeSpecification
https://schema.org/PostalCodeRangeSpecif.description: Indicates a range of postal codes, usually defined as the set of valid codes between [[postalCodeBegin]] and [[postalCodeEnd]], inclusively.

https://schema.org/relatedAnatomy.label: relatedAnatomy
https://schema.org/relatedAnatomy.description: Anatomical systems or structures that relate to the superficial anatomy.

https://schema.org/permissionType.label: permissionType
https://schema.org/permissionType.description: The type of permission granted the person, organization, or audience.

https://schema.org/HowTo.label: HowTo
https://schema.org/HowTo.description: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.

https://schema.org/TaxiService.label: TaxiService
https://schema.org/TaxiService.description: A service for a vehicle for hire with a driver for local travel. Fares are usually calculated based on distance traveled.

https://schema.org/replacer.label: replacer
https://schema.org/replacer.description: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.

https://schema.org/associatedDisease.label: associatedDisease
https://schema.org/associatedDisease.description: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.

https://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.label: hospitalAffiliation
https://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.description: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.

https://schema.org/accountId.label: accountId
https://schema.org/accountId.description: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.

https://schema.org/availableOnDevice.label: availableOnDevice
https://schema.org/availableOnDevice.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

https://schema.org/embedUrl.label: embedUrl
https://schema.org/embedUrl.description: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the ```src``` element of an ```embed``` tag and should not be the same as the content of the ```loc``` tag.

https://schema.org/workPerformed.label: workPerformed
https://schema.org/workPerformed.description: A work performed in some event, for example a play performed in a TheaterEvent.

https://schema.org/opens.label: opens
https://schema.org/opens.description: The opening hour of the place or service on the given day(s) of the week.

https://schema.org/musicArrangement.label: musicArrangement
https://schema.org/musicArrangement.description: An arrangement derived from the composition.

https://schema.org/postOp.label: postOp
https://schema.org/postOp.description: A description of the postoperative procedures, care, and/or followups for this device.

https://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpe.label: feesAndCommissionsSpecification
https://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpe.description: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.

https://schema.org/DiagnosticLab.label: DiagnosticLab
https://schema.org/DiagnosticLab.description: A medical laboratory that offers on-site or off-site diagnostic services.

https://schema.org/BedType.label: BedType
https://schema.org/BedType.description: A type of bed. This is used for indicating the bed or beds available in an accommodation.

https://schema.org/author.label: author
https://schema.org/author.description: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.
https://schema.org/author.usage_hint: The author/creator of content. Use for who wrote/said something. Works for CreativeWork, Quotation, etc.
https://schema.org/author.example_keywords: author, writer, creator, who wrote, who said, by

https://schema.org/actionOption.label: actionOption
https://schema.org/actionOption.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

https://schema.org/item.label: item
https://schema.org/item.description: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists').

https://schema.org/postOfficeBoxNumber.label: postOfficeBoxNumber
https://schema.org/postOfficeBoxNumber.description: The post office box number for PO box addresses.

https://schema.org/GiveAction.label: GiveAction
https://schema.org/GiveAction.description:
The act of transferring ownership of an object to a destination. Reciprocal of TakeAction.

Related actions:

* [[TakeAction]]: Reciprocal of GiveAction.
* [[SendAction]]: Unlike SendAction, GiveAction implies that ownership is being transferred (e.g. I may send my laptop to you, but that doesn't mean I'm giving it to you).

https://schema.org/hasBioPolymerSequence.label: hasBioPolymerSequence
https://schema.org/hasBioPolymerSequence.description: A symbolic representation of a BioChemEntity. For example, a nucleotide sequence of a Gene or an amino acid sequence of a Protein.

https://schema.org/requiredMinAge.label: requiredMinAge
https://schema.org/requiredMinAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's minimum age.

https://schema.org/validFrom.label: validFrom
https://schema.org/validFrom.description: The date when the item becomes valid.

https://schema.org/userInteractionCount.label: userInteractionCount
https://schema.org/userInteractionCount.description: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication.

https://schema.org/attendee.label: attendee
https://schema.org/attendee.description: A person or organization attending the event.

https://schema.org/nerve.label: nerve
https://schema.org/nerve.description: The underlying innervation associated with the muscle.

https://schema.org/EnergyEfficiencyEnume.label: EnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
https://schema.org/EnergyEfficiencyEnume.description: Enumerates energy efficiency levels (also known as "classes" or "ratings") and certifications that are part of several international energy efficiency standards.

https://schema.org/contentRating.label: contentRating
https://schema.org/contentRating.description: Official rating of a piece of content—for example, 'MPAA PG-13'.

https://schema.org/subStructure.label: subStructure
https://schema.org/subStructure.description: Component (sub-)structure(s) that comprise this anatomical structure.

https://schema.org/TreatmentIndication.label: TreatmentIndication
https://schema.org/TreatmentIndication.description: An indication for treating an underlying condition, symptom, etc.

https://schema.org/passengerPriorityStat.label: passengerPriorityStatus
https://schema.org/passengerPriorityStat.description: The priority status assigned to a passenger for security or boarding (e.g. FastTrack or Priority).

https://schema.org/priceComponent.label: priceComponent
https://schema.org/priceComponent.description: This property links to all [[UnitPriceSpecification]] nodes that apply in parallel for the [[CompoundPriceSpecification]] node.

https://schema.org/postalCodeBegin.label: postalCodeBegin
https://schema.org/postalCodeBegin.description: First postal code in a range (included).

https://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.label: incentiveCompensation
https://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

https://schema.org/fuelCapacity.label: fuelCapacity
https://schema.org/fuelCapacity.description: The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.\n\nTypical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).

https://schema.org/leaseLength.label: leaseLength
https://schema.org/leaseLength.description: Length of the lease for some [[Accommodation]], either particular to some [[Offer]] or in some cases intrinsic to the property.

https://schema.org/trailerWeight.label: trailerWeight
https://schema.org/trailerWeight.description:
The permitted weight of a trailer attached to the vehicle.

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound
* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/hasBioChemEntityPart.label: hasBioChemEntityPart
https://schema.org/hasBioChemEntityPart.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.

https://schema.org/branchOf.label: branchOf
https://schema.org/branchOf.description: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical) [[branch]].

https://schema.org/DeliveryChargeSpecifi.label: DeliveryChargeSpecification
https://schema.org/DeliveryChargeSpecifi.description: The price for the delivery of an offer using a particular delivery method.

https://schema.org/ListenAction.label: ListenAction
https://schema.org/ListenAction.description: The act of consuming audio content.

https://schema.org/contactPoint.label: contactPoint
https://schema.org/contactPoint.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

https://schema.org/drainsTo.label: drainsTo
https://schema.org/drainsTo.description: The vasculature that the vein drains into.

https://schema.org/collection.label: collection
https://schema.org/collection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

https://schema.org/positiveNotes.label: positiveNotes
https://schema.org/positiveNotes.description:
Provides positive considerations regarding something, for example product highlights or (alongside [[negativeNotes]]) pro/con lists for reviews.

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described.

The property values can be expressed either as unstructured text (repeated as necessary), or if ordered, as a list (in which case the most positive is at the beginning of the

https://schema.org/containedInPlace.label: containedInPlace
https://schema.org/containedInPlace.description: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

https://schema.org/accommodationCategory.label: accommodationCategory
https://schema.org/accommodationCategory.description: Category of an [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions, e.g. RESO (see [PropertySubType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertySubType+Field), and [PropertyType](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/PropertyType+Field) fields  for suggested values).

https://schema.org/dateline.label: dateline
https://schema.org/dateline.description:
A [dateline](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dateline) is a brief piece of text included in news articles that describes where and when the story was written or filed though the date is often omitted. Sometimes only a placename is provided.

Structured representations of dateline-related information can also be expressed more explicitly using [[locationCreated]] (which represents where a work was created, e.g. where a news report was written).  For location depicted or described in the content, us

https://schema.org/BoatTerminal.label: BoatTerminal
https://schema.org/BoatTerminal.description: A terminal for boats, ships, and other water vessels.

https://schema.org/competencyRequired.label: competencyRequired
https://schema.org/competencyRequired.description: Knowledge, skill, ability or personal attribute that must be demonstrated by a person or other entity in order to do something such as earn an Educational Occupational Credential or understand a LearningResource.

https://schema.org/BookSeries.label: BookSeries
https://schema.org/BookSeries.description: A series of books. Included books can be indicated with the hasPart property.

https://schema.org/iupacName.label: iupacName
https://schema.org/iupacName.description: Systematic method of naming chemical compounds as recommended by the International Union of Pure and Applied Chemistry (IUPAC).

https://schema.org/carrier.label: carrier
https://schema.org/carrier.description: 'carrier' is an out-dated term indicating the 'provider' for parcel delivery and flights.

https://schema.org/actionStatus.label: actionStatus
https://schema.org/actionStatus.description: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.

https://schema.org/dosageForm.label: dosageForm
https://schema.org/dosageForm.description: A dosage form in which this drug/supplement is available, e.g. 'tablet', 'suspension', 'injection'.

https://schema.org/reviewAspect.label: reviewAspect
https://schema.org/reviewAspect.description: This Review or Rating is relevant to this part or facet of the itemReviewed.

https://schema.org/typeOfBed.label: typeOfBed
https://schema.org/typeOfBed.description: The type of bed to which the BedDetail refers, i.e. the type of bed available in the quantity indicated by quantity.

https://schema.org/processingTime.label: processingTime
https://schema.org/processingTime.description: Estimated processing time for the service using this channel.

https://schema.org/EnergyConsumptionDeta.label: EnergyConsumptionDetails
https://schema.org/EnergyConsumptionDeta.description: EnergyConsumptionDetails represents information related to the energy efficiency of a product that consumes energy. The information that can be provided is based on international regulations such as for example [EU directive 2017/1369](https://eur-lex.europa.eu/eli/reg/2017/1369/oj) for energy labeling and the [Energy labeling rule](https://www.ftc.gov/enforcement/rules/rulemaking-regulatory-reform-proceedings/energy-water-use-labeling-consumer) under the Energy Policy and Conservation Act (EPCA

https://schema.org/subjectOf.label: subjectOf
https://schema.org/subjectOf.description: A CreativeWork or Event about this Thing.

https://schema.org/foodEvent.label: foodEvent
https://schema.org/foodEvent.description: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.

https://schema.org/relatedDrug.label: relatedDrug
https://schema.org/relatedDrug.description: Any other drug related to this one, for example commonly-prescribed alternatives.

https://schema.org/HyperToc.label: HyperToc
https://schema.org/HyperToc.description: A HyperToc represents a hypertext table of contents for complex media objects, such as [[VideoObject]], [[AudioObject]]. Items in the table of contents are indicated using the [[tocEntry]] property, and typed [[HyperTocEntry]]. For cases where the same larger work is split into multiple files, [[associatedMedia]] can be used on individual [[HyperTocEntry]] items.

https://schema.org/encodesBioChemEntity.label: encodesBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/encodesBioChemEntity.description: Another BioChemEntity encoded by this one.

https://schema.org/ComicStory.label: ComicStory
https://schema.org/ComicStory.description:
The term "story" is any indivisible, re-printable
    	unit of a comic, including the interior stories, covers, and backmatter. Most
    	comics have at least two stories: a cover (ComicCoverArt) and an interior story.

https://schema.org/naturalProgression.label: naturalProgression
https://schema.org/naturalProgression.description: The expected progression of the condition if it is not treated and allowed to progress naturally.

https://schema.org/LiveBlogPosting.label: LiveBlogPosting
https://schema.org/LiveBlogPosting.description: A [[LiveBlogPosting]] is a [[BlogPosting]] intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.label: healthPlanCostSharing
https://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.description: The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.

https://schema.org/MedicalEntity.label: MedicalEntity
https://schema.org/MedicalEntity.description: The most generic type of entity related to health and the practice of medicine.

https://schema.org/significance.label: significance
https://schema.org/significance.description: The significance associated with the superficial anatomy; as an example, how characteristics of the superficial anatomy can suggest underlying medical conditions or courses of treatment.

https://schema.org/Table.label: Table
https://schema.org/Table.description: A table on a Web page.

https://schema.org/lodgingUnitType.label: lodgingUnitType
https://schema.org/lodgingUnitType.description: Textual description of the unit type (including suite vs. room, size of bed, etc.).

https://schema.org/trainingSalary.label: trainingSalary
https://schema.org/trainingSalary.description: The estimated salary earned while in the program.

https://schema.org/recourseLoan.label: recourseLoan
https://schema.org/recourseLoan.description: The only way you get the money back in the event of default is the security. Recourse is where you still have the opportunity to go back to the borrower for the rest of the money.

https://schema.org/eligibleCustomerType.label: eligibleCustomerType
https://schema.org/eligibleCustomerType.description: The type(s) of customers for which the given offer is valid.

https://schema.org/CommentAction.label: CommentAction
https://schema.org/CommentAction.description: The act of generating a comment about a subject.

https://schema.org/sdLicense.label: sdLicense
https://schema.org/sdLicense.description: A license document that applies to this structured data, typically indicated by URL.

https://schema.org/shippingDestination.label: shippingDestination
https://schema.org/shippingDestination.description: indicates (possibly multiple) shipping destinations. These can be defined in several ways, e.g. postalCode ranges.

https://schema.org/UserPageVisits.label: UserPageVisits
https://schema.org/UserPageVisits.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/isInvolvedInBiologica.label: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess
https://schema.org/isInvolvedInBiologica.description: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

https://schema.org/AggregateRating.label: AggregateRating
https://schema.org/AggregateRating.description: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

https://schema.org/incentivizedItem.label: incentivizedItem
https://schema.org/incentivizedItem.description:
The type or specific product(s) and/or service(s) being incentivized.

DefinedTermSets are used for product and service categories such as the United Nations Standard Products and Services Code:

{ "@type": "DefinedTerm", "inDefinedTermSet": "https://www.unspsc.org/", "termCode": "261315XX", "name": "Photovoltaic module" }

For a specific product or service, use the Product type:

{ "@type": "Product", "name": "Kenmore White

https://schema.org/ItemAvailability.label: ItemAvailability
https://schema.org/ItemAvailability.description: A list of possible product availability options.

https://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineRecom.label: MedicalGuidelineRecommendation
https://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineRecom.description: A guideline recommendation that is regarded as efficacious and where quality of the data supporting the recommendation is sound.

https://schema.org/programmingModel.label: programmingModel
https://schema.org/programmingModel.description: Indicates whether API is managed or unmanaged.

https://schema.org/contentReferenceTime.label: contentReferenceTime
https://schema.org/contentReferenceTime.description: The specific time described by a creative work, for works (e.g. articles, video objects etc.) that emphasise a particular moment within an Event.

https://schema.org/ItemList.label: ItemList
https://schema.org/ItemList.description: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

https://schema.org/agent.label: agent
https://schema.org/agent.description: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). E.g. *John* wrote a book.

https://schema.org/recognizedBy.label: recognizedBy
https://schema.org/recognizedBy.description: An organization that acknowledges the validity, value or utility of a credential. Note: recognition may include a process of quality assurance or accreditation.

https://schema.org/validForMemberTier.label: validForMemberTier
https://schema.org/validForMemberTier.description: The membership program tier an Offer (or a PriceSpecification, OfferShippingDetails, or MerchantReturnPolicy under an Offer) is valid for.

https://schema.org/LymphaticVessel.label: LymphaticVessel
https://schema.org/LymphaticVessel.description: A type of blood vessel that specifically carries lymph fluid unidirectionally toward the heart.

https://schema.org/contentLocation.label: contentLocation
https://schema.org/contentLocation.description: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

https://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.label: hasBroadcastChannel
https://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.description: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.

https://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.label: accountOverdraftLimit
https://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.description: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.

https://schema.org/colorSwatch.label: colorSwatch
https://schema.org/colorSwatch.description: A color swatch image, visualizing the color of a [[Product]]. Should match the textual description specified in the [[color]] property. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.

https://schema.org/educationalFramework.label: educationalFramework
https://schema.org/educationalFramework.description: The framework to which the resource being described is aligned.

https://schema.org/PublicationIssue.label: PublicationIssue
https://schema.org/PublicationIssue.description: A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog-schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

https://schema.org/dateReceived.label: dateReceived
https://schema.org/dateReceived.description: The date/time the message was received if a single recipient exists.

https://schema.org/sodiumContent.label: sodiumContent
https://schema.org/sodiumContent.description: The number of milligrams of sodium.

https://schema.org/caption.label: caption
https://schema.org/caption.description: The caption for this object. For downloadable machine formats (closed caption, subtitles etc.) use MediaObject and indicate the [[encodingFormat]].

https://schema.org/quarantineGuidelines.label: quarantineGuidelines
https://schema.org/quarantineGuidelines.description: Guidelines about quarantine rules, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/CertificationStatusEn.label: CertificationStatusEnumeration
https://schema.org/CertificationStatusEn.description: Enumerates the different statuses of a Certification (Active and Inactive).

https://schema.org/interactionCount.label: interactionCount
https://schema.org/interactionCount.description: This property is deprecated, alongside the UserInteraction types on which it depended.

https://schema.org/UpdateAction.label: UpdateAction
https://schema.org/UpdateAction.description: The act of managing by changing/editing the state of the object.

https://schema.org/House.label: House
https://schema.org/House.description: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House).

https://schema.org/codeRepository.label: codeRepository
https://schema.org/codeRepository.description: Link to the repository where the un-compiled, human readable code and related code is located (SVN, GitHub, CodePlex).

https://schema.org/MeasurementTypeEnumer.label: MeasurementTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/MeasurementTypeEnumer.description: Enumeration of common measurement types (or dimensions), for example "chest" for a person, "inseam" for pants, "gauge" for screws, or "wheel" for bicycles.

https://schema.org/SpeakableSpecificatio.label: SpeakableSpecification
https://schema.org/SpeakableSpecificatio.description: A SpeakableSpecification indicates (typically via [[xpath]] or [[cssSelector]]) sections of a document that are highlighted as particularly [[speakable]]. Instances of this type are expected to be used primarily as values of the [[speakable]] property.

https://schema.org/modelDate.label: modelDate
https://schema.org/modelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

https://schema.org/priceComponentType.label: priceComponentType
https://schema.org/priceComponentType.description: Identifies a price component (for example, a line item on an invoice), part of the total price for an offer.

https://schema.org/datePublished.label: datePublished
https://schema.org/datePublished.description: Date of first publication or broadcast. For example the date a [[CreativeWork]] was broadcast or a [[Certification]] was issued.

https://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.label: arrivalPlatform
https://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.description: The platform where the train arrives.

https://schema.org/sdPublisher.label: sdPublisher
https://schema.org/sdPublisher.description:
Indicates the party responsible for generating and publishing the current structured data markup, typically in cases where the structured data is derived automatically from existing published content but published on a different site. For example, student projects and open data initiatives often re-publish existing content with more explicitly structured metadata. The
[[sdPublisher]] property helps make such practices more explicit.

https://schema.org/openingHours.label: openingHours
https://schema.org/openingHours.description:
The general opening hours for a business. Opening hours can be specified as a weekly time range, starting with days, then times per day. Multiple days can be listed with commas ',' separating each day. Day or time ranges are specified using a hyphen '-'.

* Days are specified using the following two-letter combinations: ```Mo```, ```Tu```, ```We```, ```Th```, ```Fr```, ```Sa```, ```Su```.
* Times are specified using 24:00 format. For example, 3pm is specified as ```15:00```, 10am as ```10:00`

https://schema.org/tongueWeight.label: tongueWeight
https://schema.org/tongueWeight.description:
The permitted vertical load (TWR) of a trailer attached to the vehicle. Also referred to as Tongue Load Rating (TLR) or Vertical Load Rating (VLR).

Typical unit code(s): KGM for kilogram, LBR for pound

* Note 1: You can indicate additional information in the [[name]] of the [[QuantitativeValue]] node.
* Note 2: You may also link to a [[QualitativeValue]] node that provides additional information using [[valueReference]].
* Note 3: Note that you can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to in

https://schema.org/ExhibitionEvent.label: ExhibitionEvent
https://schema.org/ExhibitionEvent.description: Event type: Exhibition event, e.g. at a museum, library, archive, tradeshow, ...

https://schema.org/occupationalCredentia.label: occupationalCredentialAwarded
https://schema.org/occupationalCredentia.description: A description of the qualification, award, certificate, diploma or other occupational credential awarded as a consequence of successful completion of this course or program.

https://schema.org/NoteDigitalDocument.label: NoteDigitalDocument
https://schema.org/NoteDigitalDocument.description: A file containing a note, primarily for the author.

https://schema.org/episode.label: episode
https://schema.org/episode.description: An episode of a TV, radio or game media within a series or season.

https://schema.org/bioChemInteraction.label: bioChemInteraction
https://schema.org/bioChemInteraction.description: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.

https://schema.org/programMembershipUsed.label: programMembershipUsed
https://schema.org/programMembershipUsed.description: Any membership in a frequent flyer, hotel loyalty program, etc. being applied to the reservation.

https://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.label: ethicsPolicy
https://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.description: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a [[Restaurant]], a page describing food source policies. In the case of a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.

https://schema.org/suitableForDiet.label: suitableForDiet
https://schema.org/suitableForDiet.description: Indicates a dietary restriction or guideline for which this recipe or menu item is suitable, e.g. diabetic, halal etc.

https://schema.org/RegisterAction.label: RegisterAction
https://schema.org/RegisterAction.description:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.

Related actions:

* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, *not* a group/team of people.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

https://schema.org/DefenceEstablishment.label: DefenceEstablishment
https://schema.org/DefenceEstablishment.description: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

https://schema.org/area.label: area
https://schema.org/area.description: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.

https://schema.org/suggestedMaxAge.label: suggestedMaxAge
https://schema.org/suggestedMaxAge.description: Maximum recommended age in years for the audience or user.

https://schema.org/pathophysiology.label: pathophysiology
https://schema.org/pathophysiology.description: Changes in the normal mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions that are associated with this activity or condition.

https://schema.org/MedicalTrial.label: MedicalTrial
https://schema.org/MedicalTrial.description: A medical trial is a type of medical study that uses a scientific process to compare the safety and efficacy of medical therapies or medical procedures. In general, medical trials are controlled and subjects are allocated at random to the different treatment and/or control groups.

https://schema.org/GameServer.label: GameServer
https://schema.org/GameServer.description: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

https://schema.org/surface.label: surface
https://schema.org/surface.description: A material used as a surface in some artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.

https://schema.org/identifyingTest.label: identifyingTest
https://schema.org/identifyingTest.description: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.

https://schema.org/geoMidpoint.label: geoMidpoint
https://schema.org/geoMidpoint.description: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape, e.g. GeoCircle.

https://schema.org/IncentiveStatus.label: IncentiveStatus
https://schema.org/IncentiveStatus.description: Enumerates a status for an incentive, such as whether it is active.

https://schema.org/CreativeWork.label: CreativeWork
https://schema.org/CreativeWork.description: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.
https://schema.org/CreativeWork.usage_hint: Base type for books, articles, papers, etc. Use schema:author, schema:datePublished, schema:about.
https://schema.org/CreativeWork.example_keywords: work, publication, article, book, paper, writing, creative work

https://schema.org/numberOfAvailableAcco.label: numberOfAvailableAccommodationUnits
https://schema.org/numberOfAvailableAcco.description: Indicates the number of available accommodation units in an [[ApartmentComplex]], or the number of accommodation units for a specific [[FloorPlan]] (within its specific [[ApartmentComplex]]). See also [[numberOfAccommodationUnits]].

https://schema.org/expertConsiderations.label: expertConsiderations
https://schema.org/expertConsiderations.description: Medical expert advice related to the plan.

https://schema.org/Bone.label: Bone
https://schema.org/Bone.description: Rigid connective tissue that comprises up the skeletal structure of the human body.

https://schema.org/SubscribeAction.label: SubscribeAction
https://schema.org/SubscribeAction.description:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates pushed to.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, SubscribeAction implies that the subscriber acts as a passive agent being constantly/actively pushed for updates.
* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, SubscribeAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
* [[JoinAction]]: Unlike JoinAction, Subsc

https://schema.org/affectedBy.label: affectedBy
https://schema.org/affectedBy.description: Drugs that affect the test's results.

https://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.label: alternativeHeadline
https://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.description: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/lyricist.label: lyricist
https://schema.org/lyricist.description: The person who wrote the words.

https://schema.org/QualitativeValue.label: QualitativeValue
https://schema.org/QualitativeValue.description: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

https://schema.org/permitAudience.label: permitAudience
https://schema.org/permitAudience.description: The target audience for this permit.

https://schema.org/DataDownload.label: DataDownload
https://schema.org/DataDownload.description: All or part of a [[Dataset]] in downloadable form.

https://schema.org/repeatFrequency.label: repeatFrequency
https://schema.org/repeatFrequency.description:
Defines the frequency at which [[Event]]s will occur according to a schedule [[Schedule]]. The intervals between
      events should be defined as a [[Duration]] of time.

https://schema.org/recipe.label: recipe
https://schema.org/recipe.description: A sub property of instrument. The recipe/instructions used to perform the action.

https://schema.org/applicableLocation.label: applicableLocation
https://schema.org/applicableLocation.description: The location in which the status applies.

https://schema.org/reservationId.label: reservationId
https://schema.org/reservationId.description: A unique identifier for the reservation.

https://schema.org/requiredMaxAge.label: requiredMaxAge
https://schema.org/requiredMaxAge.description: Audiences defined by a person's maximum age.

https://schema.org/PaymentMethod.label: PaymentMethod
https://schema.org/PaymentMethod.description:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction. The following legacy values should be accepted: 

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance
* http://pu

https://schema.org/DiscussionForumPostin.label: DiscussionForumPosting
https://schema.org/DiscussionForumPostin.description: A posting to a discussion forum.

https://schema.org/InviteAction.label: InviteAction
https://schema.org/InviteAction.description: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

https://schema.org/geoEquals.label: geoEquals
https://schema.org/geoEquals.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM). "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship).

https://schema.org/OrganizationRole.label: OrganizationRole
https://schema.org/OrganizationRole.description: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.
https://schema.org/OrganizationRole.usage_hint: Use for employment, membership, or affiliation with dates. Pattern: Person -> worksFor/memberOf -> OrganizationRole -> worksFor/memberOf -> Organization, add startDate/endDate to the role.
https://schema.org/OrganizationRole.example_keywords: employment, job, position, membership, affiliation, worked at, employed by

https://schema.org/mechanismOfAction.label: mechanismOfAction
https://schema.org/mechanismOfAction.description: The specific biochemical interaction through which this drug or supplement produces its pharmacological effect.

https://schema.org/rxcui.label: rxcui
https://schema.org/rxcui.description: The RxCUI drug identifier from RXNORM.

https://schema.org/DDxElement.label: DDxElement
https://schema.org/DDxElement.description: An alternative, closely-related condition typically considered later in the differential diagnosis process along with the signs that are used to distinguish it.

https://schema.org/Ligament.label: Ligament
https://schema.org/Ligament.description: A short band of tough, flexible, fibrous connective tissue that functions to connect multiple bones, cartilages, and structurally support joints.

https://schema.org/salaryCurrency.label: salaryCurrency
https://schema.org/salaryCurrency.description: The currency (coded using [ISO 4217](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217)) used for the main salary information in this job posting or for this employee.

https://schema.org/ticketToken.label: ticketToken
https://schema.org/ticketToken.description: Reference to an asset (e.g., Barcode, QR code image or PDF) usable for entrance.

https://schema.org/hasParticipationOffer.label: hasParticipationOffer
https://schema.org/hasParticipationOffer.description: An offer to participate in the event, for example, Call for Proposals, Call for Speakers, or Call for Performers.

https://schema.org/ComicSeries.label: ComicSeries
https://schema.org/ComicSeries.description:
A sequential publication of comic stories under a
    	unifying title, for example "The Amazing Spider-Man" or "Groo the
    	Wanderer".

https://schema.org/grantee.label: grantee
https://schema.org/grantee.description: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.

https://schema.org/abstract.label: abstract
https://schema.org/abstract.description: An abstract is a short description that summarizes a [[CreativeWork]].

https://schema.org/vehicleIdentification.label: vehicleIdentificationNumber
https://schema.org/vehicleIdentification.description: The Vehicle Identification Number (VIN) is a unique serial number used by the automotive industry to identify individual motor vehicles.

https://schema.org/orderStatus.label: orderStatus
https://schema.org/orderStatus.description: The current status of the order.

https://schema.org/geographicArea.label: geographicArea
https://schema.org/geographicArea.description: The geographic area associated with the audience.

https://schema.org/publisherImprint.label: publisherImprint
https://schema.org/publisherImprint.description: The publishing division which published the comic.

https://schema.org/encodingFormat.label: encodingFormat
https://schema.org/encodingFormat.description:
Media type typically expressed using a MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml) and [MDN reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/MIME_types)), e.g. application/zip for a SoftwareApplication binary, audio/mpeg for .mp3 etc.

In cases where a [[CreativeWork]] has several media type representations, [[encoding]] can be used to indicate each [[MediaObject]] alongside particular [[encodingFormat]] information.

Unr

https://schema.org/inLanguage.label: inLanguage
https://schema.org/inLanguage.description: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[availableLanguage]].

https://schema.org/EmployerReview.label: EmployerReview
https://schema.org/EmployerReview.description: An [[EmployerReview]] is a review of an [[Organization]] regarding its role as an employer, written by a current or former employee of that organization.

https://schema.org/BusReservation.label: BusReservation
https://schema.org/BusReservation.description: A reservation for bus travel. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/loanRepaymentForm.label: loanRepaymentForm
https://schema.org/loanRepaymentForm.description: A form of paying back money previously borrowed from a lender. Repayment usually takes the form of periodic payments that normally include part principal plus interest in each payment.
