https://schema.org/Season.label: Season
https://schema.org/Season.description: A media season, e.g. TV, radio, video game etc.

https://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCat.label: healthPlanPharmacyCategory
https://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCat.description: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.

https://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.label: biomechnicalClass
https://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.description: The biomechanical properties of the bone.

https://schema.org/EventSeries.label: EventSeries
https://schema.org/EventSeries.description:
A series of [[Event]]s. Included events can relate with the series using the [[superEvent]] property.

An EventSeries is a collection of events that share some unifying characteristic. For example, "The Olympic Games" is a series, which
is repeated regularly. The "2012 London Olympics" can be presented both as an [[Event]] in the series "Olympic Games", and as an
[[EventSeries]] that included a number of sporting competitions as Events.

The nature of the association between the events in an [[E

https://schema.org/BroadcastService.label: BroadcastService
https://schema.org/BroadcastService.description: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

https://schema.org/acceptedAnswer.label: acceptedAnswer
https://schema.org/acceptedAnswer.description: The answer(s) that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.

https://schema.org/trainName.label: trainName
https://schema.org/trainName.description: The name of the train (e.g. The Orient Express).

https://schema.org/accessCode.label: accessCode
https://schema.org/accessCode.description: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).

https://schema.org/produces.label: produces
https://schema.org/produces.description: The tangible thing generated by the service, e.g. a passport, permit, etc.

https://schema.org/mainEntityOfPage.label: mainEntityOfPage
https://schema.org/mainEntityOfPage.description: Indicates a page (or other CreativeWork) for which this thing is the main entity being described. See [background notes](/docs/datamodel.html#mainEntityBackground) for details.

https://schema.org/AllocateAction.label: AllocateAction
https://schema.org/AllocateAction.description: The act of organizing tasks/objects/events by associating resources to it.

https://schema.org/SpecialAnnouncement.label: SpecialAnnouncement
https://schema.org/SpecialAnnouncement.description:
A SpecialAnnouncement combines a simple date-stamped textual information update
      with contextualized Web links and other structured data.  It represents an information update made by a
      locally-oriented organization, for example schools, pharmacies, healthcare providers,  community groups, police,
      local government.

For work in progress guidelines on Coronavirus-related markup see [this doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/14ikaGCKxo50rRM7nvKSlbUpjyIk2WMQd3IkB1lItlrM/edit#).

https://schema.org/ticketNumber.label: ticketNumber
https://schema.org/ticketNumber.description: The unique identifier for the ticket.

https://schema.org/MedicalGuideline.label: MedicalGuideline
https://schema.org/MedicalGuideline.description: Any recommendation made by a standard society (e.g. ACC/AHA) or consensus statement that denotes how to diagnose and treat a particular condition. Note: this type should be used to tag the actual guideline recommendation; if the guideline recommendation occurs in a larger scholarly article, use MedicalScholarlyArticle to tag the overall article, not this type. Note also: the organization making the recommendation should be captured in the recognizingAuthority base property of MedicalEntity.

https://schema.org/Cooperative.label: Cooperative
https://schema.org/Cooperative.description: An organization that is a joint project of multiple organizations or persons.

https://schema.org/Consortium.label: Consortium
https://schema.org/Consortium.description: A Consortium is a membership [[Organization]] whose members are typically Organizations.

https://schema.org/arrivalStation.label: arrivalStation
https://schema.org/arrivalStation.description: The station where the train trip ends.

https://schema.org/dietFeatures.label: dietFeatures
https://schema.org/dietFeatures.description: Nutritional information specific to the dietary plan. May include dietary recommendations on what foods to avoid, what foods to consume, and specific alterations/deviations from the USDA or other regulatory body's approved dietary guidelines.

https://schema.org/layoutImage.label: layoutImage
https://schema.org/layoutImage.description: A schematic image showing the floorplan layout.

https://schema.org/significantLink.label: significantLink
https://schema.org/significantLink.description: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

https://schema.org/game.label: game
https://schema.org/game.description: Video game which is played on this server.

https://schema.org/dateCreated.label: dateCreated
https://schema.org/dateCreated.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was created or the item was added to a DataFeed.

https://schema.org/BrainStructure.label: BrainStructure
https://schema.org/BrainStructure.description: Any anatomical structure which pertains to the soft nervous tissue functioning as the coordinating center of sensation and intellectual and nervous activity.

https://schema.org/Series.label: Series
https://schema.org/Series.description: A Series in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. See also [[CreativeWorkSeries]], [[EventSeries]].

https://schema.org/RVPark.label: RVPark
https://schema.org/RVPark.description: A place offering space for "Recreational Vehicles", Caravans, mobile homes and the like.

https://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.label: benefitsSummaryUrl
https://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.description: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

https://schema.org/albumReleaseType.label: albumReleaseType
https://schema.org/albumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

https://schema.org/MedicalRiskScore.label: MedicalRiskScore
https://schema.org/MedicalRiskScore.description: A simple system that adds up the number of risk factors to yield a score that is associated with prognosis, e.g. CHAD score, TIMI risk score.

https://schema.org/archiveHeld.label: archiveHeld
https://schema.org/archiveHeld.description: Collection, [fonds](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fonds), or item held, kept or maintained by an [[ArchiveOrganization]].

https://schema.org/hasCertification.label: hasCertification
https://schema.org/hasCertification.description: Certification information about a product, organization, service, place, or person.

https://schema.org/seller.label: seller
https://schema.org/seller.description: An entity which offers (sells / leases / lends / loans) the services / goods.  A seller may also be a provider.

https://schema.org/negativeNotes.label: negativeNotes
https://schema.org/negativeNotes.description:
Provides negative considerations regarding something, most typically in pro/con lists for reviews (alongside [[positiveNotes]]). For symmetry 

In the case of a [[Review]], the property describes the [[itemReviewed]] from the perspective of the review; in the case of a [[Product]], the product itself is being described. Since product descriptions 
tend to emphasise positive claims, it may be relatively unusual to find [[negativeNotes]] used in this way. Nevertheless for the sake of symmetry, [[n

https://schema.org/FinancialProduct.label: FinancialProduct
https://schema.org/FinancialProduct.description: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

https://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.label: increasesRiskOf
https://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.

https://schema.org/yield.label: yield
https://schema.org/yield.description: The quantity that results by performing instructions. For example, a paper airplane, 10 personalized candles.

https://schema.org/hasDriveThroughServic.label: hasDriveThroughService
https://schema.org/hasDriveThroughServic.description: Indicates whether some facility (e.g. [[FoodEstablishment]], [[CovidTestingFacility]]) offers a service that can be used by driving through in a car. In the case of [[CovidTestingFacility]] such facilities could potentially help with social distancing from other potentially-infected users.

https://schema.org/restockingFee.label: restockingFee
https://schema.org/restockingFee.description: Use [[MonetaryAmount]] to specify a fixed restocking fee for product returns, or use [[Number]] to specify a percentage of the product price paid by the customer.

https://schema.org/numberOfPreviousOwner.label: numberOfPreviousOwners
https://schema.org/numberOfPreviousOwner.description: The number of owners of the vehicle, including the current one.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

https://schema.org/typicalCreditsPerTerm.label: typicalCreditsPerTerm
https://schema.org/typicalCreditsPerTerm.description: The number of credits or units a full-time student would be expected to take in 1 term however 'term' is defined by the institution.

https://schema.org/wheelbase.label: wheelbase
https://schema.org/wheelbase.description: The distance between the centers of the front and rear wheels.\n\nTypical unit code(s): CMT for centimeters, MTR for meters, INH for inches, FOT for foot/feet.

https://schema.org/legislationDateVersio.label: legislationDateVersion
https://schema.org/legislationDateVersio.description: The point-in-time at which the provided description of the legislation is valid (e.g.: when looking at the law on the 2016-04-07 (= dateVersion), I get the consolidation of 2015-04-12 of the "National Insurance Contributions Act 2015")

https://schema.org/AddAction.label: AddAction
https://schema.org/AddAction.description: The act of editing by adding an object to a collection.

https://schema.org/StructuredValue.label: StructuredValue
https://schema.org/StructuredValue.description: Structured values are used when the value of a property has a more complex structure than simply being a textual value or a reference to another thing.

https://schema.org/MemberProgramTier.label: MemberProgramTier
https://schema.org/MemberProgramTier.description: A MemberProgramTier specifies a tier under a loyalty (member) program, for example "gold".

https://schema.org/subEvents.label: subEvents
https://schema.org/subEvents.description: Events that are a part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each subEvents of the conference.

https://schema.org/fromLocation.label: fromLocation
https://schema.org/fromLocation.description: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.

https://schema.org/additionalProperty.label: additionalProperty
https://schema.org/additionalProperty.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristic of the entity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.\n\nNote: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. https://schema.org/width, https://schema.org/color, https://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

https://schema.org/TypeAndQuantityNode.label: TypeAndQuantityNode
https://schema.org/TypeAndQuantityNode.description: A structured value indicating the quantity, unit of measurement, and business function of goods included in a bundle offer.

https://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.label: broadcastServiceTier
https://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.description: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).

https://schema.org/MortgageLoan.label: MortgageLoan
https://schema.org/MortgageLoan.description: A loan in which property or real estate is used as collateral. (A loan securitized against some real estate.)

https://schema.org/numberOfEmployees.label: numberOfEmployees
https://schema.org/numberOfEmployees.description: The number of employees in an organization, e.g. business.

https://schema.org/Airline.label: Airline
https://schema.org/Airline.description: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

https://schema.org/MedicalAudience.label: MedicalAudience
https://schema.org/MedicalAudience.description: Target audiences for medical web pages.

https://schema.org/renegotiableLoan.label: renegotiableLoan
https://schema.org/renegotiableLoan.description: Whether the terms for payment of interest can be renegotiated during the life of the loan.

https://schema.org/Reservation.label: Reservation
https://schema.org/Reservation.description: Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets. \n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/JobPosting.label: JobPosting
https://schema.org/JobPosting.description: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

https://schema.org/torque.label: torque
https://schema.org/torque.description:
The torque (turning force) of the vehicle's engine.

Typical unit code(s): NU for newton metre (N m), F17 for pound-force per foot, or F48 for pound-force per inch

* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined (e.g. reference RPM) using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/sourceOrganization.label: sourceOrganization
https://schema.org/sourceOrganization.description: The Organization on whose behalf the creator was working.

https://schema.org/DrugPrescriptionStatu.label: DrugPrescriptionStatus
https://schema.org/DrugPrescriptionStatu.description: Indicates whether this drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter.

https://schema.org/runsTo.label: runsTo
https://schema.org/runsTo.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure runs, or efferents, to.

https://schema.org/ReactAction.label: ReactAction
https://schema.org/ReactAction.description: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

https://schema.org/roleName.label: roleName
https://schema.org/roleName.description: A role played, performed or filled by a person or organization. For example, the team of creators for a comic book might fill the roles named 'inker', 'penciller', and 'letterer'; or an athlete in a SportsTeam might play in the position named 'Quarterback'.

https://schema.org/WorkBasedProgram.label: WorkBasedProgram
https://schema.org/WorkBasedProgram.description: A program with both an educational and employment component. Typically based at a workplace and structured around work-based learning, with the aim of instilling competencies related to an occupation. WorkBasedProgram is used to distinguish programs such as apprenticeships from school, college or other classroom based educational programs.

https://schema.org/usedToDiagnose.label: usedToDiagnose
https://schema.org/usedToDiagnose.description: A condition the test is used to diagnose.

https://schema.org/isPartOfBioChemEntity.label: isPartOfBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/isPartOfBioChemEntity.description: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.

https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList.label: BreadcrumbList
https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList.description: A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.\n\nThe [[position]] property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList. The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an [[itemListOrder]] of [[ItemListOrderAscending]] (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail,

https://schema.org/composer.label: composer
https://schema.org/composer.description: The person or organization who wrote a composition, or who is the composer of a work performed at some event.

https://schema.org/PodcastSeries.label: PodcastSeries
https://schema.org/PodcastSeries.description: A podcast is an episodic series of digital audio or video files which a user can download and listen to.

https://schema.org/monoisotopicMolecular.label: monoisotopicMolecularWeight
https://schema.org/monoisotopicMolecular.description: The monoisotopic mass is the sum of the masses of the atoms in a molecule using the unbound, ground-state, rest mass of the principal (most abundant) isotope for each element instead of the isotopic average mass. Please include the units in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '770.230488 g/mol' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

https://schema.org/targetDescription.label: targetDescription
https://schema.org/targetDescription.description: The description of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/expressedIn.label: expressedIn
https://schema.org/expressedIn.description: Tissue, organ, biological sample, etc in which activity of this gene has been observed experimentally. For example brain, digestive system.

https://schema.org/workHours.label: workHours
https://schema.org/workHours.description: The typical working hours for this job (e.g. 1st shift, night shift, 8am-5pm).

https://schema.org/targetPopulation.label: targetPopulation
https://schema.org/targetPopulation.description: Characteristics of the population for which this is intended, or which typically uses it, e.g. 'adults'.

https://schema.org/distance.label: distance
https://schema.org/distance.description: The distance travelled, e.g. exercising or travelling.

https://schema.org/ProductModel.label: ProductModel
https://schema.org/ProductModel.description: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

https://schema.org/availableLanguage.label: availableLanguage
https://schema.org/availableLanguage.description: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the [IETF BCP 47 standard](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47). See also [[inLanguage]].

https://schema.org/MedicalCondition.label: MedicalCondition
https://schema.org/MedicalCondition.description: Any condition of the human body that affects the normal functioning of a person, whether physically or mentally. Includes diseases, injuries, disabilities, disorders, syndromes, etc.

https://schema.org/EventAttendanceModeEn.label: EventAttendanceModeEnumeration
https://schema.org/EventAttendanceModeEn.description: An EventAttendanceModeEnumeration value is one of potentially several modes of organising an event, relating to whether it is online or offline.

https://schema.org/serviceType.label: serviceType
https://schema.org/serviceType.description: The type of service being offered, e.g. veterans' benefits, emergency relief, etc.

https://schema.org/expectedArrivalUntil.label: expectedArrivalUntil
https://schema.org/expectedArrivalUntil.description: The latest date the package may arrive.

https://schema.org/issuedThrough.label: issuedThrough
https://schema.org/issuedThrough.description: The service through which the permit was granted.

https://schema.org/IndividualProduct.label: IndividualProduct
https://schema.org/IndividualProduct.description: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

https://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMeth.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMeth.description: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.

https://schema.org/answerExplanation.label: answerExplanation
https://schema.org/answerExplanation.description: A step-by-step or full explanation about Answer. Can outline how this Answer was achieved or contain more broad clarification or statement about it.

https://schema.org/eventStatus.label: eventStatus
https://schema.org/eventStatus.description: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.

https://schema.org/seriousAdverseOutcome.label: seriousAdverseOutcome
https://schema.org/seriousAdverseOutcome.description: A possible serious complication and/or serious side effect of this therapy. Serious adverse outcomes include those that are life-threatening; result in death, disability, or permanent damage; require hospitalization or prolong existing hospitalization; cause congenital anomalies or birth defects; or jeopardize the patient and may require medical or surgical intervention to prevent one of the outcomes in this definition.

https://schema.org/subEvent.label: subEvent
https://schema.org/subEvent.description: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

https://schema.org/VisualArtwork.label: VisualArtwork
https://schema.org/VisualArtwork.description: A work of art that is primarily visual in character.

https://schema.org/legislationRepeals.label: legislationRepeals
https://schema.org/legislationRepeals.description: Another legislation that this legislation repeals (cancels, abrogates).

https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage.label: mainContentOfPage
https://schema.org/mainContentOfPage.description: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.

https://schema.org/followup.label: followup
https://schema.org/followup.description: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.

https://schema.org/LodgingBusiness.label: LodgingBusiness
https://schema.org/LodgingBusiness.description: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

https://schema.org/DigitalPlatformEnumer.label: DigitalPlatformEnumeration
https://schema.org/DigitalPlatformEnumer.description: Enumerates some common technology platforms, for use with properties such as [[actionPlatform]]. It is not supposed to be comprehensive - when a suitable code is not enumerated here, textual or URL values can be used instead. These codes are at a fairly high level and do not deal with versioning and other nuance. Additional codes can be suggested [in github](https://github.com/schemaorg/schemaorg/issues/3057).

https://schema.org/occupationalCategory.label: occupationalCategory
https://schema.org/occupationalCategory.description:
A category describing the job, preferably using a term from a taxonomy such as [BLS O*NET-SOC](http://www.onetcenter.org/taxonomy.html), [ISCO-08](https://www.ilo.org/public/english/bureau/stat/isco/isco08/) or similar, with the property repeated for each applicable value. Ideally the taxonomy should be identified, and both the textual label and formal code for the category should be provided.\n
Note: for historical reasons, any textual label and formal code provided as a literal may be assumed

https://schema.org/paymentMethodType.label: paymentMethodType
https://schema.org/paymentMethodType.description: The type of a payment method.

https://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.label: arrivalTerminal
https://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.

https://schema.org/FlightReservation.label: FlightReservation
https://schema.org/FlightReservation.description: A reservation for air travel.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/preOp.label: preOp
https://schema.org/preOp.description: A description of the workup, testing, and other preparations required before implanting this device.

https://schema.org/inProductGroupWithID.label: inProductGroupWithID
https://schema.org/inProductGroupWithID.description: Indicates the [[productGroupID]] for a [[ProductGroup]] that this product [[isVariantOf]].

https://schema.org/securityScreening.label: securityScreening
https://schema.org/securityScreening.description: The type of security screening the passenger is subject to.

https://schema.org/DefinedTerm.label: DefinedTerm
https://schema.org/DefinedTerm.description: A word, name, acronym, phrase, etc. with a formal definition. Often used in the context of category or subject classification, glossaries or dictionaries, product or creative work types, etc. Use the name property for the term being defined, use termCode if the term has an alpha-numeric code allocated, use description to provide the definition of the term. Use the about property to specify what the term is about.

https://schema.org/quest.label: quest
https://schema.org/quest.description: The task that a player-controlled character, or group of characters may complete in order to gain a reward.

https://schema.org/learningResourceType.label: learningResourceType
https://schema.org/learningResourceType.description: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.

https://schema.org/Code.label: Code
https://schema.org/Code.description: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

https://schema.org/minValue.label: minValue
https://schema.org/minValue.description: The lower value of some characteristic or property.

https://schema.org/resultReview.label: resultReview
https://schema.org/resultReview.description: A sub property of result. The review that resulted in the performing of the action.

https://schema.org/circle.label: circle
https://schema.org/circle.description: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.

https://schema.org/creativeWorkStatus.label: creativeWorkStatus
https://schema.org/creativeWorkStatus.description: The status of a creative work in terms of its stage in a lifecycle. Example terms include Incomplete, Draft, Published, Obsolete. Some organizations define a set of terms for the stages of their publication lifecycle.

https://schema.org/MovieClip.label: MovieClip
https://schema.org/MovieClip.description: A short segment/part of a movie.

https://schema.org/potentialUse.label: potentialUse
https://schema.org/potentialUse.description: Intended use of the BioChemEntity by humans.

https://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPer.label: hasDigitalDocumentPermission
https://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPer.description: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".

https://schema.org/ShippingService.label: ShippingService
https://schema.org/ShippingService.description: ShippingService represents the criteria used to determine if and how an offer could be shipped to a customer.

https://schema.org/audience.label: audience
https://schema.org/audience.description: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.

https://schema.org/dayOfWeek.label: dayOfWeek
https://schema.org/dayOfWeek.description: The day of the week for which these opening hours are valid.

https://schema.org/startDate.label: startDate
https://schema.org/startDate.description: The start date and time of the item (in [ISO 8601 date format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601)).

https://schema.org/Question.label: Question
https://schema.org/Question.description: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

https://schema.org/gettingTestedInfo.label: gettingTestedInfo
https://schema.org/gettingTestedInfo.description: Information about getting tested (for a [[MedicalCondition]]), e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/iso6523Code.label: iso6523Code
https://schema.org/iso6523Code.description: An organization identifier as defined in [ISO 6523(-1)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO/IEC_6523). The identifier should be in the `XXXX:YYYYYY:ZZZ` or `XXXX:YYYYYY`format. Where `XXXX` is a 4 digit _ICD_ (International Code Designator), `YYYYYY` is an _OID_ (Organization Identifier) with all formatting characters (dots, dashes, spaces) removed with a maximal length of 35 characters, and `ZZZ` is an optional OPI (Organization Part Identifier) with a maximum length of 35 characters. The various

https://schema.org/vehicleEngine.label: vehicleEngine
https://schema.org/vehicleEngine.description: Information about the engine or engines of the vehicle.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19Died.label: cvdNumC19Died
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19Died.description: numc19died - DEATHS: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who died in the hospital, ED, or any overflow location.

https://schema.org/HowToTool.label: HowToTool
https://schema.org/HowToTool.description: A tool used (but not consumed) when performing instructions for how to achieve a result.

https://schema.org/PerformingArtsTheater.label: PerformingArtsTheater
https://schema.org/PerformingArtsTheater.description: A theater or other performing art center.

https://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.label: breastfeedingWarning
https://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.

https://schema.org/CovidTestingFacility.label: CovidTestingFacility
https://schema.org/CovidTestingFacility.description:
A CovidTestingFacility is a [[MedicalClinic]] where testing for the COVID-19 Coronavirus
      disease is available. If the facility is being made available from an established [[Pharmacy]], [[Hotel]], or other
      non-medical organization, multiple types can be listed. This makes it easier to re-use existing schema.org information
      about that place, e.g. contact info, address, opening hours. Note that in an emergency, such information may not always be reliable.

https://schema.org/sharedContent.label: sharedContent
https://schema.org/sharedContent.description: A CreativeWork such as an image, video, or audio clip shared as part of this posting.

https://schema.org/NewsMediaOrganization.label: NewsMediaOrganization
https://schema.org/NewsMediaOrganization.description: A News/Media organization such as a newspaper or TV station.

https://schema.org/PreOrderAction.label: PreOrderAction
https://schema.org/PreOrderAction.description: An agent orders a (not yet released) object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

https://schema.org/typicalTest.label: typicalTest
https://schema.org/typicalTest.description: A medical test typically performed given this condition.

https://schema.org/auditDate.label: auditDate
https://schema.org/auditDate.description: Date when a certification was last audited. See also  [gs1:certificationAuditDate](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationAuditDate).

https://schema.org/byDay.label: byDay
https://schema.org/byDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the week on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. May be specified using either [[DayOfWeek]], or alternatively [[Text]] conforming to iCal's syntax for byDay recurrence rules.

https://schema.org/guidelineDate.label: guidelineDate
https://schema.org/guidelineDate.description: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.

https://schema.org/birthPlace.label: birthPlace
https://schema.org/birthPlace.description: The place where the person was born.
https://schema.org/birthPlace.usage_hint: Place where someone was born. Value should be a Place.
https://schema.org/birthPlace.example_keywords: born in, birthplace, place of birth, native of

https://schema.org/intensity.label: intensity
https://schema.org/intensity.description: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.

https://schema.org/serviceArea.label: serviceArea
https://schema.org/serviceArea.description: The geographic area where the service is provided.

https://schema.org/trailer.label: trailer
https://schema.org/trailer.description: The trailer of a movie or TV/radio series, season, episode, etc.

https://schema.org/supply.label: supply
https://schema.org/supply.description: A sub-property of instrument. A supply consumed when performing instructions or a direction.

https://schema.org/correctionsPolicy.label: correctionsPolicy
https://schema.org/correctionsPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (e.g. [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement describing (in news media, the newsroom’s) disclosure and correction policy for errors.

https://schema.org/locationCreated.label: locationCreated
https://schema.org/locationCreated.description: The location where the CreativeWork was created, which may not be the same as the location depicted in the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/ingredients.label: ingredients
https://schema.org/ingredients.description: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.

https://schema.org/returnLabelSource.label: returnLabelSource
https://schema.org/returnLabelSource.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned for any reason.

https://schema.org/fiberContent.label: fiberContent
https://schema.org/fiberContent.description: The number of grams of fiber.

https://schema.org/Action.label: Action
https://schema.org/Action.description: An action performed by a direct agent and indirect participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies the exact expectation of each argument/role.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/04/16/announcing-schema-org-actions/) and [Actions overview document](https://schema.org/docs/actions.html).

https://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.label: acceptedPaymentMethod
https://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.description: The payment method(s) that are accepted in general by an organization, or for some specific demand or offer.

https://schema.org/broadcastFrequency.label: broadcastFrequency
https://schema.org/broadcastFrequency.description: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges, e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequencies of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".

https://schema.org/byMonthWeek.label: byMonthWeek
https://schema.org/byMonthWeek.description: Defines the week(s) of the month on which a recurring Event takes place. Specified as an Integer between 1-5. For clarity, byMonthWeek is best used in conjunction with byDay to indicate concepts like the first and third Mondays of a month.

https://schema.org/itemOffered.label: itemOffered
https://schema.org/itemOffered.description: An item being offered (or demanded). The transactional nature of the offer or demand is documented using [[businessFunction]], e.g. sell, lease etc. While several common expected types are listed explicitly in this definition, others can be used. Using a second type, such as Product or a subtype of Product, can clarify the nature of the offer.

https://schema.org/legislationEnsuresImp.label: legislationEnsuresImplementationOf
https://schema.org/legislationEnsuresImp.description: Indicates that this Legislation ensures the implementation of another Legislation, for example by modifying national legislations so that they do not contradict to an EU regulation or decision. This implies a legal meaning. Transpositions of EU Directive should be captured with legislationTransposes.

https://schema.org/legalStatus.label: legalStatus
https://schema.org/legalStatus.description: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.

https://schema.org/performer.label: performer
https://schema.org/performer.description: A performer at the event—for example, a presenter, musician, musical group or actor.

https://schema.org/InstantaneousEvent.label: InstantaneousEvent
https://schema.org/InstantaneousEvent.description: An event with no duration, like for instance a computer log entry.

https://schema.org/XPathType.label: XPathType
https://schema.org/XPathType.description: Text representing an XPath (typically but not necessarily version 1.0).

https://schema.org/line.label: line
https://schema.org/line.description: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.

https://schema.org/DeliveryMethod.label: DeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/DeliveryMethod.description:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1

https://schema.org/Motel.label: Motel
https://schema.org/Motel.description:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/numChildren.label: numChildren
https://schema.org/numChildren.description: The number of children staying in the unit.

https://schema.org/AssessAction.label: AssessAction
https://schema.org/AssessAction.description: The act of forming one's opinion, reaction or sentiment.

https://schema.org/MoveAction.label: MoveAction
https://schema.org/MoveAction.description:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

* [[TransferAction]]: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

https://schema.org/EmergencyService.label: EmergencyService
https://schema.org/EmergencyService.description: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

https://schema.org/BioChemEntity.label: BioChemEntity
https://schema.org/BioChemEntity.description: Any biological, chemical, or biochemical thing. For example: a protein; a gene; a chemical; a synthetic chemical.

https://schema.org/transFatContent.label: transFatContent
https://schema.org/transFatContent.description: The number of grams of trans fat.

https://schema.org/recipient.label: recipient
https://schema.org/recipient.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.

https://schema.org/availability.label: availability
https://schema.org/availability.description: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.

https://schema.org/repetitions.label: repetitions
https://schema.org/repetitions.description: Number of times one should repeat the activity.

https://schema.org/billingPeriod.label: billingPeriod
https://schema.org/billingPeriod.description: The time interval used to compute the invoice.

https://schema.org/diseaseSpreadStatisti.label: diseaseSpreadStatistics
https://schema.org/diseaseSpreadStatisti.description:
Statistical information about the spread of a disease, either as [[WebContent]], or
  described directly as a [[Dataset]], or the specific [[Observation]]s in the dataset. When a [[WebContent]] URL is
  provided, the page indicated might also contain more such markup.

https://schema.org/workTranslation.label: workTranslation
https://schema.org/workTranslation.description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work. E.g. 西遊記 has an English workTranslation “Journey to the West”, a German workTranslation “Monkeys Pilgerfahrt” and a Vietnamese  translation Tây du ký bình khảo.

https://schema.org/PublicToilet.label: PublicToilet
https://schema.org/PublicToilet.description: A public toilet is a room or small building containing one or more toilets (and possibly also urinals) which is available for use by the general public, or by customers or employees of certain businesses.

https://schema.org/SteeringPositionValue.label: SteeringPositionValue
https://schema.org/SteeringPositionValue.description: A value indicating a steering position.

https://schema.org/loanTerm.label: loanTerm
https://schema.org/loanTerm.description: The duration of the loan or credit agreement.

https://schema.org/AuthorizeAction.label: AuthorizeAction
https://schema.org/AuthorizeAction.description: The act of granting permission to an object.

https://schema.org/TradeAction.label: TradeAction
https://schema.org/TradeAction.description: The act of participating in an exchange of goods and services for monetary compensation. An agent trades an object, product or service with a participant in exchange for a one time or periodic payment.

https://schema.org/albumProductionType.label: albumProductionType
https://schema.org/albumProductionType.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

https://schema.org/BroadcastChannel.label: BroadcastChannel
https://schema.org/BroadcastChannel.description: A unique instance of a BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

https://schema.org/volumeNumber.label: volumeNumber
https://schema.org/volumeNumber.description: Identifies the volume of publication or multi-part work; for example, "iii" or "2".

https://schema.org/Trip.label: Trip
https://schema.org/Trip.description: A trip or journey. An itinerary of visits to one or more places.

https://schema.org/TieAction.label: TieAction
https://schema.org/TieAction.description: The act of reaching a draw in a competitive activity.

https://schema.org/GamePlayMode.label: GamePlayMode
https://schema.org/GamePlayMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

https://schema.org/DisagreeAction.label: DisagreeAction
https://schema.org/DisagreeAction.description: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

https://schema.org/Enumeration.label: Enumeration
https://schema.org/Enumeration.description: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

https://schema.org/loanMortgageMandateAm.label: loanMortgageMandateAmount
https://schema.org/loanMortgageMandateAm.description: Amount of mortgage mandate that can be converted into a proper mortgage at a later stage.

https://schema.org/typicalAgeRange.label: typicalAgeRange
https://schema.org/typicalAgeRange.description: The typical expected age range, e.g. '7-9', '11-'.

https://schema.org/returnPolicyCategory.label: returnPolicyCategory
https://schema.org/returnPolicyCategory.description: Specifies an applicable return policy (from an enumeration).

https://schema.org/isResizable.label: isResizable
https://schema.org/isResizable.description: Whether the 3DModel allows resizing. For example, room layout applications often do not allow 3DModel elements to be resized to reflect reality.

https://schema.org/underName.label: underName
https://schema.org/underName.description: The person or organization the reservation or ticket is for.

https://schema.org/recommendationStrengt.label: recommendationStrength
https://schema.org/recommendationStrengt.description: Strength of the guideline's recommendation (e.g. 'class I').

https://schema.org/Collection.label: Collection
https://schema.org/Collection.description: A collection of items, e.g. creative works or products.

https://schema.org/ReturnMethodEnumerati.label: ReturnMethodEnumeration
https://schema.org/ReturnMethodEnumerati.description: Enumerates several types of product return methods.

https://schema.org/contentType.label: contentType
https://schema.org/contentType.description: The supported content type(s) for an EntryPoint response.

https://schema.org/jobBenefits.label: jobBenefits
https://schema.org/jobBenefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

https://schema.org/OrderItem.label: OrderItem
https://schema.org/OrderItem.description: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.

https://schema.org/EducationalOccupation.label: EducationalOccupationalCredential
https://schema.org/EducationalOccupation.description: An educational or occupational credential. A diploma, academic degree, certification, qualification, badge, etc., that may be awarded to a person or other entity that meets the requirements defined by the credentialer.

https://schema.org/isicV4.label: isicV4
https://schema.org/isicV4.description: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.

https://schema.org/UserBlocks.label: UserBlocks
https://schema.org/UserBlocks.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/scheduleTimezone.label: scheduleTimezone
https://schema.org/scheduleTimezone.description: Indicates the timezone for which the time(s) indicated in the [[Schedule]] are given. The value provided should be among those listed in the IANA Time Zone Database.

https://schema.org/NewsArticle.label: NewsArticle
https://schema.org/NewsArticle.description:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.

A more detailed overview of [schema.org News markup](/docs/news.html) is also available.

https://schema.org/recordingOf.label: recordingOf
https://schema.org/recordingOf.description: The composition this track is a recording of.

https://schema.org/deliveryMethod.label: deliveryMethod
https://schema.org/deliveryMethod.description: A sub property of instrument. The method of delivery.

https://schema.org/jobLocation.label: jobLocation
https://schema.org/jobLocation.description: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.

https://schema.org/MediaReview.label: MediaReview
https://schema.org/MediaReview.description:
A [[MediaReview]] is a more specialized form of Review dedicated to the evaluation of media content online, typically in the context of fact-checking and misinformation.
    For more general reviews of media in the broader sense, use [[UserReview]], [[CriticReview]] or other [[Review]] types. This definition is
    a work in progress. While the [[MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration]] list reflects significant community review amongst fact-checkers and others working
    to combat misinformation,

https://schema.org/RadioBroadcastService.label: RadioBroadcastService
https://schema.org/RadioBroadcastService.description: A delivery service through which radio content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

https://schema.org/costOrigin.label: costOrigin
https://schema.org/costOrigin.description: Additional details to capture the origin of the cost data. For example, 'Medicare Part B'.

https://schema.org/departureAirport.label: departureAirport
https://schema.org/departureAirport.description: The airport where the flight originates.

https://schema.org/UseAction.label: UseAction
https://schema.org/UseAction.description: The act of applying an object to its intended purpose.

https://schema.org/awayTeam.label: awayTeam
https://schema.org/awayTeam.description: The away team in a sports event.

https://schema.org/SurgicalProcedure.label: SurgicalProcedure
https://schema.org/SurgicalProcedure.description: A medical procedure involving an incision with instruments; performed for diagnose, or therapeutic purposes.

https://schema.org/GovernmentService.label: GovernmentService
https://schema.org/GovernmentService.description: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

https://schema.org/option.label: option
https://schema.org/option.description: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.

https://schema.org/Physician.label: Physician
https://schema.org/Physician.description: An individual physician or a physician's office considered as a [[MedicalOrganization]].

https://schema.org/season.label: season
https://schema.org/season.description: A season in a media series.

https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.label: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate
https://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsurance.description: The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

https://schema.org/departurePlatform.label: departurePlatform
https://schema.org/departurePlatform.description: The platform from which the train departs.

https://schema.org/bodyType.label: bodyType
https://schema.org/bodyType.description: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).

https://schema.org/equal.label: equal
https://schema.org/equal.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

https://schema.org/Optician.label: Optician
https://schema.org/Optician.description: A store that sells reading glasses and similar devices for improving vision.

https://schema.org/SheetMusic.label: SheetMusic
https://schema.org/SheetMusic.description: Printed music, as opposed to performed or recorded music.

https://schema.org/iswcCode.label: iswcCode
https://schema.org/iswcCode.description: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.

https://schema.org/ownedFrom.label: ownedFrom
https://schema.org/ownedFrom.description: The date and time of obtaining the product.

https://schema.org/highPrice.label: highPrice
https://schema.org/highPrice.description:
The highest price of all offers available.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeries.label: CreativeWorkSeries
https://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeries.description: A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike [[ItemList]] which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as TV, radio and games).\n\nSpecific subtypes are available for describing [[TVSeries]], [[RadioSeries]], [[Movi

https://schema.org/LiquorStore.label: LiquorStore
https://schema.org/LiquorStore.description: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

https://schema.org/validUntil.label: validUntil
https://schema.org/validUntil.description: The date when the item is no longer valid.

https://schema.org/postalCodeEnd.label: postalCodeEnd
https://schema.org/postalCodeEnd.description: Last postal code in the range (included). Needs to be after [[postalCodeBegin]].

https://schema.org/saturatedFatContent.label: saturatedFatContent
https://schema.org/saturatedFatContent.description: The number of grams of saturated fat.

https://schema.org/ChooseAction.label: ChooseAction
https://schema.org/ChooseAction.description: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

https://schema.org/observationAbout.label: observationAbout
https://schema.org/observationAbout.description: The [[observationAbout]] property identifies an entity, often a [[Place]], associated with an [[Observation]].

https://schema.org/servingSize.label: servingSize
https://schema.org/servingSize.description: The serving size, in terms of the number of volume or mass.

https://schema.org/courseCode.label: courseCode
https://schema.org/courseCode.description: The identifier for the [[Course]] used by the course [[provider]] (e.g. CS101 or 6.001).

https://schema.org/RestrictedDiet.label: RestrictedDiet
https://schema.org/RestrictedDiet.description: A diet restricted to certain foods or preparations for cultural, religious, health or lifestyle reasons.

https://schema.org/measurementQualifier.label: measurementQualifier
https://schema.org/measurementQualifier.description: Provides additional qualification to an observation. For example, a GDP observation measures the Nominal value.

https://schema.org/Project.label: Project
https://schema.org/Project.description:
An enterprise (potentially individual but typically collaborative), planned to achieve a particular aim.
Use properties from [[Organization]], [[subOrganization]]/[[parentOrganization]] to indicate project sub-structures.

https://schema.org/identifyingExam.label: identifyingExam
https://schema.org/identifyingExam.description: A physical examination that can identify this sign.

https://schema.org/HealthTopicContent.label: HealthTopicContent
https://schema.org/HealthTopicContent.description: [[HealthTopicContent]] is [[WebContent]] that is about some aspect of a health topic, e.g. a condition, its symptoms or treatments. Such content may be comprised of several parts or sections and use different types of media. Multiple instances of [[WebContent]] (and hence [[HealthTopicContent]]) can be related using [[hasPart]] / [[isPartOf]] where there is some kind of content hierarchy, and their content described with [[about]] and [[mentions]] e.g. building upon the existing [[MedicalConditi

https://schema.org/creator.label: creator
https://schema.org/creator.description: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.
https://schema.org/creator.usage_hint: The creator of a CreativeWork. Similar to author but more general.
https://schema.org/creator.example_keywords: creator, made by, created by, author

https://schema.org/checkinTime.label: checkinTime
https://schema.org/checkinTime.description: The earliest someone may check into a lodging establishment.

https://schema.org/cvdNumVent.label: cvdNumVent
https://schema.org/cvdNumVent.description: numvent - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS: Total number of ventilators available.

https://schema.org/broadcaster.label: broadcaster
https://schema.org/broadcaster.description: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.

https://schema.org/Answer.label: Answer
https://schema.org/Answer.description: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

https://schema.org/ShippingRateSettings.label: ShippingRateSettings
https://schema.org/ShippingRateSettings.description: A ShippingRateSettings represents re-usable pieces of shipping information. It is designed for publication on an URL that may be referenced via the [[shippingSettingsLink]] property of an [[OfferShippingDetails]]. Several occurrences can be published, distinguished and matched (i.e. identified/referenced) by their different values for [[shippingLabel]].

https://schema.org/ItemPage.label: ItemPage
https://schema.org/ItemPage.description: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

https://schema.org/numberOfAirbags.label: numberOfAirbags
https://schema.org/numberOfAirbags.description: The number or type of airbags in the vehicle.

https://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.label: isBasedOnUrl
https://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.description: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.

https://schema.org/SizeSystemEnumeration.label: SizeSystemEnumeration
https://schema.org/SizeSystemEnumeration.description: Enumerates common size systems for different categories of products, for example "EN-13402" or "UK" for wearables or "Imperial" for screws.

https://schema.org/reviewedBy.label: reviewedBy
https://schema.org/reviewedBy.description: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.

https://schema.org/associatedMediaReview.label: associatedMediaReview
https://schema.org/associatedMediaReview.description: An associated [[MediaReview]], related by specific common content, topic or claim. The expectation is that this property would be most typically used in cases where a single activity is conducting both claim reviews and media reviews, in which case [[relatedMediaReview]] would commonly be used on a [[ClaimReview]], while [[relatedClaimReview]] would be used on [[MediaReview]].

https://schema.org/suggestedAge.label: suggestedAge
https://schema.org/suggestedAge.description: The age or age range for the intended audience or person, for example 3-12 months for infants, 1-5 years for toddlers.

https://schema.org/measuredProperty.label: measuredProperty
https://schema.org/measuredProperty.description: The measuredProperty of an [[Observation]], typically via its [[StatisticalVariable]]. There are various kinds of applicable [[Property]]: a schema.org property, a property from other RDF-compatible systems, e.g. W3C RDF Data Cube, Data Commons, Wikidata, or schema.org extensions such as [GS1's](https://www.gs1.org/voc/?show=properties).

https://schema.org/publicationType.label: publicationType
https://schema.org/publicationType.description: The type of the medical article, taken from the US NLM MeSH publication type catalog. See also [MeSH documentation](http://www.nlm.nih.gov/mesh/pubtypes.html).

https://schema.org/EducationalOrganizati.label: EducationalOrganization
https://schema.org/EducationalOrganizati.usage_hint: Type for schools, universities, colleges. Use with schema:alumniOf (person was student) or schema:employee (person worked there).
https://schema.org/EducationalOrganizati.example_keywords: school, university, college, institute, academy, educational institution

https://schema.org/RejectAction.label: RejectAction
https://schema.org/RejectAction.description:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.

Related actions:

* [[AcceptAction]]: The antonym of RejectAction.

https://schema.org/includesObject.label: includesObject
https://schema.org/includesObject.description: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in  an [[Offer]] or [[ProductCollection]].

https://schema.org/ownedThrough.label: ownedThrough
https://schema.org/ownedThrough.description: The date and time of giving up ownership on the product.

https://schema.org/returnPolicySeasonalO.label: returnPolicySeasonalOverride
https://schema.org/returnPolicySeasonalO.description: Seasonal override of a return policy.

https://schema.org/dateRead.label: dateRead
https://schema.org/dateRead.description: The date/time at which the message has been read by the recipient if a single recipient exists.

https://schema.org/AdvertiserContentArti.label: AdvertiserContentArticle
https://schema.org/AdvertiserContentArti.description: An [[Article]] that an external entity has paid to place or to produce to its specifications. Includes [advertorials](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Advertorial), sponsored content, native advertising and other paid content.

https://schema.org/fileFormat.label: fileFormat
https://schema.org/fileFormat.description: Media type, typically MIME format (see [IANA site](http://www.iana.org/assignments/media-types/media-types.xhtml)) of the content, e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.

https://schema.org/titleEIDR.label: titleEIDR
https://schema.org/titleEIDR.description:
An [EIDR](https://eidr.org/) (Entertainment Identifier Registry) [[identifier]] representing at the most general/abstract level, a work of film or television.

For example, the motion picture known as "Ghostbusters" has a titleEIDR of  "10.5240/7EC7-228A-510A-053E-CBB8-J". This title (or work) may have several variants, which EIDR calls "edits". See [[editEIDR]].

Since schema.org types like [[Movie]], [[TVEpisode]], [[TVSeason]], and [[TVSeries]] can be used for both works and their multiple ex

https://schema.org/itemCondition.label: itemCondition
https://schema.org/itemCondition.description: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition specifying the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer. Also used for product return policies to specify the condition of products accepted for returns.

https://schema.org/bodyLocation.label: bodyLocation
https://schema.org/bodyLocation.description: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.

https://schema.org/encoding.label: encoding
https://schema.org/encoding.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.

https://schema.org/CompoundPriceSpecific.label: CompoundPriceSpecification
https://schema.org/CompoundPriceSpecific.description: A compound price specification is one that bundles multiple prices that all apply in combination for different dimensions of consumption. Use the name property of the attached unit price specification for indicating the dimension of a price component (e.g. "electricity" or "final cleaning").

https://schema.org/TrainTrip.label: TrainTrip
https://schema.org/TrainTrip.description: A trip on a commercial train line.

https://schema.org/DepartAction.label: DepartAction
https://schema.org/DepartAction.description: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from a fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

https://schema.org/ProgramMembership.label: ProgramMembership
https://schema.org/ProgramMembership.description: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

https://schema.org/releasedEvent.label: releasedEvent
https://schema.org/releasedEvent.description: The place and time the release was issued, expressed as a PublicationEvent.

https://schema.org/accountablePerson.label: accountablePerson
https://schema.org/accountablePerson.description: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/musicCompositionForm.label: musicCompositionForm
https://schema.org/musicCompositionForm.description: The type of composition (e.g. overture, sonata, symphony, etc.).

https://schema.org/steps.label: steps
https://schema.org/steps.description: A single step item (as HowToStep, text, document, video, etc.) or a HowToSection (originally misnamed 'steps'; 'step' is preferred).

https://schema.org/Ticket.label: Ticket
https://schema.org/Ticket.description: Used to describe a ticket to an event, a flight, a bus ride, etc.

https://schema.org/UserInteraction.label: UserInteraction
https://schema.org/UserInteraction.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/educationalUse.label: educationalUse
https://schema.org/educationalUse.description: The purpose of a work in the context of education; for example, 'assignment', 'group work'.

https://schema.org/subtitleLanguage.label: subtitleLanguage
https://schema.org/subtitleLanguage.description: Languages in which subtitles/captions are available, in [IETF BCP 47 standard format](http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47).

https://schema.org/chemicalComposition.label: chemicalComposition
https://schema.org/chemicalComposition.description: The chemical composition describes the identity and relative ratio of the chemical elements that make up the substance.

https://schema.org/Report.label: Report
https://schema.org/Report.description: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

https://schema.org/DataFeed.label: DataFeed
https://schema.org/DataFeed.description: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.

https://schema.org/department.label: department
https://schema.org/department.description: A relationship between an organization and a department of that organization, also described as an organization (allowing different urls, logos, opening hours). For example: a store with a pharmacy, or a bakery with a cafe.

https://schema.org/playMode.label: playMode
https://schema.org/playMode.description: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.  The game can be marked as multi-player, co-op and single-player at the same time.

https://schema.org/ticketedSeat.label: ticketedSeat
https://schema.org/ticketedSeat.description: The seat associated with the ticket.

https://schema.org/availableChannel.label: availableChannel
https://schema.org/availableChannel.description: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).

https://schema.org/sizeGroup.label: sizeGroup
https://schema.org/sizeGroup.description: The size group (also known as "size type") for a product's size. Size groups are common in the fashion industry to define size segments and suggested audiences for wearable products. Multiple values can be combined, for example "men's big and tall", "petite maternity" or "regular".

https://schema.org/PlaceOfWorship.label: PlaceOfWorship
https://schema.org/PlaceOfWorship.description: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

https://schema.org/WebSite.label: WebSite
https://schema.org/WebSite.description: A WebSite is a set of related web pages and other items typically served from a single web domain and accessible via URLs.

https://schema.org/costCategory.label: costCategory
https://schema.org/costCategory.description: The category of cost, such as wholesale, retail, reimbursement cap, etc.

https://schema.org/cargoVolume.label: cargoVolume
https://schema.org/cargoVolume.description:
The available volume for cargo or luggage. For automobiles, this is usually the trunk volume.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, FTQ for cubic foot/feet

Note: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.label: greaterOrEqual
https://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.

https://schema.org/LibrarySystem.label: LibrarySystem
https://schema.org/LibrarySystem.description: A [[LibrarySystem]] is a collaborative system amongst several libraries.

https://schema.org/legalRepresentative.label: legalRepresentative
https://schema.org/legalRepresentative.description: One or multiple persons who represent this organization legally such as CEO or sole administrator.

https://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.label: accountMinimumInflow
https://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.description: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.

https://schema.org/bioChemSimilarity.label: bioChemSimilarity
https://schema.org/bioChemSimilarity.description: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.

https://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeason.label: CreativeWorkSeason
https://schema.org/CreativeWorkSeason.description: A media season, e.g. TV, radio, video game etc.

https://schema.org/regionsAllowed.label: regionsAllowed
https://schema.org/regionsAllowed.description: The regions where the media is allowed. If not specified, then it's assumed to be allowed everywhere. Specify the countries in [ISO 3166 format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166).

https://schema.org/IncentiveType.label: IncentiveType
https://schema.org/IncentiveType.description: Enumerates common financial incentives for products, including tax credits, tax deductions, rebates and subsidies, etc.

https://schema.org/occupancy.label: occupancy
https://schema.org/occupancy.description:
The allowed total occupancy for the accommodation in persons (including infants etc). For individual accommodations, this is not necessarily the legal maximum but defines the permitted usage as per the contractual agreement (e.g. a double room used by a single person).
Typical unit code(s): C62 for person.

https://schema.org/physicalRequirement.label: physicalRequirement
https://schema.org/physicalRequirement.description: A description of the types of physical activity associated with the job. Defined terms such as those in O*net may be used, but note that there is no way to specify the level of ability as well as its nature when using a defined term.

https://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatient.label: isAcceptingNewPatients
https://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatient.description: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.

https://schema.org/Vessel.label: Vessel
https://schema.org/Vessel.description: A component of the human body circulatory system comprised of an intricate network of hollow tubes that transport blood throughout the entire body.

https://schema.org/DonateAction.label: DonateAction
https://schema.org/DonateAction.description: The act of providing goods, services, or money without compensation, often for philanthropic reasons.

https://schema.org/LoseAction.label: LoseAction
https://schema.org/LoseAction.description: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

https://schema.org/productionDate.label: productionDate
https://schema.org/productionDate.description: The date of production of the item, e.g. vehicle.

https://schema.org/OrganizeAction.label: OrganizeAction
https://schema.org/OrganizeAction.description: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

https://schema.org/fuelConsumption.label: fuelConsumption
https://schema.org/fuelConsumption.description:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km.  Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the absolu

https://schema.org/PayAction.label: PayAction
https://schema.org/PayAction.description: An agent pays a price to a participant.

https://schema.org/sportsActivityLocatio.label: sportsActivityLocation
https://schema.org/sportsActivityLocatio.description: A sub property of location. The sports activity location where this action occurred.

https://schema.org/activityFrequency.label: activityFrequency
https://schema.org/activityFrequency.description: How often one should engage in the activity.

https://schema.org/foundingLocation.label: foundingLocation
https://schema.org/foundingLocation.description: The place where the Organization was founded.

https://schema.org/schemaVersion.label: schemaVersion
https://schema.org/schemaVersion.description:
Indicates (by URL or string) a particular version of a schema used in some CreativeWork. This property was created primarily to
    indicate the use of a specific schema.org release, e.g. ```10.0``` as a simple string, or more explicitly via URL, ```https://schema.org/docs/releases.html#v10.0```. There may be situations in which other schemas might usefully be referenced this way, e.g. ```http://dublincore.org/specifications/dublin-core/dces/1999-07-02/``` but this has not been carefully explore

https://schema.org/companyRegistration.label: companyRegistration
https://schema.org/companyRegistration.description: The official registration number of a business including the organization that issued it such as Company House or Chamber of Commerce.

https://schema.org/businessFunction.label: businessFunction
https://schema.org/businessFunction.description: The business function (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose) of the offer or component of a bundle (TypeAndQuantityNode). The default is http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell.

https://schema.org/minimumPaymentDue.label: minimumPaymentDue
https://schema.org/minimumPaymentDue.description: The minimum payment required at this time.

https://schema.org/durationOfWarranty.label: durationOfWarranty
https://schema.org/durationOfWarranty.description: The duration of the warranty promise. Common unitCode values are ANN for year, MON for months, or DAY for days.

https://schema.org/workFeatured.label: workFeatured
https://schema.org/workFeatured.description:
A work featured in some event, e.g. exhibited in an ExhibitionEvent.
       Specific subproperties are available for workPerformed (e.g. a play), or a workPresented (a Movie at a ScreeningEvent).

https://schema.org/codeSampleType.label: codeSampleType
https://schema.org/codeSampleType.description: What type of code sample: full (compile ready) solution, code snippet, inline code, scripts, template.

https://schema.org/acquiredFrom.label: acquiredFrom
https://schema.org/acquiredFrom.description: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.

https://schema.org/WearableMeasurementTy.label: WearableMeasurementTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/WearableMeasurementTy.description: Enumerates common types of measurement for wearables products.

https://schema.org/PodcastEpisode.label: PodcastEpisode
https://schema.org/PodcastEpisode.description: A single episode of a podcast series.

https://schema.org/dateVehicleFirstRegis.label: dateVehicleFirstRegistered
https://schema.org/dateVehicleFirstRegis.description: The date of the first registration of the vehicle with the respective public authorities.

https://schema.org/Time.label: Time
https://schema.org/Time.description: A point in time recurring on multiple days in the form hh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see [XML schema for details](http://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-2/#time)).

https://schema.org/Energy.label: Energy
https://schema.org/Energy.description: Properties that take Energy as values are of the form '<Number> <Energy unit of measure>'.

https://schema.org/hasMemberProgram.label: hasMemberProgram
https://schema.org/hasMemberProgram.description: MemberProgram offered by an Organization, for example an eCommerce merchant or an airline.

https://schema.org/member.label: member
https://schema.org/member.description: A member of an Organization or a ProgramMembership. Organizations can be members of organizations; ProgramMembership is typically for individuals.

https://schema.org/Campground.label: Campground
https://schema.org/Campground.description:
A camping site, campsite, or [[Campground]] is a place used for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically containing individual [[CampingPitch]] locations. \n\n
In British English a campsite is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual,

https://schema.org/Schedule.label: Schedule
https://schema.org/Schedule.description:
A schedule defines a repeating time period used to describe a regularly occurring [[Event]]. At a minimum a schedule will specify [[repeatFrequency]] which describes the interval between occurrences of the event. Additional information can be provided to specify the schedule more precisely.
      This includes identifying the day(s) of the week or month when the recurring event will take place, in addition to its start and end time. Schedules may also
      have start and end dates to indicate w

https://schema.org/Hotel.label: Hotel
https://schema.org/Hotel.description:
A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging paid on a short-term basis (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/catalogNumber.label: catalogNumber
https://schema.org/catalogNumber.description: The catalog number for the release.

https://schema.org/potentialAction.label: potentialAction
https://schema.org/potentialAction.description: Indicates a potential Action, which describes an idealized action in which this thing would play an 'object' role.

https://schema.org/jurisdiction.label: jurisdiction
https://schema.org/jurisdiction.description: Indicates a legal jurisdiction, e.g. of some legislation, or where some government service is based.

https://schema.org/FinancialIncentive.label: FinancialIncentive
https://schema.org/FinancialIncentive.description:
Represents financial incentives for goods/services offered by an organization (or individual).

Typically contains the [[name]] of the incentive, the [[incentivizedItem]], the [[incentiveAmount]], the [[incentiveStatus]], [[incentiveType]], the [[provider]] of the incentive, and [[eligibleWithSupplier]].

Optionally contains criteria on whether the incentive is limited based on [[purchaseType]], [[purchasePriceLimit]], [[incomeLimit]], and the [[qualifiedExpense]].

https://schema.org/isUnlabelledFallback.label: isUnlabelledFallback
https://schema.org/isUnlabelledFallback.description: This can be marked 'true' to indicate that some published [[DeliveryTimeSettings]] or [[ShippingRateSettings]] are intended to apply to all [[OfferShippingDetails]] published by the same merchant, when referenced by a [[shippingSettingsLink]] in those settings. It is not meaningful to use a 'true' value for this property alongside a transitTimeLabel (for [[DeliveryTimeSettings]]) or shippingLabel (for [[ShippingRateSettings]]), since this property is for use with unlabelled settings.

https://schema.org/dateDeleted.label: dateDeleted
https://schema.org/dateDeleted.description: The datetime the item was removed from the DataFeed.

https://schema.org/adverseOutcome.label: adverseOutcome
https://schema.org/adverseOutcome.description: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or otherwise life-threatening or requiring immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriousAdverseOutcome instead.

https://schema.org/Claim.label: Claim
