https://schema.org/Claim.description: A [[Claim]] in Schema.org represents a specific, factually-oriented claim that could be the [[itemReviewed]] in a [[ClaimReview]]. The content of a claim can be summarized with the [[text]] property. Variations on well known claims can have their common identity indicated via [[sameAs]] links, and summarized with a [[name]]. Ideally, a [[Claim]] description includes enough contextual information to minimize the risk of ambiguity or inclarity. In practice, many claims are better understood in the

https://schema.org/ParentAudience.label: ParentAudience
https://schema.org/ParentAudience.description: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

https://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.label: accessibilityHazard
https://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.description: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityHazard-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/correction.label: correction
https://schema.org/correction.description: Indicates a correction to a [[CreativeWork]], either via a [[CorrectionComment]], textually or in another document.

https://schema.org/recipeYield.label: recipeYield
https://schema.org/recipeYield.description: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).

https://schema.org/Clip.label: Clip
https://schema.org/Clip.description: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

https://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMetho.label: appliesToPaymentMethod
https://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMetho.description: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.

https://schema.org/pageStart.label: pageStart
https://schema.org/pageStart.description: The page on which the work starts; for example "135" or "xiii".

https://schema.org/episodeNumber.label: episodeNumber
https://schema.org/episodeNumber.description: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.

https://schema.org/fulfillmentType.label: fulfillmentType
https://schema.org/fulfillmentType.description: Type of fulfillment applicable to the [[ShippingService]].

https://schema.org/advanceBookingRequire.label: advanceBookingRequirement
https://schema.org/advanceBookingRequire.description: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.

https://schema.org/HowToItem.label: HowToItem
https://schema.org/HowToItem.description: An item used as either a tool or supply when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.

https://schema.org/doseValue.label: doseValue
https://schema.org/doseValue.description: The value of the dose, e.g. 500.

https://schema.org/HomeAndConstructionBu.label: HomeAndConstructionBusiness
https://schema.org/HomeAndConstructionBu.description:
A construction business.

A HomeAndConstructionBusiness is a [[LocalBusiness]] that provides services around homes and buildings.

As a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

https://schema.org/InformAction.label: InformAction
https://schema.org/InformAction.description: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.

https://schema.org/VideoGallery.label: VideoGallery
https://schema.org/VideoGallery.description: Web page type: Video gallery page.

https://schema.org/hasOccupation.label: hasOccupation
https://schema.org/hasOccupation.description: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

https://schema.org/differentialDiagnosis.label: differentialDiagnosis
https://schema.org/differentialDiagnosis.description: One of a set of differential diagnoses for the condition. Specifically, a closely-related or competing diagnosis typically considered later in the cognitive process whereby this medical condition is distinguished from others most likely responsible for a similar collection of signs and symptoms to reach the most parsimonious diagnosis or diagnoses in a patient.

https://schema.org/printSection.label: printSection
https://schema.org/printSection.description: If this NewsArticle appears in print, this field indicates the print section in which the article appeared.

https://schema.org/menu.label: menu
https://schema.org/menu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

https://schema.org/doesNotShip.label: doesNotShip
https://schema.org/doesNotShip.description: Indicates when shipping to a particular [[shippingDestination]] is not available.

https://schema.org/functionalClass.label: functionalClass
https://schema.org/functionalClass.description: The degree of mobility the joint allows.

https://schema.org/drugClass.label: drugClass
https://schema.org/drugClass.description: The class of drug this belongs to (e.g., statins).

https://schema.org/TierBenefitEnumeratio.label: TierBenefitEnumeration
https://schema.org/TierBenefitEnumeratio.description: An enumeration of possible benefits as part of a loyalty (members) program.

https://schema.org/legislationCountersig.label: legislationCountersignedBy
https://schema.org/legislationCountersig.description: The person or organization that countersigned the legislation. Depending on the legal context, a countersignature can indicate that the signed authority undertakes to assume responsibility for texts emanating from a person who is inviolable and irresponsible, (for example a King, Grand Duc or President), or that the authority is in charge of the implementation of the text.

https://schema.org/geoDisjoint.label: geoDisjoint
https://schema.org/geoDisjoint.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: "they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

https://schema.org/MemberProgram.label: MemberProgram
https://schema.org/MemberProgram.description: A MemberProgram defines a loyalty (or membership) program that provides its members with certain benefits, for example better pricing, free shipping or returns, or the ability to earn loyalty points. Member programs may have multiple tiers, for example silver and gold members, each with different benefits.

https://schema.org/menuAddOn.label: menuAddOn
https://schema.org/menuAddOn.description: Additional menu item(s) such as a side dish of salad or side order of fries that can be added to this menu item. Additionally it can be a menu section containing allowed add-on menu items for this menu item.

https://schema.org/TrainReservation.label: TrainReservation
https://schema.org/TrainReservation.description: A reservation for train travel.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/collectionSize.label: collectionSize
https://schema.org/collectionSize.description: The number of items in the [[Collection]].

https://schema.org/arrivalAirport.label: arrivalAirport
https://schema.org/arrivalAirport.description: The airport where the flight terminates.

https://schema.org/MusicReleaseFormatTyp.label: MusicReleaseFormatType
https://schema.org/MusicReleaseFormatTyp.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

https://schema.org/buyer.label: buyer
https://schema.org/buyer.description: A sub property of participant. The participant/person/organization that bought the object.

https://schema.org/musicGroupMember.label: musicGroupMember
https://schema.org/musicGroupMember.description: A member of a music group—for example, John, Paul, George, or Ringo.

https://schema.org/LendAction.label: LendAction
https://schema.org/LendAction.description:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

* [[BorrowAction]]: Reciprocal of LendAction.

https://schema.org/CreditCard.label: CreditCard
https://schema.org/CreditCard.description:
A card payment method of a particular brand or name.  Used to mark up a particular payment method and/or the financial product/service that supplies the card account.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#AmericanExpress
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DinersClub
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Discover
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#JCB
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#MasterCard
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#VISA

https://schema.org/Vehicle.label: Vehicle
https://schema.org/Vehicle.description: A vehicle is a device that is designed or used to transport people or cargo over land, water, air, or through space.

https://schema.org/HyperTocEntry.label: HyperTocEntry
https://schema.org/HyperTocEntry.description: A HyperToEntry is an item within a [[HyperToc]], which represents a hypertext table of contents for complex media objects, such as [[VideoObject]], [[AudioObject]]. The media object itself is indicated using [[associatedMedia]]. Each section of interest within that content can be described with a [[HyperTocEntry]], with associated [[startOffset]] and [[endOffset]]. When several entries are all from the same file, [[associatedMedia]] is used on the overarching [[HyperTocEntry]]; if the content ha

https://schema.org/Newspaper.label: Newspaper
https://schema.org/Newspaper.description: A publication containing information about varied topics that are pertinent to general information, a geographic area, or a specific subject matter (i.e. business, culture, education). Often published daily.

https://schema.org/proteinContent.label: proteinContent
https://schema.org/proteinContent.description: The number of grams of protein.

https://schema.org/MedicalOrganization.label: MedicalOrganization
https://schema.org/MedicalOrganization.description: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

https://schema.org/travelBans.label: travelBans
https://schema.org/travelBans.description: Information about travel bans, e.g. in the context of a pandemic.

https://schema.org/lifeEvent.label: lifeEvent
https://schema.org/lifeEvent.description: A life event like baptism, communions, Bar Mitzvahs, Aqiqah, Namakarana, Miyamairi, burial, ....

https://schema.org/rsvpResponse.label: rsvpResponse
https://schema.org/rsvpResponse.description: The response (yes, no, maybe) to the RSVP.

https://schema.org/documentation.label: documentation
https://schema.org/documentation.description: Further documentation describing the Web API in more detail.

https://schema.org/partOfSystem.label: partOfSystem
https://schema.org/partOfSystem.description: The anatomical or organ system that this structure is part of.

https://schema.org/Accommodation.label: Accommodation
https://schema.org/Accommodation.description:
An accommodation is a place that can accommodate human beings, e.g. a hotel room, a camping pitch, or a meeting room. Many accommodations are for overnight stays, but this is not a mandatory requirement. For more specific types of accommodations not defined in schema.org, one can use [[additionalType]] with external vocabularies.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/actionApplication.label: actionApplication
https://schema.org/actionApplication.description: An application that can complete the request.

https://schema.org/isVariantOf.label: isVariantOf
https://schema.org/isVariantOf.description: Indicates the kind of product that this is a variant of. In the case of [[ProductModel]], this is a pointer (from a ProductModel) to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive. In the case of a [[ProductGroup]], the group description also serves as a template, representing a set of Products that vary on explicitly defined, specific dimensions only (so i

https://schema.org/bloodSupply.label: bloodSupply
https://schema.org/bloodSupply.description: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.

https://schema.org/studyLocation.label: studyLocation
https://schema.org/studyLocation.description: The location in which the study is taking/took place.

https://schema.org/itemListElement.label: itemListElement
https://schema.org/itemListElement.description:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in y

https://schema.org/MedicalTrialDesign.label: MedicalTrialDesign
https://schema.org/MedicalTrialDesign.description: Design models for medical trials. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/unitText.label: unitText
https://schema.org/unitText.description: A string or text indicating the unit of measurement. Useful if you cannot provide a standard unit code for unitCode.

https://schema.org/PalliativeProcedure.label: PalliativeProcedure
https://schema.org/PalliativeProcedure.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for palliative purposes, aimed at relieving the symptoms of an underlying health condition.

https://schema.org/AlignmentObject.label: AlignmentObject
https://schema.org/AlignmentObject.description:
An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.
Should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

https://schema.org/legislationCorrects.label: legislationCorrects
https://schema.org/legislationCorrects.description: Another legislation in which this one introduces textual changes, like correction of spelling mistakes, with no legal impact (for modifications that have legal impact, use legislationAmends).

https://schema.org/WebPageElement.label: WebPageElement
https://schema.org/WebPageElement.description: A web page element, like a table or an image.

https://schema.org/MusicAlbumProductionT.label: MusicAlbumProductionType
https://schema.org/MusicAlbumProductionT.description: Classification of the album by its type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

https://schema.org/longitude.label: longitude
https://schema.org/longitude.description: The longitude of a location. For example ```-122.08585``` ([WGS 84](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Geodetic_System)).

https://schema.org/WebAPI.label: WebAPI
https://schema.org/WebAPI.description: An application programming interface accessible over Web/Internet technologies.

https://schema.org/honorificSuffix.label: honorificSuffix
https://schema.org/honorificSuffix.description: An honorific suffix following a Person's name such as M.D./PhD/MSCSW.

https://schema.org/contactOption.label: contactOption
https://schema.org/contactOption.description: An option available on this contact point (e.g. a toll-free number or support for hearing-impaired callers).

https://schema.org/inStoreReturnsOffered.label: inStoreReturnsOffered
https://schema.org/inStoreReturnsOffered.description: Are in-store returns offered? (For more advanced return methods use the [[returnMethod]] property.)

https://schema.org/DislikeAction.label: DislikeAction
https://schema.org/DislikeAction.description: The act of expressing a negative sentiment about the object. An agent dislikes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

https://schema.org/minPrice.label: minPrice
https://schema.org/minPrice.description: The lowest price if the price is a range.

https://schema.org/geoIntersects.label: geoIntersects
https://schema.org/geoIntersects.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/urlTemplate.label: urlTemplate
https://schema.org/urlTemplate.description: An url template (RFC6570) that will be used to construct the target of the execution of the action.

https://schema.org/healthPlanMarketingUr.label: healthPlanMarketingUrl
https://schema.org/healthPlanMarketingUr.description: The URL that goes directly to the plan brochure for the specific standard plan or plan variation.

https://schema.org/cvdNumVentUse.label: cvdNumVentUse
https://schema.org/cvdNumVentUse.description: numventuse - MECHANICAL VENTILATORS IN USE: Total number of ventilators in use.

https://schema.org/fuelType.label: fuelType
https://schema.org/fuelType.description: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.

https://schema.org/availableService.label: availableService
https://schema.org/availableService.description: A medical service available from this provider.

https://schema.org/estimatedCost.label: estimatedCost
https://schema.org/estimatedCost.description: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.

https://schema.org/speed.label: speed
https://schema.org/speed.description:
The speed range of the vehicle. If the vehicle is powered by an engine, the upper limit of the speed range (indicated by [[maxValue]]) should be the maximum speed achievable under regular conditions.

Typical unit code(s): KMH for km/h, HM for mile per hour (0.447 04 m/s), KNT for knot

*Note 1: Use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate the range. Typically, the minimal value is zero.
* Note 2: There are many different ways of measuring the speed range. You can link to information about

https://schema.org/subOrganization.label: subOrganization
https://schema.org/subOrganization.description: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

https://schema.org/temporal.label: temporal
https://schema.org/temporal.description:
The "temporal" property can be used in cases where more specific properties
(e.g. [[temporalCoverage]], [[dateCreated]], [[dateModified]], [[datePublished]]) are not known to be appropriate.

https://schema.org/announcementLocation.label: announcementLocation
https://schema.org/announcementLocation.description: Indicates a specific [[CivicStructure]] or [[LocalBusiness]] associated with the SpecialAnnouncement. For example, a specific testing facility or business with special opening hours. For a larger geographic region like a quarantine of an entire region, use [[spatialCoverage]].

https://schema.org/MedicalProcedureType.label: MedicalProcedureType
https://schema.org/MedicalProcedureType.description: An enumeration that describes different types of medical procedures.

https://schema.org/legalAddress.label: legalAddress
https://schema.org/legalAddress.description: The legal address of an organization which acts as the officially registered address used for legal and tax purposes. The legal address can be different from the place of operations of a business and other addresses can be part of an organization.

https://schema.org/targetProduct.label: targetProduct
https://schema.org/targetProduct.description: Target Operating System / Product to which the code applies.  If applies to several versions, just the product name can be used.

https://schema.org/studySubject.label: studySubject
https://schema.org/studySubject.description: A subject of the study, i.e. one of the medical conditions, therapies, devices, drugs, etc. investigated by the study.

https://schema.org/Offer.label: Offer
https://schema.org/Offer.description:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

Note: As the [[businessFunction]] property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.

For [GT

https://schema.org/publishedBy.label: publishedBy
https://schema.org/publishedBy.description: An agent associated with the publication event.

https://schema.org/MedicalEnumeration.label: MedicalEnumeration
https://schema.org/MedicalEnumeration.description: Enumerations related to health and the practice of medicine: A concept that is used to attribute a quality to another concept, as a qualifier, a collection of items or a listing of all of the elements of a set in medicine practice.

https://schema.org/isSimilarTo.label: isSimilarTo
https://schema.org/isSimilarTo.description: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).

https://schema.org/HowToSupply.label: HowToSupply
https://schema.org/HowToSupply.description: A supply consumed when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.

https://schema.org/stageAsNumber.label: stageAsNumber
https://schema.org/stageAsNumber.description: The stage represented as a number, e.g. 3.

https://schema.org/orderValue.label: orderValue
https://schema.org/orderValue.description: Minimum and maximum order value for which these shipping conditions are valid.

https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.label: energyEfficiencyScaleMax
https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.description: Specifies the most energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

https://schema.org/byMonthDay.label: byMonthDay
https://schema.org/byMonthDay.description: Defines the day(s) of the month on which a recurring [[Event]] takes place. Specified as an [[Integer]] between 1-31.

https://schema.org/speakable.label: speakable
https://schema.org/speakable.description:
Indicates sections of a Web page that are particularly 'speakable' in the sense of being highlighted as being especially appropriate for text-to-speech conversion. Other sections of a page may also be usefully spoken in particular circumstances; the 'speakable' property serves to indicate the parts most likely to be generally useful for speech.

The *speakable* property can be repeated an arbitrary number of times, with three kinds of possible 'content-locator' values:

1.) *id-value* URL refere

https://schema.org/relatedStructure.label: relatedStructure
https://schema.org/relatedStructure.description: Related anatomical structure(s) that are not part of the system but relate or connect to it, such as vascular bundles associated with an organ system.

https://schema.org/nextItem.label: nextItem
https://schema.org/nextItem.description: A link to the ListItem that follows the current one.

https://schema.org/requiresSubscription.label: requiresSubscription
https://schema.org/requiresSubscription.description: Indicates if use of the media require a subscription  (either paid or free). Allowed values are ```true``` or ```false``` (note that an earlier version had 'yes', 'no').

https://schema.org/dropoffLocation.label: dropoffLocation
https://schema.org/dropoffLocation.description: Where a rental car can be dropped off.

https://schema.org/executableLibraryName.label: executableLibraryName
https://schema.org/executableLibraryName.description: Library file name, e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.

https://schema.org/CategoryCodeSet.label: CategoryCodeSet
https://schema.org/CategoryCodeSet.description: A set of Category Code values.

https://schema.org/gracePeriod.label: gracePeriod
https://schema.org/gracePeriod.description: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.

https://schema.org/reservationStatus.label: reservationStatus
https://schema.org/reservationStatus.description: The current status of the reservation.

https://schema.org/course.label: course
https://schema.org/course.description: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.

https://schema.org/ArchiveComponent.label: ArchiveComponent
https://schema.org/ArchiveComponent.description: An intangible type to be applied to any archive content, carrying with it a set of properties required to describe archival items and collections.

https://schema.org/instrument.label: instrument
https://schema.org/instrument.description: The object that helped the agent perform the action. E.g. John wrote a book with *a pen*.

https://schema.org/LegislativeBuilding.label: LegislativeBuilding
https://schema.org/LegislativeBuilding.description: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

https://schema.org/SatiricalArticle.label: SatiricalArticle
https://schema.org/SatiricalArticle.description: An [[Article]] whose content is primarily [[satirical]](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Satire) in nature, i.e. unlikely to be literally true. A satirical article is sometimes but not necessarily also a [[NewsArticle]]. [[ScholarlyArticle]]s are also sometimes satirized.

https://schema.org/ViewAction.label: ViewAction
https://schema.org/ViewAction.description: The act of consuming static visual content.

https://schema.org/EUEnergyEfficiencyEnu.label: EUEnergyEfficiencyEnumeration
https://schema.org/EUEnergyEfficiencyEnu.description: Enumerates the EU energy efficiency classes A-G as well as A+, A++, and A+++ as defined in EU directive 2017/1369.

https://schema.org/checkoutTime.label: checkoutTime
https://schema.org/checkoutTime.description: The latest someone may check out of a lodging establishment.

https://schema.org/FollowAction.label: FollowAction
https://schema.org/FollowAction.description:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.

Related actions:

* [[BefriendAction]]: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is *not* necessarily reciprocal.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.
* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that t

https://schema.org/AnatomicalStructure.label: AnatomicalStructure
https://schema.org/AnatomicalStructure.description: Any part of the human body, typically a component of an anatomical system. Organs, tissues, and cells are all anatomical structures.

https://schema.org/TransferAction.label: TransferAction
https://schema.org/TransferAction.description: The act of transferring/moving (abstract or concrete) animate or inanimate objects from one place to another.

https://schema.org/PawnShop.label: PawnShop
https://schema.org/PawnShop.description: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.

https://schema.org/AskAction.label: AskAction
https://schema.org/AskAction.description:
The act of posing a question / favor to someone.

Related actions:

* [[ReplyAction]]: Appears generally as a response to AskAction.

https://schema.org/expires.label: expires
https://schema.org/expires.description: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a [[VideoObject]] or [[NewsArticle]] whose availability or relevance is time-limited, a [[ClaimReview]] fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date, or a [[Certification]] the validity has expired.

https://schema.org/ImagingTest.label: ImagingTest
https://schema.org/ImagingTest.description: Any medical imaging modality typically used for diagnostic purposes.

https://schema.org/GeospatialGeometry.label: GeospatialGeometry
https://schema.org/GeospatialGeometry.description: (Eventually to be defined as) a supertype of GeoShape designed to accommodate definitions from Geo-Spatial best practices.

https://schema.org/interestRate.label: interestRate
https://schema.org/interestRate.description: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.

https://schema.org/physiologicalBenefits.label: physiologicalBenefits
https://schema.org/physiologicalBenefits.description: Specific physiologic benefits associated to the plan.

https://schema.org/ReviewAction.label: ReviewAction
https://schema.org/ReviewAction.description: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

https://schema.org/relatedCondition.label: relatedCondition
https://schema.org/relatedCondition.description: A medical condition associated with this anatomy.

https://schema.org/WebContent.label: WebContent
https://schema.org/WebContent.description: WebContent is a type representing all [[WebPage]], [[WebSite]] and [[WebPageElement]] content. It is sometimes the case that detailed distinctions between Web pages, sites and their parts are not always important or obvious. The  [[WebContent]] type makes it easier to describe Web-addressable content without requiring such distinctions to always be stated. (The intent is that the existing types [[WebPage]], [[WebSite]] and [[WebPageElement]] will eventually be declared as subtypes of [[WebConten

https://schema.org/Barcode.label: Barcode
https://schema.org/Barcode.description: An image of a visual machine-readable code such as a barcode or QR code.

https://schema.org/ReceiveAction.label: ReceiveAction
https://schema.org/ReceiveAction.description:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object that has been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.

Related actions:

* [[SendAction]]: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
* [[TakeAction]]: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transferred (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

https://schema.org/variableMeasured.label: variableMeasured
https://schema.org/variableMeasured.description: The variableMeasured property can indicate (repeated as necessary) the  variables that are measured in some dataset, either described as text or as pairs of identifier and description using PropertyValue, or more explicitly as a [[StatisticalVariable]].

https://schema.org/knows.label: knows
https://schema.org/knows.description: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.
https://schema.org/knows.usage_hint: Person that this person knows. Use for general acquaintance relationships.

https://schema.org/numberOfEpisodes.label: numberOfEpisodes
https://schema.org/numberOfEpisodes.description: The number of episodes in this season or series.

https://schema.org/programType.label: programType
https://schema.org/programType.description: The type of educational or occupational program. For example, classroom, internship, alternance, etc.

https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.label: energyEfficiencyScaleMin
https://schema.org/energyEfficiencyScale.description: Specifies the least energy efficient class on the regulated EU energy consumption scale for the product category a product belongs to. For example, energy consumption for televisions placed on the market after January 1, 2020 is scaled from D to A+++.

https://schema.org/engineType.label: engineType
https://schema.org/engineType.description: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.

https://schema.org/Attorney.label: Attorney
https://schema.org/Attorney.description: Professional service: Attorney. \n\nThis type is deprecated - [[LegalService]] is more inclusive and less ambiguous.

https://schema.org/merchantReturnLink.label: merchantReturnLink
https://schema.org/merchantReturnLink.description: Specifies a Web page or service by URL, for product returns.

https://schema.org/applicationCategory.label: applicationCategory
https://schema.org/applicationCategory.description: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.

https://schema.org/ExercisePlan.label: ExercisePlan
https://schema.org/ExercisePlan.description: Fitness-related activity designed for a specific health-related purpose, including defined exercise routines as well as activity prescribed by a clinician.

https://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.label: hasDeliveryMethod
https://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.description: Method used for delivery or shipping.

https://schema.org/replacee.label: replacee
https://schema.org/replacee.description: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.

https://schema.org/aggregateElement.label: aggregateElement
https://schema.org/aggregateElement.description: Indicates a prototype of the elements in the list that is used to hold aggregate information (ratings, offers, etc.).

https://schema.org/WPAdBlock.label: WPAdBlock
https://schema.org/WPAdBlock.description: An advertising section of the page.

https://schema.org/MonetaryAmountDistrib.label: MonetaryAmountDistribution
https://schema.org/MonetaryAmountDistrib.description: A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.

https://schema.org/industry.label: industry
https://schema.org/industry.description: The industry associated with the job position.

https://schema.org/bookingAgent.label: bookingAgent
https://schema.org/bookingAgent.description: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.

https://schema.org/ReportageNewsArticle.label: ReportageNewsArticle
https://schema.org/ReportageNewsArticle.description:
The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is a subtype of [[NewsArticle]] representing
 news articles which are the result of journalistic news reporting conventions.

In practice many news publishers produce a wide variety of article types, many of which might be considered a [[NewsArticle]] but not a [[ReportageNewsArticle]]. For example, opinion pieces, reviews, analysis, sponsored or satirical articles, or articles that combine several of these elements.

The [[ReportageNewsArticle]] type is based o

https://schema.org/contactPoints.label: contactPoints
https://schema.org/contactPoints.description: A contact point for a person or organization.

https://schema.org/paymentMethod.label: paymentMethod
https://schema.org/paymentMethod.description: The name of the credit card or other method of payment for the order.

https://schema.org/diet.label: diet
https://schema.org/diet.description: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.

https://schema.org/StatisticalPopulation.label: StatisticalPopulation
https://schema.org/StatisticalPopulation.description: A StatisticalPopulation is a set of instances of a certain given type that satisfy some set of constraints. The property [[populationType]] is used to specify the type. Any property that can be used on instances of that type can appear on the statistical population. For example, a [[StatisticalPopulation]] representing all [[Person]]s with a [[homeLocation]] of East Podunk California would be described by applying the appropriate [[homeLocation]] and [[populationType]] properties to a [[Statisti

https://schema.org/SizeGroupEnumeration.label: SizeGroupEnumeration
https://schema.org/SizeGroupEnumeration.description: Enumerates common size groups for various product categories.

https://schema.org/endorsee.label: endorsee
https://schema.org/endorsee.description: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.

https://schema.org/Canal.label: Canal
https://schema.org/Canal.description: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

https://schema.org/copyrightNotice.label: copyrightNotice
https://schema.org/copyrightNotice.description: Text of a notice appropriate for describing the copyright aspects of this Creative Work, ideally indicating the owner of the copyright for the Work.

https://schema.org/boardingGroup.label: boardingGroup
https://schema.org/boardingGroup.description: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.

https://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.label: exchangeRateSpread
https://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.description: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.

https://schema.org/BoardingPolicyType.label: BoardingPolicyType
https://schema.org/BoardingPolicyType.description: A type of boarding policy used by an airline.

https://schema.org/isEncodedByBioChemEnt.label: isEncodedByBioChemEntity
https://schema.org/isEncodedByBioChemEnt.description: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.

https://schema.org/prescriptionStatus.label: prescriptionStatus
https://schema.org/prescriptionStatus.description: Indicates the status of drug prescription, e.g. local catalogs classifications or whether the drug is available by prescription or over-the-counter, etc.

https://schema.org/PropertyValue.label: PropertyValue
https://schema.org/PropertyValue.description: A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.\n\n Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

https://schema.org/HVACBusiness.label: HVACBusiness
https://schema.org/HVACBusiness.description: A business that provides Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning services.

https://schema.org/starRating.label: starRating
https://schema.org/starRating.description: An official rating for a lodging business or food establishment, e.g. from national associations or standards bodies. Use the author property to indicate the rating organization, e.g. as an Organization with name such as (e.g. HOTREC, DEHOGA, WHR, or Hotelstars).

https://schema.org/newsUpdatesAndGuideli.label: newsUpdatesAndGuidelines
https://schema.org/newsUpdatesAndGuideli.description: Indicates a page with news updates and guidelines. This could often be (but is not required to be) the main page containing [[SpecialAnnouncement]] markup on a site.

https://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.label: broadcastAffiliateOf
https://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.description: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.

https://schema.org/infectiousAgent.label: infectiousAgent
https://schema.org/infectiousAgent.description: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.

https://schema.org/netWorth.label: netWorth
https://schema.org/netWorth.description: The total financial value of the person as calculated by subtracting the total value of liabilities from the total value of assets.

https://schema.org/availableIn.label: availableIn
https://schema.org/availableIn.description: The location in which the strength is available.

https://schema.org/cvdFacilityCounty.label: cvdFacilityCounty
https://schema.org/cvdFacilityCounty.description: Name of the County of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityId]] to identify the facility. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

https://schema.org/hiringOrganization.label: hiringOrganization
https://schema.org/hiringOrganization.description: Organization or Person offering the job position.

https://schema.org/offerCount.label: offerCount
https://schema.org/offerCount.description: The number of offers for the product.

https://schema.org/StatisticalVariable.label: StatisticalVariable
https://schema.org/StatisticalVariable.description: [[StatisticalVariable]] represents any type of statistical metric that can be measured at a place and time. The usage pattern for [[StatisticalVariable]] is typically expressed using [[Observation]] with an explicit [[populationType]], which is a type, typically drawn from Schema.org. Each [[StatisticalVariable]] is marked as a [[ConstraintNode]], meaning that some properties (those listed using [[constraintProperty]]) serve in this setting solely to define the statistical variable rather than l

https://schema.org/InstallAction.label: InstallAction
https://schema.org/InstallAction.description: The act of installing an application.

https://schema.org/DataType.label: DataType
https://schema.org/DataType.description: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

https://schema.org/UserPlusOnes.label: UserPlusOnes
https://schema.org/UserPlusOnes.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/jobLocationType.label: jobLocationType
https://schema.org/jobLocationType.description: A description of the job location (e.g. TELECOMMUTE for telecommute jobs).

https://schema.org/Property.label: Property
https://schema.org/Property.description: A property, used to indicate attributes and relationships of some Thing; equivalent to rdf:Property.

https://schema.org/DietarySupplement.label: DietarySupplement
https://schema.org/DietarySupplement.description: A product taken by mouth that contains a dietary ingredient intended to supplement the diet. Dietary ingredients may include vitamins, minerals, herbs or other botanicals, amino acids, and substances such as enzymes, organ tissues, glandulars and metabolites.

https://schema.org/recipeCuisine.label: recipeCuisine
https://schema.org/recipeCuisine.description: The cuisine of the recipe (for example, French or Ethiopian).

https://schema.org/WearableSizeSystemEnu.label: WearableSizeSystemEnumeration
https://schema.org/WearableSizeSystemEnu.description: Enumerates common size systems specific for wearable products.

https://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.label: estimatesRiskOf
https://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.description: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.

https://schema.org/recognizingAuthority.label: recognizingAuthority
https://schema.org/recognizingAuthority.description: If applicable, the organization that officially recognizes this entity as part of its endorsed system of medicine.

https://schema.org/PodcastSeason.label: PodcastSeason
https://schema.org/PodcastSeason.description: A single season of a podcast. Many podcasts do not break down into separate seasons. In that case, PodcastSeries should be used.

https://schema.org/discountCode.label: discountCode
https://schema.org/discountCode.description: Code used to redeem a discount.

https://schema.org/MaximumDoseSchedule.label: MaximumDoseSchedule
https://schema.org/MaximumDoseSchedule.description: The maximum dosing schedule considered safe for a drug or supplement as recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

https://schema.org/hasSponsorshipOffer.label: hasSponsorshipOffer
https://schema.org/hasSponsorshipOffer.description: An offer to sponsor the event, for example, Sponsorship Prospectus, Sponsorship Opportunities, or Sponsor Packages.

https://schema.org/mpn.label: mpn
https://schema.org/mpn.description: The Manufacturer Part Number (MPN) of the product, or the product to which the offer refers.

https://schema.org/Play.label: Play
https://schema.org/Play.description: A play is a form of literature, usually consisting of dialogue between characters, intended for theatrical performance rather than just reading. Note: A performance of a Play would be a [[TheaterEvent]] or [[BroadcastEvent]] - the *Play* being the [[workPerformed]].

https://schema.org/PublicationEvent.label: PublicationEvent
https://schema.org/PublicationEvent.description: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type, e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

https://schema.org/coverageEndTime.label: coverageEndTime
https://schema.org/coverageEndTime.description: The time when the live blog will stop covering the Event. Note that coverage may continue after the Event concludes.

https://schema.org/warrantyScope.label: warrantyScope
https://schema.org/warrantyScope.description: The scope of the warranty promise.

https://schema.org/drugUnit.label: drugUnit
https://schema.org/drugUnit.description: The unit in which the drug is measured, e.g. '5 mg tablet'.

https://schema.org/greater.label: greater
https://schema.org/greater.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

https://schema.org/risks.label: risks
https://schema.org/risks.description: Specific physiologic risks associated to the diet plan.

https://schema.org/incentiveType.label: incentiveType
https://schema.org/incentiveType.description: The type of incentive offered (tax credit/rebate, tax deduction, tax waiver, subsidies, etc.).

https://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.label: arrivalBusStop
https://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.

https://schema.org/programPrerequisites.label: programPrerequisites
https://schema.org/programPrerequisites.description: Prerequisites for enrolling in the program.

https://schema.org/shippingOrigin.label: shippingOrigin
https://schema.org/shippingOrigin.description: Indicates the origin of a shipment, i.e. where it should be coming from.

https://schema.org/workLocation.label: workLocation
https://schema.org/workLocation.description: A contact location for a person's place of work.

https://schema.org/priceRange.label: priceRange
https://schema.org/priceRange.description: The price range of the business, for example ```$$$```.

https://schema.org/Message.label: Message
https://schema.org/Message.description: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

https://schema.org/predecessorOf.label: predecessorOf
https://schema.org/predecessorOf.description: A pointer from a previous, often discontinued variant of the product to its newer variant.

https://schema.org/InteractionCounter.label: InteractionCounter
https://schema.org/InteractionCounter.description: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

https://schema.org/BusOrCoach.label: BusOrCoach
https://schema.org/BusOrCoach.description: A bus (also omnibus or autobus) is a road vehicle designed to carry passengers. Coaches are luxury buses, usually in service for long distance travel.

https://schema.org/OccupationalTherapy.label: OccupationalTherapy
https://schema.org/OccupationalTherapy.description: A treatment of people with physical, emotional, or social problems, using purposeful activity to help them overcome or learn to deal with their problems.

https://schema.org/contactType.label: contactType
https://schema.org/contactType.description: A person or organization can have different contact points, for different purposes. For example, a sales contact point, a PR contact point and so on. This property is used to specify the kind of contact point.

https://schema.org/maps.label: maps
https://schema.org/maps.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/ClaimReview.label: ClaimReview
https://schema.org/ClaimReview.description: A fact-checking review of claims made (or reported) in some creative work (referenced via itemReviewed).

https://schema.org/CommunicateAction.label: CommunicateAction
https://schema.org/CommunicateAction.description: The act of conveying information to another person via a communication medium (instrument) such as speech, email, or telephone conversation.

https://schema.org/educationRequirements.label: educationRequirements
https://schema.org/educationRequirements.description: Educational background needed for the position or Occupation.

https://schema.org/MusicGroup.label: MusicGroup
https://schema.org/MusicGroup.description: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

https://schema.org/MusicAlbumReleaseType.label: MusicAlbumReleaseType
https://schema.org/MusicAlbumReleaseType.description: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

https://schema.org/MedicalTherapy.label: MedicalTherapy
https://schema.org/MedicalTherapy.description: Any medical intervention designed to prevent, treat, and cure human diseases and medical conditions, including both curative and palliative therapies. Medical therapies are typically processes of care relying upon pharmacotherapy, behavioral therapy, supportive therapy (with fluid or nutrition for example), or detoxification (e.g. hemodialysis) aimed at improving or preventing a health condition.

https://schema.org/competitor.label: competitor
https://schema.org/competitor.description: A competitor in a sports event.

https://schema.org/MerchantReturnPolicy.label: MerchantReturnPolicy
https://schema.org/MerchantReturnPolicy.description: A MerchantReturnPolicy provides information about product return policies associated with an [[Organization]], [[Product]], or [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/installUrl.label: installUrl
https://schema.org/installUrl.description: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.

https://schema.org/eligibleRegion.label: eligibleRegion
https://schema.org/eligibleRegion.description: The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is valid.\n\nSee also [[ineligibleRegion]].

https://schema.org/ratingCount.label: ratingCount
https://schema.org/ratingCount.description: The count of total number of ratings.

https://schema.org/BodyMeasurementTypeEn.label: BodyMeasurementTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/BodyMeasurementTypeEn.description: Enumerates types (or dimensions) of a person's body measurements, for example for fitting of clothes.

https://schema.org/gameItem.label: gameItem
https://schema.org/gameItem.description: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.

https://schema.org/ComputerLanguage.label: ComputerLanguage
https://schema.org/ComputerLanguage.description: This type covers computer programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, as well as other language-like computer representations. Natural languages are best represented with the [[Language]] type.

https://schema.org/description.label: description
https://schema.org/description.usage_hint: A description of the item - what the entity IS. NOT for quotes, events, or narrative facts about the entity.
https://schema.org/description.example_keywords: is described as, is a, definition, what it is

https://schema.org/creditedTo.label: creditedTo
https://schema.org/creditedTo.description: The group the release is credited to if different than the byArtist. For example, Red and Blue is credited to "Stefani Germanotta Band", but by Lady Gaga.

https://schema.org/legislationResponsibl.label: legislationResponsible
https://schema.org/legislationResponsibl.description: An individual or organization that has some kind of responsibility for the legislation. Typically the ministry who is/was in charge of elaborating the legislation, or the adressee for potential questions about the legislation once it is published.

https://schema.org/ratingValue.label: ratingValue
https://schema.org/ratingValue.description:
The rating for the content.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/stepValue.label: stepValue
https://schema.org/stepValue.description: The stepValue attribute indicates the granularity that is expected (and required) of the value in a PropertyValueSpecification.

https://schema.org/numItems.label: numItems
https://schema.org/numItems.description: Limits the number of items being shipped for which these conditions apply.

https://schema.org/InsertAction.label: InsertAction
https://schema.org/InsertAction.description: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

https://schema.org/incentives.label: incentives
https://schema.org/incentives.description: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.

https://schema.org/VoteAction.label: VoteAction
https://schema.org/VoteAction.description: The act of expressing a preference from a fixed/finite/structured set of choices/options.

https://schema.org/previousItem.label: previousItem
https://schema.org/previousItem.description: A link to the ListItem that precedes the current one.

https://schema.org/numberOfLoanPayments.label: numberOfLoanPayments
https://schema.org/numberOfLoanPayments.description: The number of payments contractually required at origination to repay the loan. For monthly paying loans this is the number of months from the contractual first payment date to the maturity date.

https://schema.org/frequency.label: frequency
https://schema.org/frequency.description: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.

https://schema.org/CableOrSatelliteServi.label: CableOrSatelliteService
https://schema.org/CableOrSatelliteServi.description: A service which provides access to media programming like TV or radio. Access may be via cable or satellite.

https://schema.org/partySize.label: partySize
https://schema.org/partySize.description: Number of people the reservation should accommodate.

https://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.label: includedRiskFactor
https://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.description: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.

https://schema.org/musicReleaseFormat.label: musicReleaseFormat
https://schema.org/musicReleaseFormat.description: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, i.e. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

https://schema.org/PerformingGroup.label: PerformingGroup
https://schema.org/PerformingGroup.description: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

https://schema.org/GameAvailabilityEnume.label: GameAvailabilityEnumeration
https://schema.org/GameAvailabilityEnume.description: For a [[VideoGame]], such as used with a [[PlayGameAction]], an enumeration of the kind of game availability offered.

https://schema.org/restPeriods.label: restPeriods
https://schema.org/restPeriods.description: How often one should break from the activity.

https://schema.org/BankAccount.label: BankAccount
https://schema.org/BankAccount.description: A product or service offered by a bank whereby one may deposit, withdraw or transfer money and in some cases be paid interest.

https://schema.org/RadiationTherapy.label: RadiationTherapy
https://schema.org/RadiationTherapy.description: A process of care using radiation aimed at improving a health condition.

https://schema.org/WinAction.label: WinAction
https://schema.org/WinAction.description: The act of achieving victory in a competitive activity.

https://schema.org/sdDatePublished.label: sdDatePublished
https://schema.org/sdDatePublished.description: Indicates the date on which the current structured data was generated / published. Typically used alongside [[sdPublisher]].

https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBedsOcc.label: cvdNumICUBedsOcc
https://schema.org/cvdNumICUBedsOcc.description: numicubedsocc - ICU BED OCCUPANCY: Total number of staffed inpatient ICU beds that are occupied.

https://schema.org/petsAllowed.label: petsAllowed
https://schema.org/petsAllowed.description: Indicates whether pets are allowed to enter the accommodation or lodging business. More detailed information can be put in a text value.

https://schema.org/requirements.label: requirements
https://schema.org/requirements.description: Component dependency requirements for application. This includes runtime environments and shared libraries that are not included in the application distribution package, but required to run the application (examples: DirectX, Java or .NET runtime).

https://schema.org/doseUnit.label: doseUnit
https://schema.org/doseUnit.description: The unit of the dose, e.g. 'mg'.

https://schema.org/engineDisplacement.label: engineDisplacement
https://schema.org/engineDisplacement.description:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement. 

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches
* Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueReference]] property.
* Note 2: You can use [[minValue]] and [[maxValue]] to indicate ranges.

https://schema.org/teaches.label: teaches
https://schema.org/teaches.description: The item being described is intended to help a person learn the competency or learning outcome defined by the referenced term.

https://schema.org/deliveryTime.label: deliveryTime
https://schema.org/deliveryTime.description: The total delay between the receipt of the order and the goods reaching the final customer.

https://schema.org/carbohydrateContent.label: carbohydrateContent
https://schema.org/carbohydrateContent.description: The number of grams of carbohydrates.

https://schema.org/hasMenu.label: hasMenu
https://schema.org/hasMenu.description: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.

https://schema.org/healthPlanId.label: healthPlanId
https://schema.org/healthPlanId.description: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)

https://schema.org/SendAction.label: SendAction
https://schema.org/SendAction.description:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination. Related actions:

* [[ReceiveAction]]: The reciprocal of SendAction.
* [[GiveAction]]: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

https://schema.org/reviewRating.label: reviewRating
https://schema.org/reviewRating.description: The rating given in this review. Note that reviews can themselves be rated. The ```reviewRating``` applies to rating given by the review. The [[aggregateRating]] property applies to the review itself, as a creative work.

https://schema.org/sportsTeam.label: sportsTeam
https://schema.org/sportsTeam.description: A sub property of participant. The sports team that participated on this action.

https://schema.org/Menu.label: Menu
https://schema.org/Menu.description: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.

https://schema.org/screenCount.label: screenCount
https://schema.org/screenCount.description: The number of screens in the movie theater.

https://schema.org/alcoholWarning.label: alcoholWarning
https://schema.org/alcoholWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.

https://schema.org/partOfSeries.label: partOfSeries
https://schema.org/partOfSeries.description: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

https://schema.org/businessDays.label: businessDays
https://schema.org/businessDays.description: Days of the week when the merchant typically operates, indicated via opening hours markup.

https://schema.org/dataset.label: dataset
https://schema.org/dataset.description: A dataset contained in this catalog.

https://schema.org/alumniOf.label: alumniOf
https://schema.org/alumniOf.description: An organization that the person is an alumni of.
https://schema.org/alumniOf.usage_hint: Schools/organizations someone attended as a student. Use OrganizationRole pattern if dates are needed.
https://schema.org/alumniOf.example_keywords: attended, studied at, graduated from, alumnus, student of, went to school

https://schema.org/numberOfItems.label: numberOfItems
https://schema.org/numberOfItems.description: The number of items in an ItemList. Note that some descriptions might not fully describe all items in a list (e.g., multi-page pagination); in such cases, the numberOfItems would be for the entire list.

https://schema.org/publishingPrinciples.label: publishingPrinciples
https://schema.org/publishingPrinciples.description:
The publishingPrinciples property indicates (typically via [[URL]]) a document describing the editorial principles of an [[Organization]] (or individual, e.g. a [[Person]] writing a blog) that relate to their activities as a publisher, e.g. ethics or diversity policies. When applied to a [[CreativeWork]] (e.g. [[NewsArticle]]) the principles are those of the party primarily responsible for the creation of the [[CreativeWork]].

While such policies are most typically expressed in natural language

https://schema.org/hasStore.label: hasStore
https://schema.org/hasStore.description: An eCommerce store part of an online marketplace.

https://schema.org/ResumeAction.label: ResumeAction
https://schema.org/ResumeAction.description: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

https://schema.org/UnRegisterAction.label: UnRegisterAction
https://schema.org/UnRegisterAction.description:
The act of un-registering from a service.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: antonym of UnRegisterAction.
* [[LeaveAction]]: Unlike LeaveAction, UnRegisterAction implies that you are unregistering from a service you were previously registered, rather than leaving a team/group of people.

https://schema.org/productionCompany.label: productionCompany
https://schema.org/productionCompany.description: The production company or studio responsible for the item, e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

https://schema.org/trackingUrl.label: trackingUrl
https://schema.org/trackingUrl.description: Tracking url for the parcel delivery.

https://schema.org/valueMaxLength.label: valueMaxLength
https://schema.org/valueMaxLength.description: Specifies the allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

https://schema.org/MedicalBusiness.label: MedicalBusiness
https://schema.org/MedicalBusiness.description: A particular physical or virtual business of an organization for medical purposes. Examples of MedicalBusiness include different businesses run by health professionals.

https://schema.org/Dataset.label: Dataset
https://schema.org/Dataset.description: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

https://schema.org/nerveMotor.label: nerveMotor
https://schema.org/nerveMotor.description: The neurological pathway extension that involves muscle control.

https://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.label: includedDataCatalog
https://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

https://schema.org/hasHealthAspect.label: hasHealthAspect
https://schema.org/hasHealthAspect.description: Indicates the aspect or aspects specifically addressed in some [[HealthTopicContent]]. For example, that the content is an overview, or that it talks about treatment, self-care, treatments or their side-effects.

https://schema.org/Gene.label: Gene
https://schema.org/Gene.description: A discrete unit of inheritance which affects one or more biological traits (Source: [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene)). Examples include FOXP2 (Forkhead box protein P2), SCARNA21 (small Cajal body-specific RNA 21), A- (agouti genotype).

https://schema.org/IgnoreAction.label: IgnoreAction
https://schema.org/IgnoreAction.description: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

https://schema.org/editor.label: editor
https://schema.org/editor.description: Specifies the Person who edited the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/exceptDate.label: exceptDate
https://schema.org/exceptDate.description:
Defines a [[Date]] or [[DateTime]] during which a scheduled [[Event]] will not take place. The property allows exceptions to
      a [[Schedule]] to be specified. If an exception is specified as a [[DateTime]] then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time
      should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a [[Date]] then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be
      excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to

https://schema.org/interactionType.label: interactionType
https://schema.org/interactionType.description: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use [[LikeAction]]. For down votes use [[DislikeAction]]. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.

https://schema.org/EatAction.label: EatAction
https://schema.org/EatAction.description: The act of swallowing solid objects.

https://schema.org/spatialCoverage.label: spatialCoverage
https://schema.org/spatialCoverage.description:
The spatialCoverage of a CreativeWork indicates the place(s) which are the focus of the content. It is a subproperty of
      contentLocation intended primarily for more technical and detailed materials. For example with a Dataset, it indicates
      areas that the dataset describes: a dataset of New York weather would have spatialCoverage which was the place: the state of New York.

https://schema.org/suggestedMeasurement.label: suggestedMeasurement
https://schema.org/suggestedMeasurement.description: A suggested range of body measurements for the intended audience or person, for example inseam between 32 and 34 inches or height between 170 and 190 cm. Typically found on a size chart for wearable products.

https://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.label: entertainmentBusiness
https://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.description: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.

https://schema.org/award.label: award
https://schema.org/award.description: An award won by or for this item.
https://schema.org/award.usage_hint: An award someone received. Use Role pattern if the award has a date: Person -> award -> Role -> award -> Award, with startDate on Role.
https://schema.org/award.example_keywords: received award, won, awarded, honored with, prize

https://schema.org/inChIKey.label: inChIKey
https://schema.org/inChIKey.description: InChIKey is a hashed version of the full InChI (using the SHA-256 algorithm).

https://schema.org/targetCollection.label: targetCollection
https://schema.org/targetCollection.description: A sub property of object. The collection target of the action.

https://schema.org/directors.label: directors
https://schema.org/directors.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video games etc. content. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/BoatTrip.label: BoatTrip
https://schema.org/BoatTrip.description: A trip on a commercial ferry line.

https://schema.org/ownershipFundingInfo.label: ownershipFundingInfo
https://schema.org/ownershipFundingInfo.description: For an [[Organization]] (often but not necessarily a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a description of organizational ownership structure; funding and grants. In a news/media setting, this is with particular reference to editorial independence.   Note that the [[funder]] is also available and can be used to make basic funder information machine-readable.

https://schema.org/doseSchedule.label: doseSchedule
https://schema.org/doseSchedule.description: A dosing schedule for the drug for a given population, either observed, recommended, or maximum dose based on the type used.

https://schema.org/mealService.label: mealService
https://schema.org/mealService.description: Description of the meals that will be provided or available for purchase.

https://schema.org/purchasePriceLimit.label: purchasePriceLimit
https://schema.org/purchasePriceLimit.description: Optional. The maximum price the item can have and still qualify for this offer.

https://schema.org/Residence.label: Residence
https://schema.org/Residence.description: The place where a person lives.

https://schema.org/usageInfo.label: usageInfo
https://schema.org/usageInfo.description: The schema.org [[usageInfo]] property indicates further information about a [[CreativeWork]]. This property is applicable both to works that are freely available and to those that require payment or other transactions. It can reference additional information, e.g. community expectations on preferred linking and citation conventions, as well as purchasing details. For something that can be commercially licensed, usageInfo can provide detailed, resource-specific information about licensing options

https://schema.org/Specialty.label: Specialty
https://schema.org/Specialty.description: Any branch of a field in which people typically develop specific expertise, usually after significant study, time, and effort.

https://schema.org/jobTitle.label: jobTitle
https://schema.org/jobTitle.description: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).

https://schema.org/Landform.label: Landform
https://schema.org/Landform.description: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

https://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.label: infectiousAgentClass
https://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.description: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.

https://schema.org/replyToUrl.label: replyToUrl
https://schema.org/replyToUrl.description: The URL at which a reply may be posted to the specified UserComment.

https://schema.org/floorLevel.label: floorLevel
https://schema.org/floorLevel.description:
The floor level for an [[Accommodation]] in a multi-storey building. Since counting
  systems [vary internationally](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey#Consecutive_number_floor_designations), the local system should be used where possible.

https://schema.org/sportsEvent.label: sportsEvent
https://schema.org/sportsEvent.description: A sub property of location. The sports event where this action occurred.

https://schema.org/taxID.label: taxID
https://schema.org/taxID.description: The Tax / Fiscal ID of the organization or person, e.g. the TIN in the US or the CIF/NIF in Spain.

https://schema.org/followee.label: followee
https://schema.org/followee.description: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

https://schema.org/ArchiveOrganization.label: ArchiveOrganization
https://schema.org/ArchiveOrganization.description: An organization with archival holdings. An organization which keeps and preserves archival material and typically makes it accessible to the public.

https://schema.org/application.label: application
https://schema.org/application.description: An application that can complete the request.

https://schema.org/dateSent.label: dateSent
https://schema.org/dateSent.description: The date/time at which the message was sent.

https://schema.org/DrugCostCategory.label: DrugCostCategory
https://schema.org/DrugCostCategory.description: Enumerated categories of medical drug costs.

https://schema.org/overdosage.label: overdosage
https://schema.org/overdosage.description: Any information related to overdose on a drug, including signs or symptoms, treatments, contact information for emergency response.

https://schema.org/monthlyMinimumRepayme.label: monthlyMinimumRepaymentAmount
https://schema.org/monthlyMinimumRepayme.description: The minimum payment is the lowest amount of money that one is required to pay on a credit card statement each month.

https://schema.org/Hostel.label: Hostel
https://schema.org/Hostel.description:
A hostel - cheap accommodation, often in shared dormitories.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/AnatomicalSystem.label: AnatomicalSystem
https://schema.org/AnatomicalSystem.description: An anatomical system is a group of anatomical structures that work together to perform a certain task. Anatomical systems, such as organ systems, are one organizing principle of anatomy, and can include circulatory, digestive, endocrine, integumentary, immune, lymphatic, muscular, nervous, reproductive, respiratory, skeletal, urinary, vestibular, and other systems.

https://schema.org/Motorcycle.label: Motorcycle
https://schema.org/Motorcycle.description: A motorcycle or motorbike is a single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.

https://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.label: isAccessibleForFree
https://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

https://schema.org/ParcelDelivery.label: ParcelDelivery
https://schema.org/ParcelDelivery.description: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

https://schema.org/about.label: about
https://schema.org/about.description: The subject matter of an object.
https://schema.org/about.usage_hint: The subject matter of a CreativeWork.
https://schema.org/about.example_keywords: about, concerning, regarding, subject matter, topic

https://schema.org/endTime.label: endTime
https://schema.org/endTime.description: The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. E.g. John wrote a book from January to *December*. For media, including audio and video, it's the time offset of the end of a clip within a larger file.\n\nNote that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified i

https://schema.org/numConstraints.label: numConstraints
https://schema.org/numConstraints.description: Indicates the number of constraints property values defined for a particular [[ConstraintNode]] such as [[StatisticalVariable]]. This helps applications understand if they have access to a sufficiently complete description of a [[StatisticalVariable]] or other construct that is defined using properties on template-style nodes.

https://schema.org/BookFormatType.label: BookFormatType
https://schema.org/BookFormatType.description: The publication format of the book.

https://schema.org/EventStatusType.label: EventStatusType
https://schema.org/EventStatusType.description: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

https://schema.org/activeIngredient.label: activeIngredient
https://schema.org/activeIngredient.description: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.

https://schema.org/hostingOrganization.label: hostingOrganization
https://schema.org/hostingOrganization.description: The Organization (airline, travelers' club, retailer, etc.) the membership is made with or which offers the  MemberProgram.

https://schema.org/clinicalPharmacology.label: clinicalPharmacology
https://schema.org/clinicalPharmacology.description: Description of the absorption and elimination of drugs, including their concentration (pharmacokinetics, pK) and biological effects (pharmacodynamics, pD).

https://schema.org/numberOfBedrooms.label: numberOfBedrooms
https://schema.org/numberOfBedrooms.description: The total integer number of bedrooms in a some [[Accommodation]], [[ApartmentComplex]] or [[FloorPlan]].

https://schema.org/discussionUrl.label: discussionUrl
https://schema.org/discussionUrl.description: A link to the page containing the comments of the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/MedicalDevice.label: MedicalDevice
https://schema.org/MedicalDevice.description: Any object used in a medical capacity, such as to diagnose or treat a patient.

https://schema.org/numberOfPlayers.label: numberOfPlayers
https://schema.org/numberOfPlayers.description: Indicate how many people can play this game (minimum, maximum, or range).

https://schema.org/inSupportOf.label: inSupportOf
https://schema.org/inSupportOf.description: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.

https://schema.org/ProfessionalService.label: ProfessionalService
https://schema.org/ProfessionalService.description:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."\n\nThe general [[ProfessionalService]] type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with [[Service]]. For reference, the types that it included were: [[Dentist]],
        [[AccountingService]], [[Attorney]], [[Notary]], as well as types for several kinds of [[HomeAndConstructionBusiness]]: [[Electrician]], [[GeneralContractor]],
        [[HousePainter]], [[Locksmith]], [[Plumber]], [[RoofingContractor]]. [[LegalService]] was

https://schema.org/PhotographAction.label: PhotographAction
https://schema.org/PhotographAction.description: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

https://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.label: encodesCreativeWork
https://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.description: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.

https://schema.org/TVEpisode.label: TVEpisode
https://schema.org/TVEpisode.description: A TV episode which can be part of a series or season.

https://schema.org/model.label: model
https://schema.org/model.description: The model of the product. Use with the URL of a ProductModel or a textual representation of the model identifier. The URL of the ProductModel can be from an external source. It is recommended to additionally provide strong product identifiers via the gtin8/gtin13/gtin14 and mpn properties.

https://schema.org/beforeMedia.label: beforeMedia
https://schema.org/beforeMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.

https://schema.org/partOfEpisode.label: partOfEpisode
https://schema.org/partOfEpisode.description: The episode to which this clip belongs.

https://schema.org/athlete.label: athlete
https://schema.org/athlete.description: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.

https://schema.org/pagination.label: pagination
https://schema.org/pagination.description: Any description of pages that is not separated into pageStart and pageEnd; for example, "1-6, 9, 55" or "10-12, 46-49".

https://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.label: hasCategoryCode
https://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.description: A Category code contained in this code set.
