https://schema.org/ConstraintNode.label: ConstraintNode
https://schema.org/ConstraintNode.description:
The ConstraintNode type is provided to support usecases in which a node in a structured data graph is described with properties which appear to describe a single entity, but are being used in a situation where they serve a more abstract purpose. A [[ConstraintNode]] can be described using [[constraintProperty]] and [[numConstraints]]. These constraint properties can serve a
    variety of purposes, and their values may sometimes be understood to indicate sets of possible values rather than singl

https://schema.org/biologicalRole.label: biologicalRole
https://schema.org/biologicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.

https://schema.org/RefundTypeEnumeration.label: RefundTypeEnumeration
https://schema.org/RefundTypeEnumeration.description: Enumerates several kinds of product return refund types.

https://schema.org/ApprovedIndication.label: ApprovedIndication
https://schema.org/ApprovedIndication.description: An indication for a medical therapy that has been formally specified or approved by a regulatory body that regulates use of the therapy; for example, the US FDA approves indications for most drugs in the US.

https://schema.org/ReplyAction.label: ReplyAction
https://schema.org/ReplyAction.description:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to [[AskAction]].

Related actions:

* [[AskAction]]: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

https://schema.org/ServiceChannel.label: ServiceChannel
https://schema.org/ServiceChannel.description: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

https://schema.org/DoseSchedule.label: DoseSchedule
https://schema.org/DoseSchedule.description: A specific dosing schedule for a drug or supplement.

https://schema.org/duplicateTherapy.label: duplicateTherapy
https://schema.org/duplicateTherapy.description: A therapy that duplicates or overlaps this one.

https://schema.org/InfectiousAgentClass.label: InfectiousAgentClass
https://schema.org/InfectiousAgentClass.description: Classes of agents or pathogens that transmit infectious diseases. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/screenshot.label: screenshot
https://schema.org/screenshot.description: A link to a screenshot image of the app.

https://schema.org/certificationIdentifi.label: certificationIdentification
https://schema.org/certificationIdentifi.description: Identifier of a certification instance (as registered with an independent certification body). Typically this identifier can be used to consult and verify the certification instance. See also [gs1:certificationIdentification](https://www.gs1.org/voc/certificationIdentification).

https://schema.org/LegalService.label: LegalService
https://schema.org/LegalService.description: A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

https://schema.org/VideoGame.label: VideoGame
https://schema.org/VideoGame.description: A video game is an electronic game that involves human interaction with a user interface to generate visual feedback on a video device.

https://schema.org/warrantyPromise.label: warrantyPromise
https://schema.org/warrantyPromise.description: The warranty promise(s) included in the offer.

https://schema.org/subReservation.label: subReservation
https://schema.org/subReservation.description: The individual reservations included in the package. Typically a repeated property.

https://schema.org/familyName.label: familyName
https://schema.org/familyName.description: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

https://schema.org/MedicalDevicePurpose.label: MedicalDevicePurpose
https://schema.org/MedicalDevicePurpose.description: Categories of medical devices, organized by the purpose or intended use of the device.

https://schema.org/RentalCarReservation.label: RentalCarReservation
https://schema.org/RentalCarReservation.description: A reservation for a rental car.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

https://schema.org/additionalVariable.label: additionalVariable
https://schema.org/additionalVariable.description: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.

https://schema.org/supplyTo.label: supplyTo
https://schema.org/supplyTo.description: The area to which the artery supplies blood.

https://schema.org/Role.label: Role
https://schema.org/Role.description: Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/06/16/intr
https://schema.org/Role.usage_hint: Use as an intermediate node to add qualifiers (dates, role name) to a relationship. Pattern: subject -> property -> Role -> property -> object, with dates on the Role.
https://schema.org/Role.example_keywords: role, position, capacity, function, qualified relationship, temporal relationship

https://schema.org/billingIncrement.label: billingIncrement
https://schema.org/billingIncrement.description: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

https://schema.org/diversityPolicy.label: diversityPolicy
https://schema.org/diversityPolicy.description: Statement on diversity policy by an [[Organization]] e.g. a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]. For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a statement describing the newsroom’s diversity policy on both staffing and sources, typically providing staffing data.

https://schema.org/PhysicalActivityCateg.label: PhysicalActivityCategory
https://schema.org/PhysicalActivityCateg.description: Categories of physical activity, organized by physiologic classification.

https://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.label: countryOfOrigin
https://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.description:
The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative  works such as movie and TV content.

In the case of TV and movie, this would be the country of the principle offices of the production company or individual responsible for the movie. For other kinds of [[CreativeWork]] it is difficult to provide fully general guidance, and properties such as [[contentLocation]] and [[locationCreated]] may be more applicable.

In the case of products, the country of origin of the product

https://schema.org/Mountain.label: Mountain
https://schema.org/Mountain.description: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

https://schema.org/articleBody.label: articleBody
https://schema.org/articleBody.description: The actual body of the article.

https://schema.org/availabilityStarts.label: availabilityStarts
https://schema.org/availabilityStarts.description: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

https://schema.org/deliveryStatus.label: deliveryStatus
https://schema.org/deliveryStatus.description: New entry added as the package passes through each leg of its journey (from shipment to final delivery).

https://schema.org/hasCredential.label: hasCredential
https://schema.org/hasCredential.description: A credential awarded to the Person or Organization.

https://schema.org/paymentMethodId.label: paymentMethodId
https://schema.org/paymentMethodId.description: An identifier for the method of payment used (e.g. the last 4 digits of the credit card).

https://schema.org/UserReview.label: UserReview
https://schema.org/UserReview.description: A review created by an end-user (e.g. consumer, purchaser, attendee etc.), in contrast with [[CriticReview]].

https://schema.org/significantLinks.label: significantLinks
https://schema.org/significantLinks.description: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.

https://schema.org/artEdition.label: artEdition
https://schema.org/artEdition.description: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").

https://schema.org/causeOf.label: causeOf
https://schema.org/causeOf.description: The condition, complication, symptom, sign, etc. caused.

https://schema.org/State.label: State
https://schema.org/State.description: A state or province of a country.

https://schema.org/isAvailableGenericall.label: isAvailableGenerically
https://schema.org/isAvailableGenericall.description: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).

https://schema.org/parentItem.label: parentItem
https://schema.org/parentItem.description: The parent of a question, answer or item in general. Typically used for Q/A discussion threads e.g. a chain of comments with the first comment being an [[Article]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. See also [[comment]] which points from something to a comment about it.

https://schema.org/encodingType.label: encodingType
https://schema.org/encodingType.description: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.

https://schema.org/GeoCircle.label: GeoCircle
https://schema.org/GeoCircle.description:
A GeoCircle is a GeoShape representing a circular geographic area. As it is a GeoShape
          it provides the simple textual property 'circle', but also allows the combination of postalCode alongside geoRadius.
          The center of the circle can be indicated via the 'geoMidpoint' property, or more approximately using 'address', 'postalCode'.

https://schema.org/sponsor.label: sponsor
https://schema.org/sponsor.description: A person or organization that supports a thing through a pledge, promise, or financial contribution. E.g. a sponsor of a Medical Study or a corporate sponsor of an event.

https://schema.org/downloadUrl.label: downloadUrl
https://schema.org/downloadUrl.description: If the file can be downloaded, URL to download the binary.

https://schema.org/valueMinLength.label: valueMinLength
https://schema.org/valueMinLength.description: Specifies the minimum allowed range for number of characters in a literal value.

https://schema.org/coach.label: coach
https://schema.org/coach.description: A person that acts in a coaching role for a sports team.

https://schema.org/performerIn.label: performerIn
https://schema.org/performerIn.description: Event that this person is a performer or participant in.

https://schema.org/isConsumableFor.label: isConsumableFor
https://schema.org/isConsumableFor.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.

https://schema.org/maximumPhysicalAttend.label: maximumPhysicalAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumPhysicalAttend.description: The maximum physical attendee capacity of an [[Event]] whose [[eventAttendanceMode]] is [[OfflineEventAttendanceMode]] (or the offline aspects, in the case of a [[MixedEventAttendanceMode]]).

https://schema.org/Poster.label: Poster
https://schema.org/Poster.description: A large, usually printed placard, bill, or announcement, often illustrated, that is posted to advertise or publicize something.

https://schema.org/agentInteractionStati.label: agentInteractionStatistic
https://schema.org/agentInteractionStati.description: The number of completed interactions for this entity, in a particular role (the 'agent'), in a particular action (indicated in the statistic), and in a particular context (i.e. interactionService).

https://schema.org/Quantity.label: Quantity
https://schema.org/Quantity.description: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 kg' or '4 milligrams'.

https://schema.org/masthead.label: masthead
https://schema.org/masthead.description: For a [[NewsMediaOrganization]], a link to the masthead page or a page listing top editorial management.

https://schema.org/bccRecipient.label: bccRecipient
https://schema.org/bccRecipient.description: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.

https://schema.org/Mass.label: Mass
https://schema.org/Mass.description: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

https://schema.org/dataFeedElement.label: dataFeedElement
https://schema.org/dataFeedElement.description: An item within a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

https://schema.org/billingStart.label: billingStart
https://schema.org/billingStart.description: Specifies after how much time this price (or price component) becomes valid and billing starts. Can be used, for example, to model a price increase after the first year of a subscription. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.

https://schema.org/primaryPrevention.label: primaryPrevention
https://schema.org/primaryPrevention.description: A preventative therapy used to prevent an initial occurrence of the medical condition, such as vaccination.

https://schema.org/serviceOperator.label: serviceOperator
https://schema.org/serviceOperator.description: The operating organization, if different from the provider.  This enables the representation of services that are provided by an organization, but operated by another organization like a subcontractor.

https://schema.org/includedComposition.label: includedComposition
https://schema.org/includedComposition.description: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).

https://schema.org/MolecularEntity.label: MolecularEntity
https://schema.org/MolecularEntity.description: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

https://schema.org/Invoice.label: Invoice
https://schema.org/Invoice.description: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

https://schema.org/recipeCategory.label: recipeCategory
https://schema.org/recipeCategory.description: The category of the recipe—for example, appetizer, entree, etc.

https://schema.org/geoWithin.label: geoWithin
https://schema.org/geoWithin.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/givenName.label: givenName
https://schema.org/givenName.description: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

https://schema.org/branchCode.label: branchCode
https://schema.org/branchCode.description: A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.\n\nFor example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.

https://schema.org/borrower.label: borrower
https://schema.org/borrower.description: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.

https://schema.org/WriteAction.label: WriteAction
https://schema.org/WriteAction.description: The act of authoring written creative content.

https://schema.org/subTest.label: subTest
https://schema.org/subTest.description: A component test of the panel.

https://schema.org/musicalKey.label: musicalKey
https://schema.org/musicalKey.description: The key, mode, or scale this composition uses.

https://schema.org/error.label: error
https://schema.org/error.description: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure. Consider using the Error type.

https://schema.org/startOffset.label: startOffset
https://schema.org/startOffset.description: The start time of the clip expressed as the number of seconds from the beginning of the work.

https://schema.org/cvdFacilityId.label: cvdFacilityId
https://schema.org/cvdFacilityId.description: Identifier of the NHSN facility that this data record applies to. Use [[cvdFacilityCounty]] to indicate the county. To provide other details, [[healthcareReportingData]] can be used on a [[Hospital]] entry.

https://schema.org/partOfTrip.label: partOfTrip
https://schema.org/partOfTrip.description: Identifies that this [[Trip]] is a subTrip of another Trip.  For example Day 1, Day 2, etc. of a multi-day trip.

https://schema.org/geoCoveredBy.label: geoCoveredBy
https://schema.org/geoCoveredBy.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/abridged.label: abridged
https://schema.org/abridged.description: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.

https://schema.org/lastReviewed.label: lastReviewed
https://schema.org/lastReviewed.description: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.

https://schema.org/cvdNumBeds.label: cvdNumBeds
https://schema.org/cvdNumBeds.description: numbeds - HOSPITAL INPATIENT BEDS: Inpatient beds, including all staffed, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients.

https://schema.org/worksFor.label: worksFor
https://schema.org/worksFor.description: Organizations that the person works for.
https://schema.org/worksFor.usage_hint: Organization someone works/worked for. Use OrganizationRole pattern for employment with dates.
https://schema.org/worksFor.example_keywords: works for, employed by, job at, position at, worked at

https://schema.org/CarUsageType.label: CarUsageType
https://schema.org/CarUsageType.description: A value indicating a special usage of a car, e.g. commercial rental, driving school, or as a taxi.

https://schema.org/specialty.label: specialty
https://schema.org/specialty.description: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.

https://schema.org/interactivityType.label: interactivityType
https://schema.org/interactivityType.description: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.

https://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.label: includedInDataCatalog
https://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.description: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

https://schema.org/VideoGameClip.label: VideoGameClip
https://schema.org/VideoGameClip.description: A short segment/part of a video game.

https://schema.org/DownloadAction.label: DownloadAction
https://schema.org/DownloadAction.description: The act of downloading an object.

https://schema.org/numberedPosition.label: numberedPosition
https://schema.org/numberedPosition.description: A number associated with a role in an organization, for example, the number on an athlete's jersey.

https://schema.org/ImageGallery.label: ImageGallery
https://schema.org/ImageGallery.description: Web page type: Image gallery page.

https://schema.org/maximumAttendeeCapaci.label: maximumAttendeeCapacity
https://schema.org/maximumAttendeeCapaci.description: The total number of individuals that may attend an event or venue.

https://schema.org/guideline.label: guideline
https://schema.org/guideline.description: A medical guideline related to this entity.

https://schema.org/UserCheckins.label: UserCheckins
https://schema.org/UserCheckins.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/associatedPathophysio.label: associatedPathophysiology
https://schema.org/associatedPathophysio.description: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.

https://schema.org/lesser.label: lesser
https://schema.org/lesser.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

https://schema.org/EngineSpecification.label: EngineSpecification
https://schema.org/EngineSpecification.description: Information about the engine of the vehicle. A vehicle can have multiple engines represented by multiple engine specification entities.

https://schema.org/returnPolicyCountry.label: returnPolicyCountry
https://schema.org/returnPolicyCountry.description: The country where the product has to be sent to for returns, for example "Ireland" using the [[name]] property of [[Country]]. You can also provide the two-letter [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-1). Note that this can be different from the country where the product was originally shipped from or sent to.

https://schema.org/translator.label: translator
https://schema.org/translator.description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.

https://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVo.label: eligibleTransactionVolume
https://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVo.description: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.

https://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.label: healthPlanDrugTier
https://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.description: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.

https://schema.org/DigitalDocumentPermis.label: DigitalDocumentPermissionType
https://schema.org/DigitalDocumentPermis.description: A type of permission which can be granted for accessing a digital document.

https://schema.org/creditText.label: creditText
https://schema.org/creditText.description: Text that can be used to credit person(s) and/or organization(s) associated with a published Creative Work.

https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorColor.label: vehicleInteriorColor
https://schema.org/vehicleInteriorColor.description: The color or color combination of the interior of the vehicle.

https://schema.org/Suite.label: Suite
https://schema.org/Suite.description:
A suite in a hotel or other public accommodation, denotes a class of luxury accommodations, the key feature of which is multiple rooms (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suite_(hotel)).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/TelevisionChannel.label: TelevisionChannel
https://schema.org/TelevisionChannel.description: A unique instance of a television BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

https://schema.org/ResearchOrganization.label: ResearchOrganization
https://schema.org/ResearchOrganization.description: A Research Organization (e.g. scientific institute, research company).

https://schema.org/taxonomicRange.label: taxonomicRange
https://schema.org/taxonomicRange.description: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in some way related to the BioChemEntity.

https://schema.org/location.label: location
https://schema.org/location.description: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

https://schema.org/legislationAmends.label: legislationAmends
https://schema.org/legislationAmends.description: Another legislation that this legislation amends, introducing legal changes.

https://schema.org/inCodeSet.label: inCodeSet
https://schema.org/inCodeSet.description: A [[CategoryCodeSet]] that contains this category code.

https://schema.org/CheckInAction.label: CheckInAction
https://schema.org/CheckInAction.description:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check-in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).

Related actions:

* [[CheckOutAction]]: The antonym of CheckInAction.
* [[ArriveAction]]: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
* [[ConfirmAction]]: Unlike

https://schema.org/MedicalCause.label: MedicalCause
https://schema.org/MedicalCause.description: The causative agent(s) that are responsible for the pathophysiologic process that eventually results in a medical condition, symptom or sign. In this schema, unless otherwise specified this is meant to be the proximate cause of the medical condition, symptom or sign. The proximate cause is defined as the causative agent that most directly results in the medical condition, symptom or sign. For example, the HIV virus could be considered a cause of AIDS. Or in a diagnostic context, if a patient fel

https://schema.org/timeOfDay.label: timeOfDay
https://schema.org/timeOfDay.description: The time of day the program normally runs. For example, "evenings".

https://schema.org/messageAttachment.label: messageAttachment
https://schema.org/messageAttachment.description: A CreativeWork attached to the message.

https://schema.org/BusinessFunction.label: BusinessFunction
https://schema.org/BusinessFunction.description:
The business function specifies the type of activity or access (i.e., the bundle of rights) offered by the organization or business person through the offer. Typical are sell, rental or lease, maintenance or repair, manufacture / produce, recycle / dispose, engineering / construction, or installation. Proprietary specifications of access rights are also instances of this class.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ConstructionInstallation
* http://purl.org/goodrelation

https://schema.org/SellAction.label: SellAction
https://schema.org/SellAction.description: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

https://schema.org/Blog.label: Blog
https://schema.org/Blog.description: A [blog](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blog), sometimes known as a "weblog". Note that the individual posts ([[BlogPosting]]s) in a [[Blog]] are often colloquially referred to by the same term.

https://schema.org/offersPrescriptionByM.label: offersPrescriptionByMail
https://schema.org/offersPrescriptionByM.description: Whether prescriptions can be delivered by mail.

https://schema.org/DriveWheelConfigurati.label: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
https://schema.org/DriveWheelConfigurati.description: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

https://schema.org/letterer.label: letterer
https://schema.org/letterer.description: The individual who adds lettering, including speech balloons and sound effects, to artwork.

https://schema.org/actors.label: actors
https://schema.org/actors.description: An actor, e.g. in TV, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/availableTest.label: availableTest
https://schema.org/availableTest.description: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.

https://schema.org/seeks.label: seeks
https://schema.org/seeks.description: A pointer to products or services sought by the organization or person (demand).

https://schema.org/legislationDate.label: legislationDate
https://schema.org/legislationDate.description: The date of adoption or signature of the legislation. This is the date at which the text is officially aknowledged to be a legislation, even though it might not even be published or in force.

https://schema.org/serviceLocation.label: serviceLocation
https://schema.org/serviceLocation.description: The location (e.g. civic structure, local business, etc.) where a person can go to access the service.

https://schema.org/applicationSubCategor.label: applicationSubCategory
https://schema.org/applicationSubCategor.description: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.

https://schema.org/numberOfPages.label: numberOfPages
https://schema.org/numberOfPages.description: The number of pages in the book.

https://schema.org/mapType.label: mapType
https://schema.org/mapType.description: Indicates the kind of Map, from the MapCategoryType Enumeration.

https://schema.org/CDCPMDRecord.label: CDCPMDRecord
https://schema.org/CDCPMDRecord.description:
A CDCPMDRecord is a data structure representing a record in a CDC tabular data format
      used for hospital data reporting. See [documentation](/docs/cdc-covid.html) for details, and the linked CDC materials for authoritative
      definitions used as the source here.

https://schema.org/MedicalRiskCalculator.label: MedicalRiskCalculator
https://schema.org/MedicalRiskCalculator.description: A complex mathematical calculation requiring an online calculator, used to assess prognosis. Note: use the url property of Thing to record any URLs for online calculators.

https://schema.org/ratingExplanation.label: ratingExplanation
https://schema.org/ratingExplanation.description: A short explanation (e.g. one to two sentences) providing background context and other information that led to the conclusion expressed in the rating. This is particularly applicable to ratings associated with "fact check" markup using [[ClaimReview]].

https://schema.org/HowToTip.label: HowToTip
https://schema.org/HowToTip.description: An explanation in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It provides supplementary information about a technique, supply, author's preference, etc. It can explain what could be done, or what should not be done, but doesn't specify what should be done (see HowToDirection).

https://schema.org/contributor.label: contributor
https://schema.org/contributor.description: A secondary contributor to the CreativeWork or Event.

https://schema.org/paymentDueDate.label: paymentDueDate
https://schema.org/paymentDueDate.description: The date that payment is due.

https://schema.org/Recommendation.label: Recommendation
https://schema.org/Recommendation.description: [[Recommendation]] is a type of [[Review]] that suggests or proposes something as the best option or best course of action. Recommendations may be for products or services, or other concrete things, as in the case of a ranked list or product guide. A [[Guide]] may list multiple recommendations for different categories. For example, in a [[Guide]] about which TVs to buy, the author may have several [[Recommendation]]s.

https://schema.org/translationOfWork.label: translationOfWork
https://schema.org/translationOfWork.description: The work that this work has been translated from. E.g. 物种起源 is a translationOf “On the Origin of Species”.

https://schema.org/winner.label: winner
https://schema.org/winner.description: A sub property of participant. The winner of the action.

https://schema.org/utterances.label: utterances
https://schema.org/utterances.description: Text of an utterances (spoken words, lyrics etc.) that occurs at a certain section of a media object, represented as a [[HyperTocEntry]].

https://schema.org/MedicalCode.label: MedicalCode
https://schema.org/MedicalCode.description: A code for a medical entity.

https://schema.org/LinkRole.label: LinkRole
https://schema.org/LinkRole.description: A Role that represents a Web link, e.g. as expressed via the 'url' property. Its linkRelationship property can indicate URL-based and plain textual link types, e.g. those in IANA link registry or others such as 'amphtml'. This structure provides a placeholder where details from HTML's link element can be represented outside of HTML, e.g. in JSON-LD feeds.

https://schema.org/loanType.label: loanType
https://schema.org/loanType.description: The type of a loan or credit.

https://schema.org/passengerSequenceNumb.label: passengerSequenceNumber
https://schema.org/passengerSequenceNumb.description: The passenger's sequence number as assigned by the airline.

https://schema.org/makesOffer.label: makesOffer
https://schema.org/makesOffer.description: A pointer to products or services offered by the organization or person.

https://schema.org/applicationSuite.label: applicationSuite
https://schema.org/applicationSuite.description: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).

https://schema.org/alternativeOf.label: alternativeOf
https://schema.org/alternativeOf.description: Another gene which is a variation of this one.

https://schema.org/PurchaseType.label: PurchaseType
https://schema.org/PurchaseType.description: Enumerates a purchase type for an item.

https://schema.org/WorkersUnion.label: WorkersUnion
https://schema.org/WorkersUnion.description: A Workers Union (also known as a Labor Union, Labour Union, or Trade Union) is an organization that promotes the interests of its worker members by collectively bargaining with management, organizing, and political lobbying.

https://schema.org/enginePower.label: enginePower
https://schema.org/enginePower.description:
The power of the vehicle's engine.
    Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

* Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see  [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine\_power\_test\_codes](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Engine_power_test_codes).
* Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the [[valueRefer

https://schema.org/verificationFactCheck.label: verificationFactCheckingPolicy
https://schema.org/verificationFactCheck.description: Disclosure about verification and fact-checking processes for a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] or other fact-checking [[Organization]].

https://schema.org/productGroupID.label: productGroupID
https://schema.org/productGroupID.description: Indicates a textual identifier for a ProductGroup.

https://schema.org/legislationApplies.label: legislationApplies
https://schema.org/legislationApplies.description: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) somehow transfers another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the legislationTransposes property. For example an informative consolidated law of a European Union's member state "applies" the consolidated version of the European Directive implemented in it.

https://schema.org/observationPeriod.label: observationPeriod
https://schema.org/observationPeriod.description: The length of time an Observation took place over. The format follows `P[0-9]*[Y|M|D|h|m|s]`. For example, P1Y is Period 1 Year, P3M is Period 3 Months, P3h is Period 3 hours.

https://schema.org/inPlaylist.label: inPlaylist
https://schema.org/inPlaylist.description: The playlist to which this recording belongs.

https://schema.org/map.label: map
https://schema.org/map.description: A URL to a map of the place.

https://schema.org/vatID.label: vatID
https://schema.org/vatID.description: The Value-added Tax ID of the organization or person.

https://schema.org/BusinessEntityType.label: BusinessEntityType
https://schema.org/BusinessEntityType.description:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

https://schema.org/valueRequired.label: valueRequired
https://schema.org/valueRequired.description: Whether the property must be filled in to complete the action.  Default is false.

https://schema.org/associatedMedia.label: associatedMedia
https://schema.org/associatedMedia.description: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.

https://schema.org/participant.label: participant
https://schema.org/participant.description: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. E.g. John wrote a book with *Steve*.

https://schema.org/discountCurrency.label: discountCurrency
https://schema.org/discountCurrency.description: The currency of the discount.\n\nUse standard formats: [ISO 4217 currency format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217), e.g. "USD"; [Ticker symbol](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_cryptocurrencies) for cryptocurrencies, e.g. "BTC"; well known names for [Local Exchange Trading Systems](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Local_exchange_trading_system) (LETS) and other currency types, e.g. "Ithaca HOUR".

https://schema.org/maximumIntake.label: maximumIntake
https://schema.org/maximumIntake.description: Recommended intake of this supplement for a given population as defined by a specific recommending authority.

https://schema.org/datePosted.label: datePosted
https://schema.org/datePosted.description: Publication date of an online listing.

https://schema.org/originatesFrom.label: originatesFrom
https://schema.org/originatesFrom.description: The vasculature the lymphatic structure originates, or afferents, from.

https://schema.org/permissions.label: permissions
https://schema.org/permissions.description: Permission(s) required to run the app (for example, a mobile app may require full internet access or may run only on wifi).

https://schema.org/molecularWeight.label: molecularWeight
https://schema.org/molecularWeight.description: This is the molecular weight of the entity being described, not of the parent. Units should be included in the form '<Number> <unit>', for example '12 amu' or as '<QuantitativeValue>.

https://schema.org/nonProprietaryName.label: nonProprietaryName
https://schema.org/nonProprietaryName.description: The generic name of this drug or supplement.

https://schema.org/pattern.label: pattern
https://schema.org/pattern.description: A pattern that something has, for example 'polka dot', 'striped', 'Canadian flag'. Values are typically expressed as text, although links to controlled value schemes are also supported.

https://schema.org/asin.label: asin
https://schema.org/asin.description:
An Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN) is a 10-character alphanumeric unique identifier assigned by Amazon.com and its partners for product identification within the Amazon organization (summary from [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amazon_Standard_Identification_Number)'s article).

Note also that this is a definition for how to include ASINs in Schema.org data, and not a definition of ASINs in general - see documentation from Amazon for authoritative details.
ASINs are most c

https://schema.org/gamePlatform.label: gamePlatform
https://schema.org/gamePlatform.description: The electronic systems used to play video games.

https://schema.org/MedicalProcedure.label: MedicalProcedure
https://schema.org/MedicalProcedure.description: A process of care used in either a diagnostic, therapeutic, preventive or palliative capacity that relies on invasive (surgical), non-invasive, or other techniques.

https://schema.org/directApply.label: directApply
https://schema.org/directApply.description: Indicates whether an [[url]] that is associated with a [[JobPosting]] enables direct application for the job, via the posting website. A job posting is considered to have directApply of [[True]] if an application process for the specified job can be directly initiated via the url(s) given (noting that e.g. multiple internet domains might nevertheless be involved at an implementation level). A value of [[False]] is appropriate if there is no clear path to applying directly online for the specifie

https://schema.org/PhysicalExam.label: PhysicalExam
https://schema.org/PhysicalExam.description: A type of physical examination of a patient performed by a physician.

https://schema.org/educationalAlignment.label: educationalAlignment
https://schema.org/educationalAlignment.description:
An alignment to an established educational framework.

This property should not be used where the nature of the alignment can be described using a simple property, for example to express that a resource [[teaches]] or [[assesses]] a competency.

https://schema.org/ReservationPackage.label: ReservationPackage
https://schema.org/ReservationPackage.description: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

https://schema.org/PhysicalTherapy.label: PhysicalTherapy
https://schema.org/PhysicalTherapy.description: A process of progressive physical care and rehabilitation aimed at improving a health condition.

https://schema.org/usesHealthPlanIdStand.label: usesHealthPlanIdStandard
https://schema.org/usesHealthPlanIdStand.description: The standard for interpreting the Plan ID. The preferred is "HIOS". See the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services for more details.

https://schema.org/TechArticle.label: TechArticle
https://schema.org/TechArticle.description: A technical article - Example: How-to (task) topics, step-by-step, procedural troubleshooting, specifications, etc.

https://schema.org/Brand.label: Brand
https://schema.org/Brand.description: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

https://schema.org/serialNumber.label: serialNumber
https://schema.org/serialNumber.description: The serial number or any alphanumeric identifier of a particular product. When attached to an offer, it is a shortcut for the serial number of the product included in the offer.

https://schema.org/MedicalRiskEstimator.label: MedicalRiskEstimator
https://schema.org/MedicalRiskEstimator.description: Any rule set or interactive tool for estimating the risk of developing a complication or condition.

https://schema.org/previousStartDate.label: previousStartDate
https://schema.org/previousStartDate.description: Used in conjunction with eventStatus for rescheduled or cancelled events. This property contains the previously scheduled start date. For rescheduled events, the startDate property should be used for the newly scheduled start date. In the (rare) case of an event that has been postponed and rescheduled multiple times, this field may be repeated.

https://schema.org/OfferForLease.label: OfferForLease
https://schema.org/OfferForLease.description:
An [[OfferForLease]] in Schema.org represents an [[Offer]] to lease out something, i.e. an [[Offer]] whose
  [[businessFunction]] is [lease out](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut.). See [Good Relations](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GoodRelations) for
  background on the underlying concepts.

https://schema.org/credentialCategory.label: credentialCategory
https://schema.org/credentialCategory.description: The category or type of credential being described, for example "degree”, “certificate”, “badge”, or more specific term.

https://schema.org/CreateAction.label: CreateAction
https://schema.org/CreateAction.description: The act of deliberately creating/producing/generating/building a result out of the agent.

https://schema.org/MarryAction.label: MarryAction
https://schema.org/MarryAction.description: The act of marrying a person.

https://schema.org/InvestmentFund.label: InvestmentFund
https://schema.org/InvestmentFund.description: A company or fund that gathers capital from a number of investors to create a pool of money that is then re-invested into stocks, bonds and other assets.

https://schema.org/gameLocation.label: gameLocation
https://schema.org/gameLocation.description: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).

https://schema.org/RsvpAction.label: RsvpAction
https://schema.org/RsvpAction.description: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

https://schema.org/Thing.label: Thing
https://schema.org/Thing.description: The most generic type of item.

https://schema.org/incentiveStatus.label: incentiveStatus
https://schema.org/incentiveStatus.description: The status of the incentive (active, on hold, retired, etc.).

https://schema.org/hasCourse.label: hasCourse
https://schema.org/hasCourse.description: A course or class that is one of the learning opportunities that constitute an educational / occupational program. No information is implied about whether the course is mandatory or optional; no guarantee is implied about whether the course will be available to everyone on the program.

https://schema.org/EventReservation.label: EventReservation
https://schema.org/EventReservation.description: A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use [[Offer]].

https://schema.org/weightPercentage.label: weightPercentage
https://schema.org/weightPercentage.description: Value in the range [0.0 ; 1.0] representing the fraction of the weight that is used to compute the shipping price.

https://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.label: accessibilityAPI
https://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.description: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API. Values should be drawn from the [approved vocabulary](https://www.w3.org/2021/a11y-discov-vocab/latest/#accessibilityAPI-vocabulary).

https://schema.org/duns.label: duns
https://schema.org/duns.description: The Dun & Bradstreet DUNS number for identifying an organization or business person.

https://schema.org/GovernmentOffice.label: GovernmentOffice
https://schema.org/GovernmentOffice.description: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

https://schema.org/geoTouches.label: geoTouches
https://schema.org/geoTouches.description: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: "they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (A symmetric relationship, as defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).)

https://schema.org/box.label: box
https://schema.org/box.description: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.

https://schema.org/HobbyShop.label: HobbyShop
https://schema.org/HobbyShop.description: A store that sells materials useful or necessary for various hobbies.

https://schema.org/worstRating.label: worstRating
https://schema.org/worstRating.description: The lowest value allowed in this rating system.

https://schema.org/director.label: director
https://schema.org/director.description: A director of e.g. TV, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

https://schema.org/characterName.label: characterName
https://schema.org/characterName.description: The name of a character played in some acting or performing role, i.e. in a PerformanceRole.

https://schema.org/chemicalRole.label: chemicalRole
https://schema.org/chemicalRole.description: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a chemical context.

https://schema.org/diagram.label: diagram
https://schema.org/diagram.description: An image containing a diagram that illustrates the structure and/or its component substructures and/or connections with other structures.

https://schema.org/providesBroadcastServ.label: providesBroadcastService
https://schema.org/providesBroadcastServ.description: The BroadcastService offered on this channel.

https://schema.org/artMedium.label: artMedium
https://schema.org/artMedium.description: The material used. (E.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)

https://schema.org/RecommendedDoseSchedu.label: RecommendedDoseSchedule
https://schema.org/RecommendedDoseSchedu.description: A recommended dosing schedule for a drug or supplement as prescribed or recommended by an authority or by the drug/supplement's manufacturer. Capture the recommending authority in the recognizingAuthority property of MedicalEntity.

https://schema.org/termCode.label: termCode
https://schema.org/termCode.description: A code that identifies this [[DefinedTerm]] within a [[DefinedTermSet]].

https://schema.org/UserPlays.label: UserPlays
https://schema.org/UserPlays.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.label: fuelEfficiency
https://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.description:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

* Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use [[unitText]] to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
* Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, [[fuelConsumption]] (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and [[fuelEfficiency]] (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
* Note 3: Often, the a

https://schema.org/loser.label: loser
https://schema.org/loser.description: A sub property of participant. The loser of the action.

https://schema.org/HealthAspectEnumerati.label: HealthAspectEnumeration
https://schema.org/HealthAspectEnumerati.description: HealthAspectEnumeration enumerates several aspects of health content online, each of which might be described using [[hasHealthAspect]] and [[HealthTopicContent]].

https://schema.org/hasShippingService.label: hasShippingService
https://schema.org/hasShippingService.description: Specification of a shipping service offered by the organization.

https://schema.org/variantCover.label: variantCover
https://schema.org/variantCover.description:
A description of the variant cover
    	for the issue, if the issue is a variant printing. For example, "Bryan Hitch
    	Variant Cover" or "2nd Printing Variant".

https://schema.org/PsychologicalTreatmen.label: PsychologicalTreatment
https://schema.org/PsychologicalTreatmen.description: A process of care relying upon counseling, dialogue and communication  aimed at improving a mental health condition without use of drugs.

https://schema.org/image.label: image
https://schema.org/image.description: An image of the item. This can be a [[URL]] or a fully described [[ImageObject]].

https://schema.org/RadioChannel.label: RadioChannel
https://schema.org/RadioChannel.description: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

https://schema.org/tracks.label: tracks
https://schema.org/tracks.description: A music recording (track)—usually a single song.

https://schema.org/confirmationNumber.label: confirmationNumber
https://schema.org/confirmationNumber.description: A number that confirms the given order or payment has been received.

https://schema.org/totalTime.label: totalTime
https://schema.org/totalTime.description: The total time required to perform instructions or a direction (including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/Review.label: Review
https://schema.org/Review.description: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

https://schema.org/homeLocation.label: homeLocation
https://schema.org/homeLocation.description: A contact location for a person's residence.

https://schema.org/MedicalEvidenceLevel.label: MedicalEvidenceLevel
https://schema.org/MedicalEvidenceLevel.description: Level of evidence for a medical guideline. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/offeredBy.label: offeredBy
https://schema.org/offeredBy.description: A pointer to the organization or person making the offer.

https://schema.org/billingAddress.label: billingAddress
https://schema.org/billingAddress.description: The billing address for the order.

https://schema.org/TherapeuticProcedure.label: TherapeuticProcedure
https://schema.org/TherapeuticProcedure.description: A medical procedure intended primarily for therapeutic purposes, aimed at improving a health condition.

https://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.label: accessibilitySummary
https://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.description: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed".

https://schema.org/embeddedTextCaption.label: embeddedTextCaption
https://schema.org/embeddedTextCaption.description: Represents textual captioning from a [[MediaObject]], e.g. text of a 'meme'.

https://schema.org/exampleOfWork.label: exampleOfWork
https://schema.org/exampleOfWork.description: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.

https://schema.org/CourseInstance.label: CourseInstance
https://schema.org/CourseInstance.description: An instance of a [[Course]] which is distinct from other instances because it is offered at a different time or location or through different media or modes of study or to a specific section of students.

https://schema.org/MedicalSpecialty.label: MedicalSpecialty
https://schema.org/MedicalSpecialty.description: Any specific branch of medical science or practice. Medical specialities include clinical specialties that pertain to particular organ systems and their respective disease states, as well as allied health specialties. Enumerated type.

https://schema.org/BackgroundNewsArticle.label: BackgroundNewsArticle
https://schema.org/BackgroundNewsArticle.description: A [[NewsArticle]] providing historical context, definition and detail on a specific topic (aka "explainer" or "backgrounder"). For example, an in-depth article or frequently-asked-questions ([FAQ](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)) document on topics such as Climate Change or the European Union. Other kinds of background material from a non-news setting are often described using [[Book]] or [[Article]], in particular [[ScholarlyArticle]]. See also [[NewsArticle]] for related vocabulary from a l

https://schema.org/publication.label: publication
https://schema.org/publication.description: A publication event associated with the item.

https://schema.org/MonetaryAmount.label: MonetaryAmount
https://schema.org/MonetaryAmount.description: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use [[PriceSpecification]] Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

https://schema.org/MobilePhoneStore.label: MobilePhoneStore
https://schema.org/MobilePhoneStore.description: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.

https://schema.org/reviewBody.label: reviewBody
https://schema.org/reviewBody.description: The actual body of the review.

https://schema.org/ActivateAction.label: ActivateAction
https://schema.org/ActivateAction.description: The act of starting or activating a device or application (e.g. starting a timer or turning on a flashlight).

https://schema.org/CheckOutAction.label: CheckOutAction
https://schema.org/CheckOutAction.description:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their departure of a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check-in) or place (e.g. hotel).

Related actions:

* [[CheckInAction]]: The antonym of CheckOutAction.
* [[DepartAction]]: Unlike DepartAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.
* [[CancelAction]]: Unlike CancelAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end

https://schema.org/HowToDirection.label: HowToDirection
https://schema.org/HowToDirection.description: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.

https://schema.org/fundedItem.label: fundedItem
https://schema.org/fundedItem.description: Indicates something directly or indirectly funded or sponsored through a [[Grant]]. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].

https://schema.org/vehicleModelDate.label: vehicleModelDate
https://schema.org/vehicleModelDate.description: The release date of a vehicle model (often used to differentiate versions of the same make and model).

https://schema.org/FoodService.label: FoodService
https://schema.org/FoodService.description: A food service, like breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

https://schema.org/Syllabus.label: Syllabus
https://schema.org/Syllabus.description: A syllabus that describes the material covered in a course, often with several such sections per [[Course]] so that a distinct [[timeRequired]] can be provided for that section of the [[Course]].

https://schema.org/eligibleQuantity.label: eligibleQuantity
https://schema.org/eligibleQuantity.description: The interval and unit of measurement of ordering quantities for which the offer or price specification is valid. This allows e.g. specifying that a certain freight charge is valid only for a certain quantity.

https://schema.org/GovernmentBenefitsTyp.label: GovernmentBenefitsType
https://schema.org/GovernmentBenefitsTyp.description: GovernmentBenefitsType enumerates several kinds of government benefits to support the COVID-19 situation. Note that this structure may not capture all benefits offered.

https://schema.org/UserDownloads.label: UserDownloads
https://schema.org/UserDownloads.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/MusicPlaylist.label: MusicPlaylist
https://schema.org/MusicPlaylist.description: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

https://schema.org/BodyOfWater.label: BodyOfWater
https://schema.org/BodyOfWater.description: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

https://schema.org/Number.label: Number
https://schema.org/Number.description:
Data type: Number.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/SearchAction.label: SearchAction
https://schema.org/SearchAction.description:
The act of searching for an object.

Related actions:

* [[FindAction]]: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily.

https://schema.org/repeatCount.label: repeatCount
https://schema.org/repeatCount.description: Defines the number of times a recurring [[Event]] will take place.

https://schema.org/pregnancyWarning.label: pregnancyWarning
https://schema.org/pregnancyWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use during pregnancy.

https://schema.org/tripOrigin.label: tripOrigin
https://schema.org/tripOrigin.description: The location of origin of the trip, prior to any destination(s).

https://schema.org/performTime.label: performTime
https://schema.org/performTime.description: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/hasPOS.label: hasPOS
https://schema.org/hasPOS.description: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.

https://schema.org/ReturnLabelSourceEnum.label: ReturnLabelSourceEnumeration
https://schema.org/ReturnLabelSourceEnum.description: Enumerates several types of return labels for product returns.

https://schema.org/bitrate.label: bitrate
https://schema.org/bitrate.description: The bitrate of the media object.

https://schema.org/Substance.label: Substance
https://schema.org/Substance.description: Any matter of defined composition that has discrete existence, whose origin may be biological, mineral or chemical.

https://schema.org/OpinionNewsArticle.label: OpinionNewsArticle
https://schema.org/OpinionNewsArticle.description: An [[OpinionNewsArticle]] is a [[NewsArticle]] that primarily expresses opinions rather than journalistic reporting of news and events. For example, a [[NewsArticle]] consisting of a column or [[Blog]]/[[BlogPosting]] entry in the Opinions section of a news publication.

https://schema.org/TouristTrip.label: TouristTrip
https://schema.org/TouristTrip.description:
A tourist trip. A created itinerary of visits to one or more places of interest ([[TouristAttraction]]/[[TouristDestination]]) often linked by a similar theme, geographic area, or interest to a particular [[touristType]]. The [UNWTO](http://www2.unwto.org/) defines tourism trip as the Trip taken by visitors.
  (See examples below.)

https://schema.org/ContactPoint.label: ContactPoint
https://schema.org/ContactPoint.description: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

https://schema.org/busName.label: busName
https://schema.org/busName.description: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

https://schema.org/softwareAddOn.label: softwareAddOn
https://schema.org/softwareAddOn.description: Additional content for a software application.

https://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePar.label: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor
https://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePar.description: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.

https://schema.org/foodWarning.label: foodWarning
https://schema.org/foodWarning.description: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.

https://schema.org/paymentAccepted.label: paymentAccepted
https://schema.org/paymentAccepted.description: Cash, Credit Card, Cryptocurrency, Local Exchange Tradings System, etc.

https://schema.org/MobileApplication.label: MobileApplication
https://schema.org/MobileApplication.description: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

https://schema.org/driveWheelConfigurati.label: driveWheelConfiguration
https://schema.org/driveWheelConfigurati.description: The drive wheel configuration, i.e. which roadwheels will receive torque from the vehicle's engine via the drivetrain.

https://schema.org/seatNumber.label: seatNumber
https://schema.org/seatNumber.description: The location of the reserved seat (e.g., 27).

https://schema.org/departureBusStop.label: departureBusStop
https://schema.org/departureBusStop.description: The stop or station from which the bus departs.

https://schema.org/Statement.label: Statement
https://schema.org/Statement.description: A statement about something, for example a fun or interesting fact. If known, the main entity this statement is about can be indicated using mainEntity. For more formal claims (e.g. in Fact Checking), consider using [[Claim]] instead. Use the [[text]] property to capture the text of the statement.

https://schema.org/ReviewNewsArticle.label: ReviewNewsArticle
https://schema.org/ReviewNewsArticle.description: A [[NewsArticle]] and [[CriticReview]] providing a professional critic's assessment of a service, product, performance, or artistic or literary work.

https://schema.org/medicineSystem.label: medicineSystem
https://schema.org/medicineSystem.description: The system of medicine that includes this MedicalEntity, for example 'evidence-based', 'homeopathic', 'chiropractic', etc.

https://schema.org/MedicalContraindicati.label: MedicalContraindication
https://schema.org/MedicalContraindicati.description: A condition or factor that serves as a reason to withhold a certain medical therapy. Contraindications can be absolute (there are no reasonable circumstances for undertaking a course of action) or relative (the patient is at higher risk of complications, but these risks may be outweighed by other considerations or mitigated by other measures).

https://schema.org/WarrantyScope.label: WarrantyScope
https://schema.org/WarrantyScope.description:
A range of services that will be provided to a customer free of charge in case of a defect or malfunction of a product.

Commonly used values:

* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Labor-BringIn
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-BringIn
* http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PartsAndLabor-PickUp

https://schema.org/disambiguatingDescrip.label: disambiguatingDescription
https://schema.org/disambiguatingDescrip.description: A sub property of description. A short description of the item used to disambiguate from other, similar items. Information from other properties (in particular, name) may be necessary for the description to be useful for disambiguation.

https://schema.org/responsibilities.label: responsibilities
https://schema.org/responsibilities.description: Responsibilities associated with this role or Occupation.

https://schema.org/DefinedTermSet.label: DefinedTermSet
https://schema.org/DefinedTermSet.description: A set of defined terms, for example a set of categories or a classification scheme, a glossary, dictionary or enumeration. Use the about property to specify what the term set is about.

https://schema.org/isLocatedInSubcellula.label: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation
https://schema.org/isLocatedInSubcellula.description: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.

https://schema.org/device.label: device
https://schema.org/device.description: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.

https://schema.org/countriesNotSupported.label: countriesNotSupported
https://schema.org/countriesNotSupported.description: Countries for which the application is not supported. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.

https://schema.org/DatedMoneySpecificati.label: DatedMoneySpecification
https://schema.org/DatedMoneySpecificati.description: A DatedMoneySpecification represents monetary values with optional start and end dates. For example, this could represent an employee's salary over a specific period of time. __Note:__ This type has been superseded by [[MonetaryAmount]], use of that type is recommended.

https://schema.org/position.label: position
https://schema.org/position.description: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

https://schema.org/relatedLink.label: relatedLink
https://schema.org/relatedLink.description: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.

https://schema.org/MediaManipulationRati.label: MediaManipulationRatingEnumeration
https://schema.org/MediaManipulationRati.description: Codes for use with the [[mediaAuthenticityCategory]] property, indicating the authenticity of a media object (in the context of how it was published or shared). In general these codes are not mutually exclusive, although some combinations (such as 'original' versus 'transformed', 'edited' and 'staged') would be contradictory if applied in the same [[MediaReview]]. Note that the application of these codes is with regard to a piece of media shared or published in a particular context.

https://schema.org/validThrough.label: validThrough
https://schema.org/validThrough.description: The date after when the item is not valid. For example the end of an offer, salary period, or a period of opening hours.

https://schema.org/tissueSample.label: tissueSample
https://schema.org/tissueSample.description: The type of tissue sample required for the test.

https://schema.org/hasGS1DigitalLink.label: hasGS1DigitalLink
https://schema.org/hasGS1DigitalLink.description:
The GS1 digital link associated with the object. This URL should conform to the particular requirements of digital links. The link should only contain the Application Identifiers (AIs) that are relevant for the entity being annotated, for instance a [[Product]] or an [[Organization]], and for the correct granularity. In particular, for products:
  • A Digital Link that contains a serial number (AI 21) should only be pre

https://schema.org/conditionsOfAccess.label: conditionsOfAccess
https://schema.org/conditionsOfAccess.description: Conditions that affect the availability of, or method(s) of access to, an item. Typically used for real world items such as an [[ArchiveComponent]] held by an [[ArchiveOrganization]]. This property is not suitable for use as a general Web access control mechanism. It is expressed only in natural language.\n\nFor example "Available by appointment from the Reading Room" or "Accessible only from logged-in accounts ".

https://schema.org/mainEntity.label: mainEntity
https://schema.org/mainEntity.description: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/copyrightYear.label: copyrightYear
https://schema.org/copyrightYear.description: The year during which the claimed copyright for the CreativeWork was first asserted.

https://schema.org/acrissCode.label: acrissCode
https://schema.org/acrissCode.description: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.

https://schema.org/additionalName.label: additionalName
https://schema.org/additionalName.description: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.

https://schema.org/PaymentChargeSpecific.label: PaymentChargeSpecification
https://schema.org/PaymentChargeSpecific.description: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

https://schema.org/text.label: text
https://schema.org/text.description: The textual content of this CreativeWork.
https://schema.org/text.usage_hint: The textual content of a CreativeWork (including Quotation). Use this for the actual quote text in a Quotation.
https://schema.org/text.example_keywords: text content, quote text, body, content, words, the actual text

https://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineContr.label: MedicalGuidelineContraindication
https://schema.org/MedicalGuidelineContr.description: A guideline contraindication that designates a process as harmful and where quality of the data supporting the contraindication is sound.

https://schema.org/contentUrl.label: contentUrl
https://schema.org/contentUrl.description: Actual bytes of the media object, for example the image file or video file.

https://schema.org/Rating.label: Rating
https://schema.org/Rating.description: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

https://schema.org/LodgingReservation.label: LodgingReservation
https://schema.org/LodgingReservation.description: A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.\n\nNote: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

https://schema.org/seatRow.label: seatRow
https://schema.org/seatRow.description: The row location of the reserved seat (e.g., B).

https://schema.org/cashBack.label: cashBack
https://schema.org/cashBack.description: A cardholder benefit that pays the cardholder a small percentage of their net expenditures.

https://schema.org/TipAction.label: TipAction
https://schema.org/TipAction.description: The act of giving money voluntarily to a beneficiary in recognition of services rendered.

https://schema.org/OwnershipInfo.label: OwnershipInfo
https://schema.org/OwnershipInfo.description: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

https://schema.org/reservedTicket.label: reservedTicket
https://schema.org/reservedTicket.description: A ticket associated with the reservation.

https://schema.org/tickerSymbol.label: tickerSymbol
https://schema.org/tickerSymbol.description: The exchange traded instrument associated with a Corporation object. The tickerSymbol is expressed as an exchange and an instrument name separated by a space character. For the exchange component of the tickerSymbol attribute, we recommend using the controlled vocabulary of Market Identifier Codes (MIC) specified in ISO 15022.

https://schema.org/defaultValue.label: defaultValue
https://schema.org/defaultValue.description: The default value of the input.  For properties that expect a literal, the default is a literal value, for properties that expect an object, it's an ID reference to one of the current values.

https://schema.org/childTaxon.label: childTaxon
https://schema.org/childTaxon.description: Closest child taxa of the taxon in question.

https://schema.org/PathologyTest.label: PathologyTest
https://schema.org/PathologyTest.description: A medical test performed by a laboratory that typically involves examination of a tissue sample by a pathologist.

https://schema.org/releaseDate.label: releaseDate
https://schema.org/releaseDate.description: The release date of a product or product model. This can be used to distinguish the exact variant of a product.

https://schema.org/MedicalClinic.label: MedicalClinic
https://schema.org/MedicalClinic.description: A facility, often associated with a hospital or medical school, that is devoted to the specific diagnosis and/or healthcare. Previously limited to outpatients but with evolution it may be open to inpatients as well.

https://schema.org/preparation.label: preparation
https://schema.org/preparation.description: Typical preparation that a patient must undergo before having the procedure performed.

https://schema.org/interpretedAsClaim.label: interpretedAsClaim
https://schema.org/interpretedAsClaim.description: Used to indicate a specific claim contained, implied, translated or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]] or other [[CreativeWork]]. The interpreting party can be indicated using [[claimInterpreter]].

https://schema.org/procedure.label: procedure
https://schema.org/procedure.description: A description of the procedure involved in setting up, using, and/or installing the device.

https://schema.org/diagnosis.label: diagnosis
https://schema.org/diagnosis.description: One or more alternative conditions considered in the differential diagnosis process as output of a diagnosis process.

https://schema.org/callSign.label: callSign
https://schema.org/callSign.description: A [callsign](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Call_sign), as used in broadcasting and radio communications to identify people, radio and TV stations, or vehicles.

https://schema.org/cookTime.label: cookTime
https://schema.org/cookTime.description: The time it takes to actually cook the dish, in [ISO 8601 duration format](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601).

https://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.label: hasOfferCatalog
https://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.description: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.

https://schema.org/isPartOf.label: isPartOf
https://schema.org/isPartOf.description: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

https://schema.org/LikeAction.label: LikeAction
https://schema.org/LikeAction.description: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

https://schema.org/legislationChanges.label: legislationChanges
https://schema.org/legislationChanges.description: Another legislation that this legislation changes. This encompasses the notions of amendment, replacement, correction, repeal, or other types of change. This may be a direct change (textual or non-textual amendment) or a consequential or indirect change. The property is to be used to express the existence of a change relationship between two acts rather than the existence of a consolidated version of the text that shows the result of the change. For consolidation relationships, use the <a href="

https://schema.org/deathPlace.label: deathPlace
https://schema.org/deathPlace.description: The place where the person died.

https://schema.org/claimInterpreter.label: claimInterpreter
https://schema.org/claimInterpreter.description: For a [[Claim]] interpreted from [[MediaObject]] content, the [[interpretedAsClaim]] property can be used to indicate a claim contained, implied or refined from the content of a [[MediaObject]].

https://schema.org/landlord.label: landlord
https://schema.org/landlord.description: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.

https://schema.org/antagonist.label: antagonist
https://schema.org/antagonist.description: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.

https://schema.org/nonprofitStatus.label: nonprofitStatus
https://schema.org/nonprofitStatus.description: nonprofitStatus indicates the legal status of a non-profit organization in its primary place of business.

https://schema.org/transmissionMethod.label: transmissionMethod
https://schema.org/transmissionMethod.description: How the disease spreads, either as a route or vector, for example 'direct contact', 'Aedes aegypti', etc.

https://schema.org/VitalSign.label: VitalSign
https://schema.org/VitalSign.description: Vital signs are measures of various physiological functions in order to assess the most basic body functions.

https://schema.org/UKNonprofitType.label: UKNonprofitType
https://schema.org/UKNonprofitType.description: UKNonprofitType: Non-profit organization type originating from the United Kingdom.

https://schema.org/itemListOrder.label: itemListOrder
https://schema.org/itemListOrder.description: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).

https://schema.org/UserLikes.label: UserLikes
https://schema.org/UserLikes.description: UserInteraction and its subtypes is an old way of talking about users interacting with pages. It is generally better to use [[Action]]-based vocabulary, alongside types such as [[Comment]].

https://schema.org/shippingRate.label: shippingRate
https://schema.org/shippingRate.description: The shipping rate is the cost of shipping to the specified destination. Typically, the maxValue and currency values (of the [[MonetaryAmount]]) are most appropriate.

https://schema.org/termDuration.label: termDuration
