https://schema.org/termDuration.description: The amount of time in a term as defined by the institution. A term is a length of time where students take one or more classes. Semesters and quarters are common units for term.

https://schema.org/linkRelationship.label: linkRelationship
https://schema.org/linkRelationship.description: Indicates the relationship type of a Web link.

https://schema.org/httpMethod.label: httpMethod
https://schema.org/httpMethod.description: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.

https://schema.org/numberOfBathroomsTota.label: numberOfBathroomsTotal
https://schema.org/numberOfBathroomsTota.description: The total integer number of bathrooms in some [[Accommodation]], following real estate conventions as [documented in RESO](https://ddwiki.reso.org/display/DDW17/BathroomsTotalInteger+Field): "The simple sum of the number of bathrooms. For example for a property with two Full Bathrooms and one Half Bathroom, the Bathrooms Total Integer will be 3.". See also [[numberOfRooms]].

https://schema.org/browserRequirements.label: browserRequirements
https://schema.org/browserRequirements.description: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.

https://schema.org/FindAction.label: FindAction
https://schema.org/FindAction.description:
The act of finding an object.

Related actions:

* [[SearchAction]]: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

https://schema.org/priceSpecification.label: priceSpecification
https://schema.org/priceSpecification.description: One or more detailed price specifications, indicating the unit price and delivery or payment charges.

https://schema.org/numberOfAxles.label: numberOfAxles
https://schema.org/numberOfAxles.description: The number of axles.\n\nTypical unit code(s): C62.

https://schema.org/exercisePlan.label: exercisePlan
https://schema.org/exercisePlan.description: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.

https://schema.org/arrivalGate.label: arrivalGate
https://schema.org/arrivalGate.description: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.

https://schema.org/speechToTextMarkup.label: speechToTextMarkup
https://schema.org/speechToTextMarkup.description: Form of markup used. eg. [SSML](https://www.w3.org/TR/speech-synthesis11) or [IPA](https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Property:P898).

https://schema.org/DepositAccount.label: DepositAccount
https://schema.org/DepositAccount.description: A type of Bank Account with a main purpose of depositing funds to gain interest or other benefits.

https://schema.org/geoCrosses.label: geoCrosses
https://schema.org/geoCrosses.description: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in [DE-9IM](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DE-9IM).

https://schema.org/earlyPrepaymentPenalt.label: earlyPrepaymentPenalty
https://schema.org/earlyPrepaymentPenalt.description: The amount to be paid as a penalty in the event of early payment of the loan.

https://schema.org/AskPublicNewsArticle.label: AskPublicNewsArticle
https://schema.org/AskPublicNewsArticle.description: A [[NewsArticle]] expressing an open call by a [[NewsMediaOrganization]] asking the public for input, insights, clarifications, anecdotes, documentation, etc., on an issue, for reporting purposes.

https://schema.org/QuoteAction.label: QuoteAction
https://schema.org/QuoteAction.description: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

https://schema.org/educationalLevel.label: educationalLevel
https://schema.org/educationalLevel.description: The level in terms of progression through an educational or training context. Examples of educational levels include 'beginner', 'intermediate' or 'advanced', and formal sets of level indicators.

https://schema.org/AMRadioChannel.label: AMRadioChannel
https://schema.org/AMRadioChannel.description: A radio channel that uses AM.

https://schema.org/variesBy.label: variesBy
https://schema.org/variesBy.description: Indicates the property or properties by which the variants in a [[ProductGroup]] vary, e.g. their size, color etc. Schema.org properties can be referenced by their short name e.g. "color"; terms defined elsewhere can be referenced with their URIs.

https://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.label: broadcastDisplayName
https://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.description: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.

https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnFees.label: itemDefectReturnFees
https://schema.org/itemDefectReturnFees.description: The type of return fees for returns of defect products.

https://schema.org/AccountingService.label: AccountingService
https://schema.org/AccountingService.description: Accountancy business.\n\nAs a [[LocalBusiness]] it can be described as a [[provider]] of one or more [[Service]]\(s).

https://schema.org/administrationRoute.label: administrationRoute
https://schema.org/administrationRoute.description: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.

https://schema.org/eventSchedule.label: eventSchedule
https://schema.org/eventSchedule.description:
Associates an [[Event]] with a [[Schedule]]. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of
      repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly
      gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An [[Event]] that
      is associated with a [[Schedule]] using t

https://schema.org/toLocation.label: toLocation
https://schema.org/toLocation.description: A sub property of location. The final location of the object or the agent after the action.

https://schema.org/SearchResultsPage.label: SearchResultsPage
https://schema.org/SearchResultsPage.description: Web page type: Search results page.

https://schema.org/applicantLocationRequ.label: applicantLocationRequirements
https://schema.org/applicantLocationRequ.description: The location(s) applicants can apply from. This is usually used for telecommuting jobs where the applicant does not need to be in a physical office. Note: This should not be used for citizenship or work visa requirements.

https://schema.org/postalCodePrefix.label: postalCodePrefix
https://schema.org/postalCodePrefix.description: A defined range of postal codes indicated by a common textual prefix. Used for non-numeric systems such as UK.

https://schema.org/sizeSystem.label: sizeSystem
https://schema.org/sizeSystem.description: The size system used to identify a product's size. Typically either a standard (for example, "GS1" or "ISO-EN13402"), country code (for example "US" or "JP"), or a measuring system (for example "Metric" or "Imperial").

https://schema.org/founders.label: founders
https://schema.org/founders.description: A person who founded this organization.

https://schema.org/articleSection.label: articleSection
https://schema.org/articleSection.description: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.

https://schema.org/AdultOrientedEnumerat.label: AdultOrientedEnumeration
https://schema.org/AdultOrientedEnumerat.description: Enumeration of considerations that make a product relevant or potentially restricted for adults only.

https://schema.org/subStageSuffix.label: subStageSuffix
https://schema.org/subStageSuffix.description: The substage, e.g. 'a' for Stage IIIa.

https://schema.org/regionDrained.label: regionDrained
https://schema.org/regionDrained.description: The anatomical or organ system drained by this vessel; generally refers to a specific part of an organ.

https://schema.org/Periodical.label: Periodical
https://schema.org/Periodical.description: A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended to continue indefinitely, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

https://schema.org/IndividualPhysician.label: IndividualPhysician
https://schema.org/IndividualPhysician.description:
An individual medical practitioner. For their official address use [[address]], for affiliations to hospitals use [[hospitalAffiliation]]. 
The [[practicesAt]] property can be used to indicate [[MedicalOrganization]] hospitals, clinics, pharmacies etc. where this physician practices.

https://schema.org/applicationContact.label: applicationContact
https://schema.org/applicationContact.description: Contact details for further information relevant to this job posting.

https://schema.org/numAdults.label: numAdults
https://schema.org/numAdults.description: The number of adults staying in the unit.

https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.label: customerRemorseReturnLabelSource
https://schema.org/customerRemorseReturn.description: The method (from an enumeration) by which the customer obtains a return shipping label for a product returned due to customer remorse.

https://schema.org/WearAction.label: WearAction
https://schema.org/WearAction.description: The act of dressing oneself in clothing.

https://schema.org/activityDuration.label: activityDuration
https://schema.org/activityDuration.description: Length of time to engage in the activity.

https://schema.org/validFor.label: validFor
https://schema.org/validFor.description: The duration of validity of a permit or similar thing.

https://schema.org/primaryImageOfPage.label: primaryImageOfPage
https://schema.org/primaryImageOfPage.description: Indicates the main image on the page.

https://schema.org/penciler.label: penciler
https://schema.org/penciler.description: The individual who draws the primary narrative artwork.

https://schema.org/MedicalTest.label: MedicalTest
https://schema.org/MedicalTest.description: Any medical test, typically performed for diagnostic purposes.

https://schema.org/errorCode.label: errorCode
https://schema.org/errorCode.description: Application or platform dependant error code.

https://schema.org/sender.label: sender
https://schema.org/sender.description: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the sending end of the action.

https://schema.org/bestRating.label: bestRating
https://schema.org/bestRating.description: The highest value allowed in this rating system.

https://schema.org/character.label: character
https://schema.org/character.description: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

https://schema.org/MedicalSymptom.label: MedicalSymptom
https://schema.org/MedicalSymptom.description: Any complaint sensed and expressed by the patient (therefore defined as subjective)  like stomachache, lower-back pain, or fatigue.

https://schema.org/spouse.label: spouse
https://schema.org/spouse.usage_hint: Spouse of a person. For marriage dates, use Role pattern.
https://schema.org/spouse.example_keywords: married to, spouse, husband, wife, partner

https://schema.org/copyrightHolder.label: copyrightHolder
https://schema.org/copyrightHolder.description: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

https://schema.org/FAQPage.label: FAQPage
https://schema.org/FAQPage.description: A [[FAQPage]] is a [[WebPage]] presenting one or more "[Frequently asked questions](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FAQ)" (see also [[QAPage]]).

https://schema.org/runtimePlatform.label: runtimePlatform
https://schema.org/runtimePlatform.description: Runtime platform or script interpreter dependencies (example: Java v1, Python 2.3, .NET Framework 3.0).

https://schema.org/target.label: target
https://schema.org/target.description: Indicates a target EntryPoint, or url, for an Action.

https://schema.org/free.label: free
https://schema.org/free.description: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.

https://schema.org/benefits.label: benefits
https://schema.org/benefits.description: Description of benefits associated with the job.

https://schema.org/TrackAction.label: TrackAction
https://schema.org/TrackAction.description:
An agent tracks an object for updates.

Related actions:

* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, TrackAction refers to the interest on the location of innanimates objects.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, TrackAction refers to  the interest on the location of innanimate objects.

https://schema.org/securityClearanceRequ.label: securityClearanceRequirement
https://schema.org/securityClearanceRequ.description: A description of any security clearance requirements of the job.

https://schema.org/gameAvailabilityType.label: gameAvailabilityType
https://schema.org/gameAvailabilityType.description: Indicates the availability type of the game content associated with this action, such as whether it is a full version or a demo.

https://schema.org/specialCommitments.label: specialCommitments
https://schema.org/specialCommitments.description: Any special commitments associated with this job posting. Valid entries include VeteranCommit, MilitarySpouseCommit, etc.

https://schema.org/departureStation.label: departureStation
https://schema.org/departureStation.description: The station from which the train departs.

https://schema.org/issuedBy.label: issuedBy
https://schema.org/issuedBy.description: The organization issuing the item, for example a [[Permit]], [[Ticket]], or [[Certification]].

https://schema.org/backstory.label: backstory
https://schema.org/backstory.description: For an [[Article]], typically a [[NewsArticle]], the backstory property provides a textual summary giving a brief explanation of why and how an article was created. In a journalistic setting this could include information about reporting process, methods, interviews, data sources, etc.

https://schema.org/AudioObjectSnapshot.label: AudioObjectSnapshot
https://schema.org/AudioObjectSnapshot.description: A specific and exact (byte-for-byte) version of an [[AudioObject]]. Two byte-for-byte identical files, for the purposes of this type, considered identical. If they have different embedded metadata the files will differ. Different external facts about the files, e.g. creator or dateCreated that aren't represented in their actual content, do not affect this notion of identity.

https://schema.org/dateModified.label: dateModified
https://schema.org/dateModified.description: The date on which the CreativeWork was most recently modified or when the item's entry was modified within a DataFeed.

https://schema.org/DayOfWeek.label: DayOfWeek
https://schema.org/DayOfWeek.description:
The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer.

Originally, URLs from [GoodRelations](http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1) were used (for [[Monday]], [[Tuesday]], [[Wednesday]], [[Thursday]], [[Friday]], [[Saturday]], [[Sunday]] plus a special entry for [[PublicHolidays]]); these have now been integrated directly into schema.org.

https://schema.org/departureTerminal.label: departureTerminal
https://schema.org/departureTerminal.description: Identifier of the flight's departure terminal.

https://schema.org/OfferCatalog.label: OfferCatalog
https://schema.org/OfferCatalog.description: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

https://schema.org/Distance.label: Distance
https://schema.org/Distance.description: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

https://schema.org/BorrowAction.label: BorrowAction
https://schema.org/BorrowAction.description:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.

Related actions:

* [[LendAction]]: Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

https://schema.org/resultComment.label: resultComment
https://schema.org/resultComment.description: A sub property of result. The Comment created or sent as a result of this action.

https://schema.org/mediaItemAppearance.label: mediaItemAppearance
https://schema.org/mediaItemAppearance.description: In the context of a [[MediaReview]], indicates specific media item(s) that are grouped using a [[MediaReviewItem]].

https://schema.org/aspect.label: aspect
https://schema.org/aspect.description: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.

https://schema.org/currentExchangeRate.label: currentExchangeRate
https://schema.org/currentExchangeRate.description: The current price of a currency.

https://schema.org/availabilityEnds.label: availabilityEnds
https://schema.org/availabilityEnds.description: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.

https://schema.org/priceValidUntil.label: priceValidUntil
https://schema.org/priceValidUntil.description: The date after which the price is no longer available.

https://schema.org/Article.label: Article
https://schema.org/Article.description: An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.\n\nSee also [blog post](https://blog.schema.org/2014/09/02/schema-org-support-for-bibliographic-relationships-and-periodicals/).

https://schema.org/ActionAccessSpecifica.label: ActionAccessSpecification
https://schema.org/ActionAccessSpecifica.description: A set of requirements that must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action.

https://schema.org/TouristAttraction.label: TouristAttraction
https://schema.org/TouristAttraction.description: A tourist attraction.  In principle any Thing can be a [[TouristAttraction]], from a [[Mountain]] and [[LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings]] to a [[LocalBusiness]].  This Type can be used on its own to describe a general [[TouristAttraction]], or be used as an [[additionalType]] to add tourist attraction properties to any other type.  (See examples below)

https://schema.org/includedInHealthInsur.label: includedInHealthInsurancePlan
https://schema.org/includedInHealthInsur.description: The insurance plans that cover this drug.

https://schema.org/hasTierRequirement.label: hasTierRequirement
https://schema.org/hasTierRequirement.description: A requirement for a user to join a membership tier, for example: a CreditCard if the tier requires sign up for a credit card, A UnitPriceSpecification if the user is required to pay a (periodic) fee, or a MonetaryAmount if the user needs to spend a minimum amount to join the tier. If a tier is free to join then this property does not need to be specified.

https://schema.org/afterMedia.label: afterMedia
https://schema.org/afterMedia.description: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.

https://schema.org/availableAtOrFrom.label: availableAtOrFrom
https://schema.org/availableAtOrFrom.description: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

https://schema.org/EntryPoint.label: EntryPoint
https://schema.org/EntryPoint.description: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

https://schema.org/Thesis.label: Thesis
https://schema.org/Thesis.description: A thesis or dissertation document submitted in support of candidature for an academic degree or professional qualification.

https://schema.org/StatusEnumeration.label: StatusEnumeration
https://schema.org/StatusEnumeration.description: Lists or enumerations dealing with status types.

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OverflowPats.label: cvdNumC19OverflowPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19OverflowPats.description: numc19overflowpats - ED/OVERFLOW: Patients with suspected or confirmed COVID-19 who are in the ED or any overflow location awaiting an inpatient bed.

https://schema.org/sensoryUnit.label: sensoryUnit
https://schema.org/sensoryUnit.description: The neurological pathway extension that inputs and sends information to the brain or spinal cord.

https://schema.org/cvdNumTotBeds.label: cvdNumTotBeds
https://schema.org/cvdNumTotBeds.description: numtotbeds - ALL HOSPITAL BEDS: Total number of all inpatient and outpatient beds, including all staffed, ICU, licensed, and overflow (surge) beds used for inpatients or outpatients.

https://schema.org/healthcareReportingDa.label: healthcareReportingData
https://schema.org/healthcareReportingDa.description: Indicates data describing a hospital, e.g. a CDC [[CDCPMDRecord]] or as some kind of [[Dataset]].

https://schema.org/Nerve.label: Nerve
https://schema.org/Nerve.description: A common pathway for the electrochemical nerve impulses that are transmitted along each of the axons.

https://schema.org/dissolutionDate.label: dissolutionDate
https://schema.org/dissolutionDate.description: The date that this organization was dissolved.

https://schema.org/MeetingRoom.label: MeetingRoom
https://schema.org/MeetingRoom.description:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

https://schema.org/cutoffTime.label: cutoffTime
https://schema.org/cutoffTime.description: Order cutoff time allows merchants to describe the time after which they will no longer process orders received on that day. For orders processed after cutoff time, one day gets added to the delivery time estimate. This property is expected to be most typically used via the [[ShippingRateSettings]] publication pattern. The time is indicated using the ISO-8601 Time format, e.g. "23:30:00-05:00" would represent 6:30 pm Eastern Standard Time (EST) which is 5 hours behind Coordinated Universal Time

https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HospPats.label: cvdNumC19HospPats
https://schema.org/cvdNumC19HospPats.description: numc19hosppats - HOSPITALIZED: Patients currently hospitalized in an inpatient care location who have suspected or confirmed COVID-19.

https://schema.org/unnamedSourcesPolicy.label: unnamedSourcesPolicy
https://schema.org/unnamedSourcesPolicy.description: For an [[Organization]] (typically a [[NewsMediaOrganization]]), a statement about policy on use of unnamed sources and the decision process required.

https://schema.org/DataFeedItem.label: DataFeedItem
https://schema.org/DataFeedItem.description: A single item within a larger data feed.

https://schema.org/targetName.label: targetName
https://schema.org/targetName.description: The name of a node in an established educational framework.

https://schema.org/estimatedSalary.label: estimatedSalary
https://schema.org/estimatedSalary.description: An estimated salary for a job posting or occupation, based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. Estimated salaries  are often computed by outside organizations rather than the hiring organization, who may not have committed to the estimated value.

https://schema.org/drug.label: drug
https://schema.org/drug.description: Specifying a drug or medicine used in a medication procedure.

https://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.label: annualPercentageRate
https://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.description: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.

https://schema.org/episodes.label: episodes
https://schema.org/episodes.description: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.

https://schema.org/owns.label: owns
https://schema.org/owns.description: Things owned by the organization or person.

https://schema.org/incentiveAmount.label: incentiveAmount
https://schema.org/incentiveAmount.description:
Describes the amount that can be redeemed from this incentive.

[[QuantitativeValue]]: Use this for incentives based on price (either raw amount or percentage-based). For a raw amount example, "You can claim $2,500 - $7,500 from the total cost of installation" would be represented as the following:

{ "@type": "QuantitativeValue", “minValue”: 2500, “maxValue”: 7500, "unitCode": "USD" }

[[QuantitivateValue]] can also be used for percentage amou

https://schema.org/inker.label: inker
https://schema.org/inker.description: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.

https://schema.org/scheduledTime.label: scheduledTime
https://schema.org/scheduledTime.description: The time the object is scheduled to.

https://schema.org/Muscle.label: Muscle
https://schema.org/Muscle.description: A muscle is an anatomical structure consisting of a contractile form of tissue that animals use to effect movement.

https://schema.org/DrugPregnancyCategory.label: DrugPregnancyCategory
https://schema.org/DrugPregnancyCategory.description: Categories that represent an assessment of the risk of fetal injury due to a drug or pharmaceutical used as directed by the mother during pregnancy.

https://schema.org/totalPrice.label: totalPrice
https://schema.org/totalPrice.description:
The total price for the reservation or ticket, including applicable taxes, shipping, etc.

Usage guidelines:

* Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similar Unicode symbols.
* Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

https://schema.org/amenityFeature.label: amenityFeature
https://schema.org/amenityFeature.description: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.

https://schema.org/qualifications.label: qualifications
https://schema.org/qualifications.description: Specific qualifications required for this role or Occupation.

https://schema.org/OperatingSystem.label: OperatingSystem
https://schema.org/OperatingSystem.description: System software that manages computer hardware and software resources, and provides common services for computer programs.

https://schema.org/JoinAction.label: JoinAction
https://schema.org/JoinAction.description:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

* [[RegisterAction]]: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
* [[SubscribeAction]]: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
* [[FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.
